compression_ratio": 1.5709779179810726, "no_speech_prob": 1.0081165503078582e-12}, {"id": 5, "seek": 3000, "start": 30.44, "end": 33.14, "text": " And, you know, how we understand our own physical bodies.", "tokens": [50387, 400, 11, 291, 458, 11, 577, 321, 1223, 527, 1065, 4001, 7510, 13, 50522], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 6, "seek": 3000, "start": 33.38, "end": 34.86, "text": " So welcome to the Deep Dive.", "tokens": [50534, 407, 2928, 281, 264, 14895, 413, 488, 13, 50608], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 7, "seek": 3000, "start": 35.02, "end": 35.58, "text": " Glad to be here.", "tokens": [50616, 28301, 281, 312, 510, 13, 50644], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 8, "seek": 3000, "start": 35.72, "end": 42.2, "text": " We are looking at a highly technical, completely fascinating 2026 monograph by an independent researcher named Flixinen.", "tokens": [50651, 492, 366, 1237, 412, 257, 5405, 6191, 11, 2584, 10343, 945, 10880, 1108, 3108, 538, 364, 6695, 21751, 4926, 3235, 970, 5636, 13, 50975], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 9, "seek": 3000, "start": 42.68, "end": 46.78, "text": " It's titled Hierarchical Continuation and the Geometry of Locomotion.", "tokens": [50999, 467, 311, 19841, 10886, 1178, 804, 14674, 16073, 293, 264, 2876, 34730, 295, 12859, 298, 19228, 13, 51204], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 10, "seek": 3000, "start": 46.78, "end": 47.620000000000005, "text": " That's the one?", "tokens": [51204, 663, 311, 264, 472, 30, 51246], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 11, "seek": 3000, "start": 47.82, "end": 50.94, "text": " I've just been buried in this dense theoretical essay all week.", "tokens": [51256, 286, 600, 445, 668, 14101, 294, 341, 18011, 20864, 16238, 439, 1243, 13, 51412], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 12, "seek": 3000, "start": 51.019999999999996, "end": 54.14, "text": " And the mission today is to really untangle it for you, the listener.", "tokens": [51416, 400, 264, 4447, 965, 307, 281, 534, 1701, 7846, 309, 337, 291, 11, 264, 31569, 13, 51572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 13, "seek": 3000, "start": 54.28, "end": 56.72, "text": " Because it's definitely not light reading.", "tokens": [51579, 1436, 309, 311, 2138, 406, 1442, 3760, 13, 51701], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 14, "seek": 3000, "start": 57.24, "end": 58.34, "text": " No, definitely not.", "tokens": [51727, 883, 11, 2138, 406, 13, 51782], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17370243778935185, "compression_ratio": 1.541033434650456, "no_speech_prob": 7.261721605977822e-13}, {"id": 15, "seek": 5834, "start": 58.34, "end": 60.38, "text": " But why should you care?", "tokens": [50365, 583, 983, 820, 291, 1127, 30, 50467], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 16, "seek": 5834, "start": 60.760000000000005, "end": 64.10000000000001, "text": " Because this isn't just abstract math happening on a chalkboard somewhere.", "tokens": [50486, 1436, 341, 1943, 380, 445, 12649, 5221, 2737, 322, 257, 28660, 3787, 4079, 13, 50653], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 17, "seek": 5834, "start": 64.48, "end": 69.42, "text": " This paper actually challenges the fundamental definition of what it means to be balanced.", "tokens": [50672, 639, 3035, 767, 4759, 264, 8088, 7123, 295, 437, 309, 1355, 281, 312, 13902, 13, 50919], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 18, "seek": 5834, "start": 69.54, "end": 69.72, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50925, 1779, 13, 50934], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 19, "seek": 5834, "start": 69.80000000000001, "end": 71.34, "text": " It completely redefines it.", "tokens": [50938, 467, 2584, 38818, 1652, 309, 13, 51015], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 20, "seek": 5834, "start": 71.44, "end": 71.64, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51020, 865, 13, 51030], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 21, "seek": 5834, "start": 71.78, "end": 75.9, "text": " It suggests that stability isn't a static pose you achieve and just hold.", "tokens": [51037, 467, 13409, 300, 11826, 1943, 380, 257, 13437, 10774, 291, 4584, 293, 445, 1797, 13, 51243], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 22, "seek": 5834, "start": 76.38, "end": 79.80000000000001, "text": " It's actually a continuously rolling wave of rhythms.", "tokens": [51267, 467, 311, 767, 257, 15684, 9439, 5772, 295, 44892, 13, 51438], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 23, "seek": 5834, "start": 80.18, "end": 80.66, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51457, 7587, 13, 51481], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19747238573820694, "compression_ratio": 1.51440329218107, "no_speech_prob": 1.0857202723674186e-12}, {"id": 24, "seek": 8066, "start": 80.66, "end": 87.1, "text": " So the next time you take a step or even just stand still waiting for a bus, you are going to think about your body entirely differently.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 264, 958, 565, 291, 747, 257, 1823, 420, 754, 445, 1463, 920, 3806, 337, 257, 1255, 11, 291, 366, 516, 281, 519, 466, 428, 1772, 7696, 7614, 13, 50687], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11793799627394903, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2545452957729575e-12}, {"id": 25, "seek": 8066, "start": 87.46, "end": 89.92, "text": " The paradigm shift here is just, it's profound.", "tokens": [50705, 440, 24709, 5513, 510, 307, 445, 11, 309, 311, 14382, 13, 50828], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11793799627394903, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2545452957729575e-12}, {"id": 26, "seek": 8066, "start": 89.92, "end": 95.89999999999999, "text": " It completely upends the conventional wisdom of how we describe movement mathematically and biologically.", "tokens": [50828, 467, 2584, 493, 2581, 264, 16011, 10712, 295, 577, 321, 6786, 3963, 44003, 293, 3228, 17157, 13, 51127], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11793799627394903, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2545452957729575e-12}, {"id": 27, "seek": 8066, "start": 96.62, "end": 96.67999999999999, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51163, 865, 13, 51166], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11793799627394903, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2545452957729575e-12}, {"id": 28, "seek": 8066, "start": 96.75999999999999, "end": 101.97999999999999, "text": " And to really grasp the magnitude of what Flixian is proposing, we kind of have to look at the baseline first.", "tokens": [51170, 400, 281, 534, 21743, 264, 15668, 295, 437, 3235, 970, 952, 307, 29939, 11, 321, 733, 295, 362, 281, 574, 412, 264, 20518, 700, 13, 51431], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11793799627394903, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2545452957729575e-12}, {"id": 29, "seek": 8066, "start": 102.1, "end": 102.46, "text": " We do.", "tokens": [51437, 492, 360, 13, 51455], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11793799627394903, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2545452957729575e-12}, {"id": 30, "seek": 8066, "start": 102.6, "end": 102.84, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51462, 865, 13, 51474], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11793799627394903, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2545452957729575e-12}, {"id": 31, "seek": 10284, "start": 102.84, "end": 106.34, "text": " We have to look at what the paper calls the state-centric default.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 362, 281, 574, 412, 437, 264, 3035, 5498, 264, 1785, 12, 45300, 7576, 13, 50540], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1963628370370438, "compression_ratio": 1.405128205128205, "no_speech_prob": 1.2063027443262597e-12}, {"id": 32, "seek": 10284, "start": 106.5, "end": 106.74000000000001, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50548, 1033, 13, 50560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1963628370370438, "compression_ratio": 1.405128205128205, "no_speech_prob": 1.2063027443262597e-12}, {"id": 33, "seek": 10284, "start": 106.92, "end": 110.60000000000001, "text": " Let's unpack this because I found this part incredibly relatable.", "tokens": [50569, 961, 311, 26699, 341, 570, 286, 1352, 341, 644, 6252, 42355, 13, 50753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1963628370370438, "compression_ratio": 1.405128205128205, "no_speech_prob": 1.2063027443262597e-12}, {"id": 34, "seek": 10284, "start": 110.92, "end": 116.56, "text": " It basically describes how almost all modern robotics and computer animation currently work.", "tokens": [50769, 467, 1936, 15626, 577, 1920, 439, 4363, 34145, 293, 3820, 9603, 4362, 589, 13, 51051], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1963628370370438, "compression_ratio": 1.405128205128205, "no_speech_prob": 1.2063027443262597e-12}, {"id": 35, "seek": 10284, "start": 116.84, "end": 118.38000000000001, "text": " It's the industry standard, really.", "tokens": [51065, 467, 311, 264, 3518, 3832, 11, 534, 13, 51142], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1963628370370438, "compression_ratio": 1.405128205128205, "no_speech_prob": 1.2063027443262597e-12}, {"id": 36, "seek": 10284, "start": 118.7, "end": 118.92, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51158, 1779, 13, 51169], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1963628370370438, "compression_ratio": 1.405128205128205, "no_speech_prob": 1.2063027443262597e-12}, {"id": 37, "seek": 11892, "start": 118.92, "end": 123.44, "text": " And when I read about state-centric control, I instantly thought of stop-motion animation.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 562, 286, 1401, 466, 1785, 12, 45300, 1969, 11, 286, 13518, 1194, 295, 1590, 12, 44968, 9603, 13, 50591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 38, "seek": 11892, "start": 124.3, "end": 124.76, "text": " You know, like...", "tokens": [50634, 509, 458, 11, 411, 485, 50657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 39, "seek": 11892, "start": 124.76, "end": 126.26, "text": " Oh, like Wallace and Gromit or something.", "tokens": [50657, 876, 11, 411, 32626, 293, 2606, 298, 270, 420, 746, 13, 50732], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 40, "seek": 11892, "start": 126.38, "end": 126.96000000000001, "text": " Yeah, exactly.", "tokens": [50738, 865, 11, 2293, 13, 50767], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 41, "seek": 11892, "start": 127.06, "end": 128.5, "text": " You have a clay figure on a table.", "tokens": [50772, 509, 362, 257, 13517, 2573, 322, 257, 3199, 13, 50844], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 42, "seek": 11892, "start": 128.78, "end": 136.92000000000002, "text": " If you want it to look like it's walking, you physically move the arm a tiny fraction of an inch, lock it into that state, and take a picture.", "tokens": [50858, 759, 291, 528, 309, 281, 574, 411, 309, 311, 4494, 11, 291, 9762, 1286, 264, 3726, 257, 5870, 14135, 295, 364, 7227, 11, 4017, 309, 666, 300, 1785, 11, 293, 747, 257, 3036, 13, 51265], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 43, "seek": 11892, "start": 137.06, "end": 137.28, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51272, 1779, 13, 51283], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 44, "seek": 11892, "start": 137.52, "end": 141.36, "text": " Then you move it another fraction, lock it into a new state, and take another picture.", "tokens": [51295, 1396, 291, 1286, 309, 1071, 14135, 11, 4017, 309, 666, 257, 777, 1785, 11, 293, 747, 1071, 3036, 13, 51487], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 45, "seek": 11892, "start": 141.62, "end": 145.98000000000002, "text": " The entire process of movement is just a sequence of static poses.", "tokens": [51500, 440, 2302, 1399, 295, 3963, 307, 445, 257, 8310, 295, 13437, 26059, 13, 51718], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12997782931608312, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3778471636208267e-12}, {"id": 46, "seek": 14598, "start": 145.98, "end": 152.12, "text": " And that stop-motion model is the perfect lens for how we currently engineer movement.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 300, 1590, 12, 44968, 2316, 307, 264, 2176, 6765, 337, 577, 321, 4362, 11403, 3963, 13, 50672], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 47, "seek": 14598, "start": 152.26, "end": 152.48, "text": " Really?", "tokens": [50679, 4083, 30, 50690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 48, "seek": 14598, "start": 152.95999999999998, "end": 153.22, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50714, 865, 13, 50727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 49, "seek": 14598, "start": 153.35999999999999, "end": 161.04, "text": " I mean, in applied robotics, if you want a robotic arm to reach for a cup of coffee, the software controller isn't actually thinking about a fluid motion.", "tokens": [50734, 286, 914, 11, 294, 6456, 34145, 11, 498, 291, 528, 257, 30468, 3726, 281, 2524, 337, 257, 4414, 295, 4982, 11, 264, 4722, 10561, 1943, 380, 767, 1953, 466, 257, 9113, 5394, 13, 51118], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 50, "seek": 14598, "start": 161.17999999999998, "end": 161.56, "text": " It's not.", "tokens": [51125, 467, 311, 406, 13, 51144], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 51, "seek": 14598, "start": 161.7, "end": 161.92, "text": " No.", "tokens": [51151, 883, 13, 51162], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 52, "seek": 14598, "start": 162.01999999999998, "end": 165.64, "text": " It is thinking about a target configuration, a pose.", "tokens": [51167, 467, 307, 1953, 466, 257, 3779, 11694, 11, 257, 10774, 13, 51348], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 53, "seek": 14598, "start": 166.12, "end": 171.26, "text": " The software specifies the exact 3D coordinates where that mechanical hand needs to end up.", "tokens": [51372, 440, 4722, 1608, 11221, 264, 1900, 805, 35, 21056, 689, 300, 12070, 1011, 2203, 281, 917, 493, 13, 51629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 54, "seek": 14598, "start": 171.38, "end": 171.57999999999998, "text": " Yep.", "tokens": [51635, 7010, 13, 51645], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1447109875378308, "compression_ratio": 1.5692883895131087, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856275710837697e-12}, {"id": 55, "seek": 17158, "start": 171.58, "end": 176.88000000000002, "text": " Then it uses a computational method called inverse kinematics to make it happen.", "tokens": [50365, 1396, 309, 4960, 257, 28270, 3170, 1219, 17340, 15784, 37541, 281, 652, 309, 1051, 13, 50630], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124258864159677, "compression_ratio": 1.5615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2300942599588471e-12}, {"id": 56, "seek": 17158, "start": 176.96, "end": 178.02, "text": " Boy, inverse kinematics.", "tokens": [50634, 9486, 11, 17340, 15784, 37541, 13, 50687], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124258864159677, "compression_ratio": 1.5615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2300942599588471e-12}, {"id": 57, "seek": 17158, "start": 178.24, "end": 182.18, "text": " I always struggled with that term until I realized it literally just means working backward.", "tokens": [50698, 286, 1009, 19023, 365, 300, 1433, 1826, 286, 5334, 309, 3736, 445, 1355, 1364, 23897, 13, 50895], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124258864159677, "compression_ratio": 1.5615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2300942599588471e-12}, {"id": 58, "seek": 17158, "start": 182.5, "end": 183.76000000000002, "text": " That's exactly what it is.", "tokens": [50911, 663, 311, 2293, 437, 309, 307, 13, 50974], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124258864159677, "compression_ratio": 1.5615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2300942599588471e-12}, {"id": 59, "seek": 17158, "start": 183.88000000000002, "end": 190.42000000000002, "text": " Because the forward way would be saying, you know, my shoulder is at 45 degrees, my elbow is at 90 degrees, so where is my hand?", "tokens": [50980, 1436, 264, 2128, 636, 576, 312, 1566, 11, 291, 458, 11, 452, 7948, 307, 412, 6905, 5310, 11, 452, 18507, 307, 412, 4289, 5310, 11, 370, 689, 307, 452, 1011, 30, 51307], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124258864159677, "compression_ratio": 1.5615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2300942599588471e-12}, {"id": 60, "seek": 17158, "start": 190.54000000000002, "end": 190.76000000000002, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51313, 1779, 13, 51324], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124258864159677, "compression_ratio": 1.5615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2300942599588471e-12}, {"id": 61, "seek": 17158, "start": 190.86, "end": 193.12, "text": " You calculate the end point from the angles.", "tokens": [51329, 509, 8873, 264, 917, 935, 490, 264, 14708, 13, 51442], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12124258864159677, "compression_ratio": 1.5615384615384615, "no_speech_prob": 1.2300942599588471e-12}, {"id": 62, "seek": 19312, "start": 193.12, "end": 195.18, "text": " But inverse kinematics asks the opposite.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 17340, 15784, 37541, 8962, 264, 6182, 13, 50468], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421870960908777, "compression_ratio": 1.5395348837209302, "no_speech_prob": 1.5977319293980496e-12}, {"id": 63, "seek": 19312, "start": 195.58, "end": 198.74, "text": " It says, I want my hand at this specific spot in the air.", "tokens": [50488, 467, 1619, 11, 286, 528, 452, 1011, 412, 341, 2685, 4008, 294, 264, 1988, 13, 50646], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421870960908777, "compression_ratio": 1.5395348837209302, "no_speech_prob": 1.5977319293980496e-12}, {"id": 64, "seek": 19312, "start": 199.38, "end": 204.28, "text": " What angles do my shoulder and elbow need to instantly snap to in order to get it there?", "tokens": [50678, 708, 14708, 360, 452, 7948, 293, 18507, 643, 281, 13518, 13650, 281, 294, 1668, 281, 483, 309, 456, 30, 50923], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421870960908777, "compression_ratio": 1.5395348837209302, "no_speech_prob": 1.5977319293980496e-12}, {"id": 65, "seek": 19312, "start": 204.36, "end": 205.44, "text": " Precisely the mechanic.", "tokens": [50927, 48746, 736, 264, 23860, 13, 50981], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421870960908777, "compression_ratio": 1.5395348837209302, "no_speech_prob": 1.5977319293980496e-12}, {"id": 66, "seek": 19312, "start": 205.94, "end": 211.92000000000002, "text": " You feed the system the desired end state, and the algorithm calculates the necessary joint angles in reverse.", "tokens": [51006, 509, 3154, 264, 1185, 264, 14721, 917, 1785, 11, 293, 264, 9284, 4322, 1024, 264, 4818, 7225, 14708, 294, 9943, 13, 51305], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421870960908777, "compression_ratio": 1.5395348837209302, "no_speech_prob": 1.5977319293980496e-12}, {"id": 67, "seek": 19312, "start": 212.16, "end": 212.48000000000002, "text": " Got it.", "tokens": [51317, 5803, 309, 13, 51333], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13421870960908777, "compression_ratio": 1.5395348837209302, "no_speech_prob": 1.5977319293980496e-12}, {"id": 68, "seek": 21248, "start": 212.48, "end": 218.39999999999998, "text": " But under this view, balance is a condition that must be achieved at every single isolated millisecond.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 833, 341, 1910, 11, 4772, 307, 257, 4188, 300, 1633, 312, 11042, 412, 633, 2167, 14621, 27940, 18882, 13, 50661], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1389962346930253, "compression_ratio": 1.5775862068965518, "no_speech_prob": 2.16726116220034e-12}, {"id": 69, "seek": 21248, "start": 218.51999999999998, "end": 219.06, "text": " Oh, man.", "tokens": [50667, 876, 11, 587, 13, 50694], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1389962346930253, "compression_ratio": 1.5775862068965518, "no_speech_prob": 2.16726116220034e-12}, {"id": 70, "seek": 21248, "start": 219.23999999999998, "end": 219.38, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50703, 865, 13, 50710], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1389962346930253, "compression_ratio": 1.5775862068965518, "no_speech_prob": 2.16726116220034e-12}, {"id": 71, "seek": 21248, "start": 219.44, "end": 222.42, "text": " The controller is trapped in this loop of constant anxiety.", "tokens": [50713, 440, 10561, 307, 14994, 294, 341, 6367, 295, 5754, 9119, 13, 50862], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1389962346930253, "compression_ratio": 1.5775862068965518, "no_speech_prob": 2.16726116220034e-12}, {"id": 72, "seek": 21248, "start": 222.73999999999998, "end": 230.42, "text": " It measures where the robot currently is, compares it to the target pose, calculates the discrepancy, and fires the motors to correct it.", "tokens": [50878, 467, 8000, 689, 264, 7881, 4362, 307, 11, 38334, 309, 281, 264, 3779, 10774, 11, 4322, 1024, 264, 2983, 265, 6040, 1344, 11, 293, 15044, 264, 25035, 281, 3006, 309, 13, 51262], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1389962346930253, "compression_ratio": 1.5775862068965518, "no_speech_prob": 2.16726116220034e-12}, {"id": 73, "seek": 21248, "start": 230.42, "end": 231.29999999999998, "text": " Over and over again.", "tokens": [51262, 4886, 293, 670, 797, 13, 51306], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1389962346930253, "compression_ratio": 1.5775862068965518, "no_speech_prob": 2.16726116220034e-12}, {"id": 74, "seek": 21248, "start": 231.54, "end": 232.64, "text": " Thousands of times a second.", "tokens": [51318, 40535, 295, 1413, 257, 1150, 13, 51373], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1389962346930253, "compression_ratio": 1.5775862068965518, "no_speech_prob": 2.16726116220034e-12}, {"id": 75, "seek": 23264, "start": 232.64, "end": 242.16, "text": " So locomotion, then, is really just a rapid-fire series of microscopic corrections happening so fast that the naked eye perceives it as smooth walking.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 36369, 19228, 11, 550, 11, 307, 534, 445, 257, 7558, 12, 12037, 2638, 295, 47897, 36406, 2737, 370, 2370, 300, 264, 15791, 3313, 9016, 1539, 309, 382, 5508, 4494, 13, 50841], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14323764486411183, "compression_ratio": 1.542857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619795817351957e-12}, {"id": 76, "seek": 23264, "start": 242.33999999999997, "end": 250.06, "text": " But Flickshun argues that this state-centric default treats the actual path the robot takes as, like, an afterthought, right?", "tokens": [50850, 583, 3235, 618, 2716, 409, 38218, 300, 341, 1785, 12, 45300, 7576, 19566, 264, 3539, 3100, 264, 7881, 2516, 382, 11, 411, 11, 364, 934, 43135, 11, 558, 30, 51236], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14323764486411183, "compression_ratio": 1.542857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619795817351957e-12}, {"id": 77, "seek": 23264, "start": 250.11999999999998, "end": 250.29999999999998, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51239, 865, 13, 51248], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14323764486411183, "compression_ratio": 1.542857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619795817351957e-12}, {"id": 78, "seek": 23264, "start": 250.6, "end": 250.92, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51263, 1079, 13, 51279], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14323764486411183, "compression_ratio": 1.542857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619795817351957e-12}, {"id": 79, "seek": 23264, "start": 251.56, "end": 253.07999999999998, "text": " The pose is the primary goal.", "tokens": [51311, 440, 10774, 307, 264, 6194, 3387, 13, 51387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14323764486411183, "compression_ratio": 1.542857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619795817351957e-12}, {"id": 80, "seek": 23264, "start": 253.64, "end": 256.88, "text": " The path is just the accidental blurring between the poses.", "tokens": [51415, 440, 3100, 307, 445, 264, 38094, 14257, 2937, 1296, 264, 26059, 13, 51577], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14323764486411183, "compression_ratio": 1.542857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.6619795817351957e-12}, {"id": 81, "seek": 25688, "start": 256.88, "end": 264.56, "text": " And the author proposes flipping this entirely upside down with a trajectory-centric alternative.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 264, 3793, 2365, 4201, 26886, 341, 7696, 14119, 760, 365, 257, 21512, 12, 45300, 8535, 13, 50749], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514352506345457, "compression_ratio": 1.603448275862069, "no_speech_prob": 1.3459257579978567e-12}, {"id": 82, "seek": 25688, "start": 264.92, "end": 265.14, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50767, 1779, 13, 50778], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514352506345457, "compression_ratio": 1.603448275862069, "no_speech_prob": 1.3459257579978567e-12}, {"id": 83, "seek": 25688, "start": 265.34, "end": 265.76, "text": " The alternative.", "tokens": [50788, 440, 8535, 13, 50809], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514352506345457, "compression_ratio": 1.603448275862069, "no_speech_prob": 1.3459257579978567e-12}, {"id": 84, "seek": 25688, "start": 266.08, "end": 271.68, "text": " So instead of stop motion, Flickshun wants us to think of movement like a single, fluid brush stroke.", "tokens": [50825, 407, 2602, 295, 1590, 5394, 11, 3235, 618, 2716, 409, 2738, 505, 281, 519, 295, 3963, 411, 257, 2167, 11, 9113, 5287, 12403, 13, 51105], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514352506345457, "compression_ratio": 1.603448275862069, "no_speech_prob": 1.3459257579978567e-12}, {"id": 85, "seek": 25688, "start": 272.21999999999997, "end": 280.14, "text": " The continuous sweep of the brush is the primary object, and the specific pose of the bristles at any given microsecond is just a derivative byproduct.", "tokens": [51132, 440, 10957, 22169, 295, 264, 5287, 307, 264, 6194, 2657, 11, 293, 264, 2685, 10774, 295, 264, 738, 29923, 412, 604, 2212, 3123, 37841, 18882, 307, 445, 257, 13760, 538, 33244, 13, 51528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514352506345457, "compression_ratio": 1.603448275862069, "no_speech_prob": 1.3459257579978567e-12}, {"id": 86, "seek": 25688, "start": 280.3, "end": 280.78, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51536, 7587, 13, 51560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514352506345457, "compression_ratio": 1.603448275862069, "no_speech_prob": 1.3459257579978567e-12}, {"id": 87, "seek": 25688, "start": 281.2, "end": 284.88, "text": " Now, the paper acknowledges that state-centric control is incredibly successful.", "tokens": [51581, 823, 11, 264, 3035, 15195, 2880, 300, 1785, 12, 45300, 1969, 307, 6252, 4406, 13, 51765], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514352506345457, "compression_ratio": 1.603448275862069, "no_speech_prob": 1.3459257579978567e-12}, {"id": 88, "seek": 28488, "start": 284.88, "end": 290.14, "text": " I mean, those viral videos of humanoid robots doing backflips and parkour.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 914, 11, 729, 16132, 2145, 295, 1952, 17079, 14733, 884, 646, 3423, 2600, 293, 3884, 396, 13, 50628], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 89, "seek": 28488, "start": 290.21999999999997, "end": 290.52, "text": " Oh, yeah.", "tokens": [50632, 876, 11, 1338, 13, 50647], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 90, "seek": 28488, "start": 290.6, "end": 291.8, "text": " The Boston Dynamics stuff.", "tokens": [50651, 440, 12333, 22947, 1167, 1507, 13, 50711], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 91, "seek": 28488, "start": 291.9, "end": 292.14, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50716, 1779, 13, 50728], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 92, "seek": 28488, "start": 292.56, "end": 295.88, "text": " That is inverse kinematics pushed to its absolute computational limits.", "tokens": [50749, 663, 307, 17340, 15784, 37541, 9152, 281, 1080, 8236, 28270, 10406, 13, 50915], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 93, "seek": 28488, "start": 296.58, "end": 296.86, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [50950, 3153, 13, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 94, "seek": 28488, "start": 297.2, "end": 300.68, "text": " But Flickshun is making a philosophical and mathematical claim here.", "tokens": [50981, 583, 3235, 618, 2716, 409, 307, 1455, 257, 25066, 293, 18894, 3932, 510, 13, 51155], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 95, "seek": 28488, "start": 301.06, "end": 306.34, "text": " By treating the pose as primary, we are fundamentally misrepresenting how natural systems actually operate.", "tokens": [51174, 3146, 15083, 264, 10774, 382, 6194, 11, 321, 366, 17879, 3346, 19919, 11662, 278, 577, 3303, 3652, 767, 9651, 13, 51438], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 96, "seek": 28488, "start": 306.44, "end": 307.94, "text": " Because nature doesn't do stop motion.", "tokens": [51443, 1436, 3687, 1177, 380, 360, 1590, 5394, 13, 51518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 97, "seek": 28488, "start": 308.18, "end": 309.24, "text": " No, it doesn't.", "tokens": [51530, 883, 11, 309, 1177, 380, 13, 51583], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12916084758022375, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 2.028030304454531e-12}, {"id": 98, "seek": 30924, "start": 309.24, "end": 318.8, "text": " If you treat the trajectory, the continuous history of the movement, as the primary mathematical object, balance ceases to be a target you desperately try to hit at every instant.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 291, 2387, 264, 21512, 11, 264, 10957, 2503, 295, 264, 3963, 11, 382, 264, 6194, 18894, 2657, 11, 4772, 1769, 1957, 281, 312, 257, 3779, 291, 23726, 853, 281, 2045, 412, 633, 9836, 13, 50843], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1368764741080148, "compression_ratio": 1.582010582010582, "no_speech_prob": 1.7553959587995882e-12}, {"id": 99, "seek": 30924, "start": 319.1, "end": 320.16, "text": " It becomes something else.", "tokens": [50858, 467, 3643, 746, 1646, 13, 50911], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1368764741080148, "compression_ratio": 1.582010582010582, "no_speech_prob": 1.7553959587995882e-12}, {"id": 100, "seek": 30924, "start": 320.26, "end": 320.46000000000004, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50916, 1779, 13, 50926], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1368764741080148, "compression_ratio": 1.582010582010582, "no_speech_prob": 1.7553959587995882e-12}, {"id": 101, "seek": 30924, "start": 320.82, "end": 322.54, "text": " Balance becomes an ongoing process.", "tokens": [50944, 41899, 3643, 364, 10452, 1399, 13, 51030], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1368764741080148, "compression_ratio": 1.582010582010582, "no_speech_prob": 1.7553959587995882e-12}, {"id": 102, "seek": 30924, "start": 322.7, "end": 324.58, "text": " It becomes a property of the brush stroke itself.", "tokens": [51038, 467, 3643, 257, 4707, 295, 264, 5287, 12403, 2564, 13, 51132], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1368764741080148, "compression_ratio": 1.582010582010582, "no_speech_prob": 1.7553959587995882e-12}, {"id": 103, "seek": 32458, "start": 324.58, "end": 333.94, "text": " And Flickshun actually points out that this reversal, you know, prioritizing the continuous history over the frozen state, is something we already do in software in other ways.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 3235, 618, 2716, 409, 767, 2793, 484, 300, 341, 42778, 11, 291, 458, 11, 14846, 3319, 264, 10957, 2503, 670, 264, 12496, 1785, 11, 307, 746, 321, 1217, 360, 294, 4722, 294, 661, 2098, 13, 50833], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08258615493774414, "compression_ratio": 1.5568181818181819, "no_speech_prob": 1.7547492322037006e-12}, {"id": 104, "seek": 32458, "start": 334.03999999999996, "end": 334.74, "text": " We do, yeah.", "tokens": [50838, 492, 360, 11, 1338, 13, 50873], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08258615493774414, "compression_ratio": 1.5568181818181819, "no_speech_prob": 1.7547492322037006e-12}, {"id": 105, "seek": 32458, "start": 334.76, "end": 336.71999999999997, "text": " Think about the undo button on your computer.", "tokens": [50874, 6557, 466, 264, 23779, 2960, 322, 428, 3820, 13, 50972], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08258615493774414, "compression_ratio": 1.5568181818181819, "no_speech_prob": 1.7547492322037006e-12}, {"id": 106, "seek": 32458, "start": 337.44, "end": 344.64, "text": " When you hit undo on a word processor, the computer hasn't just saved a million separate isolated screenshots of your document.", "tokens": [51008, 1133, 291, 2045, 23779, 322, 257, 1349, 15321, 11, 264, 3820, 6132, 380, 445, 6624, 257, 2459, 4994, 14621, 40661, 295, 428, 4166, 13, 51368], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08258615493774414, "compression_ratio": 1.5568181818181819, "no_speech_prob": 1.7547492322037006e-12}, {"id": 107, "seek": 32458, "start": 344.82, "end": 346.64, "text": " No, that would take way too much memory.", "tokens": [51377, 883, 11, 300, 576, 747, 636, 886, 709, 4675, 13, 51468], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08258615493774414, "compression_ratio": 1.5568181818181819, "no_speech_prob": 1.7547492322037006e-12}, {"id": 108, "seek": 32458, "start": 346.76, "end": 346.9, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51474, 1779, 13, 51481], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08258615493774414, "compression_ratio": 1.5568181818181819, "no_speech_prob": 1.7547492322037006e-12}, {"id": 109, "seek": 34690, "start": 346.9, "end": 349.44, "text": " It preserves a continuous history of your keystrokes.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1183, 9054, 257, 10957, 2503, 295, 428, 2141, 27616, 5993, 13, 50492], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15698965976112766, "compression_ratio": 1.6150442477876106, "no_speech_prob": 1.5791130339101733e-12}, {"id": 110, "seek": 34690, "start": 350.58, "end": 354.21999999999997, "text": " Any given state of the document is just a compressed summary of that history.", "tokens": [50549, 2639, 2212, 1785, 295, 264, 4166, 307, 445, 257, 30353, 12691, 295, 300, 2503, 13, 50731], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15698965976112766, "compression_ratio": 1.6150442477876106, "no_speech_prob": 1.5791130339101733e-12}, {"id": 111, "seek": 34690, "start": 354.58, "end": 357.03999999999996, "text": " A macro shortcut is the exact same thing.", "tokens": [50749, 316, 18887, 24822, 307, 264, 1900, 912, 551, 13, 50872], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15698965976112766, "compression_ratio": 1.6150442477876106, "no_speech_prob": 1.5791130339101733e-12}, {"id": 112, "seek": 34690, "start": 357.12, "end": 357.94, "text": " It's not an action.", "tokens": [50876, 467, 311, 406, 364, 3069, 13, 50917], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15698965976112766, "compression_ratio": 1.6150442477876106, "no_speech_prob": 1.5791130339101733e-12}, {"id": 113, "seek": 34690, "start": 358.17999999999995, "end": 361.32, "text": " It's a compressed record of a previously traversed sequence.", "tokens": [50929, 467, 311, 257, 30353, 2136, 295, 257, 8046, 23149, 292, 8310, 13, 51086], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15698965976112766, "compression_ratio": 1.6150442477876106, "no_speech_prob": 1.5791130339101733e-12}, {"id": 114, "seek": 34690, "start": 361.85999999999996, "end": 364.59999999999997, "text": " So Flickshun's essay asks a radical question.", "tokens": [51113, 407, 3235, 618, 2716, 409, 311, 16238, 8962, 257, 12001, 1168, 13, 51250], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15698965976112766, "compression_ratio": 1.6150442477876106, "no_speech_prob": 1.5791130339101733e-12}, {"id": 115, "seek": 34690, "start": 365.5, "end": 369.79999999999995, "text": " What if human and animal locomotion operates the exact same way?", "tokens": [51295, 708, 498, 1952, 293, 5496, 36369, 19228, 22577, 264, 1900, 912, 636, 30, 51510], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15698965976112766, "compression_ratio": 1.6150442477876106, "no_speech_prob": 1.5791130339101733e-12}, {"id": 116, "seek": 36980, "start": 369.8, "end": 370.16, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50383], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12963452002014778, "compression_ratio": 1.6176470588235294, "no_speech_prob": 1.443742477999499e-12}, {"id": 117, "seek": 36980, "start": 370.28000000000003, "end": 382.08000000000004, "text": " What if, instead of asking our brains to calculate the exact angle our knee should occupy at time T, our biology is simply executing a local operator that generates the sweeping motion?", "tokens": [50389, 708, 498, 11, 2602, 295, 3365, 527, 15442, 281, 8873, 264, 1900, 5802, 527, 9434, 820, 30645, 412, 565, 314, 11, 527, 14956, 307, 2935, 32368, 257, 2654, 12973, 300, 23815, 264, 33285, 5394, 30, 50979], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12963452002014778, "compression_ratio": 1.6176470588235294, "no_speech_prob": 1.443742477999499e-12}, {"id": 118, "seek": 36980, "start": 382.42, "end": 382.64, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50996, 865, 13, 51007], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12963452002014778, "compression_ratio": 1.6176470588235294, "no_speech_prob": 1.443742477999499e-12}, {"id": 119, "seek": 36980, "start": 382.74, "end": 394.8, "text": " And to understand how a physical body could possibly generate this fluid brush stroke without calculating all those tiny stop motion poses, we actually have to step away from robotics entirely for a second.", "tokens": [51012, 400, 281, 1223, 577, 257, 4001, 1772, 727, 6264, 8460, 341, 9113, 5287, 12403, 1553, 28258, 439, 729, 5870, 1590, 5394, 26059, 11, 321, 767, 362, 281, 1823, 1314, 490, 34145, 7696, 337, 257, 1150, 13, 51615], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12963452002014778, "compression_ratio": 1.6176470588235294, "no_speech_prob": 1.443742477999499e-12}, {"id": 120, "seek": 36980, "start": 394.96000000000004, "end": 395.34000000000003, "text": " We do.", "tokens": [51623, 492, 360, 13, 51642], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12963452002014778, "compression_ratio": 1.6176470588235294, "no_speech_prob": 1.443742477999499e-12}, {"id": 121, "seek": 36980, "start": 395.46000000000004, "end": 396.52, "text": " We have to look at biology.", "tokens": [51648, 492, 362, 281, 574, 412, 14956, 13, 51701], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12963452002014778, "compression_ratio": 1.6176470588235294, "no_speech_prob": 1.443742477999499e-12}, {"id": 122, "seek": 39652, "start": 396.52, "end": 403.29999999999995, "text": " Specifically, a foundational and admittedly somewhat gruesome experiment from 1911 involving cats.", "tokens": [50365, 26058, 11, 257, 32195, 293, 14920, 356, 8344, 48238, 423, 5120, 490, 1294, 5348, 17030, 11111, 13, 50704], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 123, "seek": 39652, "start": 403.47999999999996, "end": 404.44, "text": " Ah, yes.", "tokens": [50713, 2438, 11, 2086, 13, 50761], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 124, "seek": 39652, "start": 405.02, "end": 406.4, "text": " The work of Thomas Graham Brown.", "tokens": [50790, 440, 589, 295, 8500, 22691, 8030, 13, 50859], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 125, "seek": 39652, "start": 406.62, "end": 411.46, "text": " This is really the biological bedrock for Flickshun's entire geometric theory.", "tokens": [50870, 639, 307, 534, 264, 13910, 2901, 17799, 337, 3235, 618, 2716, 409, 311, 2302, 33246, 5261, 13, 51112], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 126, "seek": 39652, "start": 411.97999999999996, "end": 417.12, "text": " So to set the context, I had to look up what the prevailing scientific consensus was before Graham Brown.", "tokens": [51138, 407, 281, 992, 264, 4319, 11, 286, 632, 281, 574, 493, 437, 264, 12642, 23315, 8134, 19115, 390, 949, 22691, 8030, 13, 51395], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 127, "seek": 39652, "start": 417.24, "end": 417.59999999999997, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51401, 1779, 13, 51419], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 128, "seek": 39652, "start": 417.76, "end": 418.9, "text": " Because it was very different.", "tokens": [51427, 1436, 309, 390, 588, 819, 13, 51484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 129, "seek": 39652, "start": 419.03999999999996, "end": 419.21999999999997, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51491, 865, 13, 51500], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 130, "seek": 39652, "start": 419.35999999999996, "end": 423.52, "text": " Back in the early 20th century, the heavy hitter in neurophysiology was a guy named Charles Sherrington.", "tokens": [51507, 5833, 294, 264, 2440, 945, 392, 4901, 11, 264, 4676, 2045, 391, 294, 16499, 950, 749, 46457, 390, 257, 2146, 4926, 10523, 11789, 2937, 1756, 13, 51715], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1370645073371205, "compression_ratio": 1.5290322580645161, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674034336068954e-12}, {"id": 131, "seek": 42352, "start": 423.52, "end": 427.28, "text": " And he championed the reflex chain theory of movement.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 415, 10971, 292, 264, 23802, 5021, 5261, 295, 3963, 13, 50553], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12487089911172557, "compression_ratio": 1.5642201834862386, "no_speech_prob": 1.687546478425228e-12}, {"id": 132, "seek": 42352, "start": 427.53999999999996, "end": 427.94, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50566, 1079, 13, 50586], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12487089911172557, "compression_ratio": 1.5642201834862386, "no_speech_prob": 1.687546478425228e-12}, {"id": 133, "seek": 42352, "start": 428.41999999999996, "end": 433.29999999999995, "text": " When I read about Sherrington's theory, I just pictured a chain reaction of falling dominoes.", "tokens": [50610, 1133, 286, 1401, 466, 11789, 2937, 1756, 311, 5261, 11, 286, 445, 49896, 257, 5021, 5480, 295, 7440, 3285, 2982, 279, 13, 50854], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12487089911172557, "compression_ratio": 1.5642201834862386, "no_speech_prob": 1.687546478425228e-12}, {"id": 134, "seek": 42352, "start": 433.4, "end": 433.58, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50859, 865, 13, 50868], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12487089911172557, "compression_ratio": 1.5642201834862386, "no_speech_prob": 1.687546478425228e-12}, {"id": 135, "seek": 42352, "start": 433.84, "end": 440.32, "text": " He believed that every single phase of a movement was purely a reaction to sensory feedback from the phase right before it.", "tokens": [50881, 634, 7847, 300, 633, 2167, 5574, 295, 257, 3963, 390, 17491, 257, 5480, 281, 27233, 5824, 490, 264, 5574, 558, 949, 309, 13, 51205], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12487089911172557, "compression_ratio": 1.5642201834862386, "no_speech_prob": 1.687546478425228e-12}, {"id": 136, "seek": 42352, "start": 440.38, "end": 443.0, "text": " And Sherrington's model was incredibly intuitive, really.", "tokens": [51208, 400, 11789, 2937, 1756, 311, 2316, 390, 6252, 21769, 11, 534, 13, 51339], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12487089911172557, "compression_ratio": 1.5642201834862386, "no_speech_prob": 1.687546478425228e-12}, {"id": 137, "seek": 44300, "start": 443.0, "end": 444.56, "text": " I mean, imagine taking a step.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 914, 11, 3811, 1940, 257, 1823, 13, 50443], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.138115170975806, "compression_ratio": 1.523076923076923, "no_speech_prob": 2.1757556693813296e-12}, {"id": 138, "seek": 44300, "start": 444.72, "end": 445.98, "text": " Your heel strikes the ground.", "tokens": [50451, 2260, 9430, 16750, 264, 2727, 13, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.138115170975806, "compression_ratio": 1.523076923076923, "no_speech_prob": 2.1757556693813296e-12}, {"id": 139, "seek": 44300, "start": 446.42, "end": 450.46, "text": " That physical impact sends a sensory signal up your leg to your spinal cord.", "tokens": [50536, 663, 4001, 2712, 14790, 257, 27233, 6358, 493, 428, 1676, 281, 428, 28022, 12250, 13, 50738], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.138115170975806, "compression_ratio": 1.523076923076923, "no_speech_prob": 2.1757556693813296e-12}, {"id": 140, "seek": 44300, "start": 451.54, "end": 460.0, "text": " Sherrington argued that this specific sensory input is what triggers the reflex to fire the muscles for the next phase of the walk, which is lifting your knee.", "tokens": [50792, 11789, 2937, 1756, 20219, 300, 341, 2685, 27233, 4846, 307, 437, 22827, 264, 23802, 281, 2610, 264, 9530, 337, 264, 958, 5574, 295, 264, 1792, 11, 597, 307, 15798, 428, 9434, 13, 51215], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.138115170975806, "compression_ratio": 1.523076923076923, "no_speech_prob": 2.1757556693813296e-12}, {"id": 141, "seek": 46000, "start": 460.0, "end": 462.54, "text": " Okay, so the heel strike is the trigger.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 11, 370, 264, 9430, 9302, 307, 264, 7875, 13, 50492], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 142, "seek": 46000, "start": 462.76, "end": 463.28, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50503, 7587, 13, 50529], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 143, "seek": 46000, "start": 464.02, "end": 470.12, "text": " Then, lifting your knee stretches a tendon, which sends another sensory signal, triggering the ankle to flex.", "tokens": [50566, 1396, 11, 15798, 428, 9434, 29058, 257, 46479, 11, 597, 14790, 1071, 27233, 6358, 11, 40406, 264, 21999, 281, 5896, 13, 50871], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 144, "seek": 46000, "start": 470.48, "end": 474.16, "text": " So it's a continuous loop relying entirely on guidance from the outside world.", "tokens": [50889, 407, 309, 311, 257, 10957, 6367, 24140, 7696, 322, 10056, 490, 264, 2380, 1002, 13, 51073], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 145, "seek": 46000, "start": 474.2, "end": 474.44, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51075, 1779, 13, 51087], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 146, "seek": 46000, "start": 474.62, "end": 477.22, "text": " Without the sensory trigger, the dominoes just stop falling.", "tokens": [51096, 9129, 264, 27233, 7875, 11, 264, 3285, 2982, 279, 445, 1590, 7440, 13, 51226], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 147, "seek": 46000, "start": 477.52, "end": 482.38, "text": " But then Graham Brown comes along and physically severs the sensory nerves in cats.", "tokens": [51241, 583, 550, 22691, 8030, 1487, 2051, 293, 9762, 369, 840, 264, 27233, 23078, 294, 11111, 13, 51484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 148, "seek": 46000, "start": 482.8, "end": 485.94, "text": " He created what biologists call deferented subjects.", "tokens": [51505, 634, 2942, 437, 3228, 12256, 818, 25704, 6003, 13066, 13, 51662], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 149, "seek": 46000, "start": 486.16, "end": 486.42, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51673, 1779, 13, 51686], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15832165554837063, "compression_ratio": 1.6071428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.762275330004226e-12}, {"id": 150, "seek": 48642, "start": 486.42, "end": 493.58000000000004, "text": " And for those of us who aren't neurosurgeons, the spinal cord has these nerve bundles called dorsal roots that plug into the back of it.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 337, 729, 295, 505, 567, 3212, 380, 28813, 374, 30636, 11, 264, 28022, 12250, 575, 613, 16355, 13882, 904, 1219, 274, 830, 304, 10669, 300, 5452, 666, 264, 646, 295, 309, 13, 50723], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09661511717171505, "compression_ratio": 1.648936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622713184561878e-12}, {"id": 151, "seek": 48642, "start": 494.04, "end": 500.16, "text": " They act like literal USB cables, transmitting touch, pressure, and pain from the legs up to the brain.", "tokens": [50746, 814, 605, 411, 20411, 10109, 17555, 11, 7715, 2414, 2557, 11, 3321, 11, 293, 1822, 490, 264, 5668, 493, 281, 264, 3567, 13, 51052], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09661511717171505, "compression_ratio": 1.648936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622713184561878e-12}, {"id": 152, "seek": 48642, "start": 500.40000000000003, "end": 501.72, "text": " That's a good way to picture it.", "tokens": [51064, 663, 311, 257, 665, 636, 281, 3036, 309, 13, 51130], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09661511717171505, "compression_ratio": 1.648936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622713184561878e-12}, {"id": 153, "seek": 48642, "start": 501.84000000000003, "end": 503.56, "text": " So Graham Brown unplugged those cables.", "tokens": [51136, 407, 22691, 8030, 39456, 3004, 729, 17555, 13, 51222], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09661511717171505, "compression_ratio": 1.648936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622713184561878e-12}, {"id": 154, "seek": 48642, "start": 503.90000000000003, "end": 506.66, "text": " The motor nerves telling the muscles to move were still intact.", "tokens": [51239, 440, 5932, 23078, 3585, 264, 9530, 281, 1286, 645, 920, 23493, 13, 51377], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09661511717171505, "compression_ratio": 1.648936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622713184561878e-12}, {"id": 155, "seek": 48642, "start": 506.90000000000003, "end": 511.3, "text": " But the spinal cord was completely blind and deaf to what the legs were actually doing.", "tokens": [51389, 583, 264, 28022, 12250, 390, 2584, 6865, 293, 15559, 281, 437, 264, 5668, 645, 767, 884, 13, 51609], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09661511717171505, "compression_ratio": 1.648936170212766, "no_speech_prob": 1.7622713184561878e-12}, {"id": 156, "seek": 51130, "start": 511.3, "end": 521.26, "text": " And according to Sherrington's reflex chain theory, a cat in this condition shouldn't be able to produce the rhythmic, alternating stepping pattern of walking.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 4650, 281, 11789, 2937, 1756, 311, 23802, 5021, 5261, 11, 257, 3857, 294, 341, 4188, 4659, 380, 312, 1075, 281, 5258, 264, 46967, 11, 40062, 16821, 5102, 295, 4494, 13, 50863], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 157, "seek": 51130, "start": 521.52, "end": 522.5600000000001, "text": " Because there's no feedback.", "tokens": [50876, 1436, 456, 311, 572, 5824, 13, 50928], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 158, "seek": 51130, "start": 523.04, "end": 523.5, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50952, 7587, 13, 50975], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 159, "seek": 51130, "start": 524.02, "end": 530.36, "text": " If there is no sensory signal confirming the foot hit the ground, the reflex for the next step should never fire.", "tokens": [51001, 759, 456, 307, 572, 27233, 6358, 42861, 264, 2671, 2045, 264, 2727, 11, 264, 23802, 337, 264, 958, 1823, 820, 1128, 2610, 13, 51318], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 160, "seek": 51130, "start": 530.62, "end": 532.42, "text": " The system should just paralyze.", "tokens": [51331, 440, 1185, 820, 445, 32645, 1381, 13, 51421], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 161, "seek": 51130, "start": 532.54, "end": 534.42, "text": " But the deferent cats did step.", "tokens": [51427, 583, 264, 25704, 317, 11111, 630, 1823, 13, 51521], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 162, "seek": 51130, "start": 535.08, "end": 537.78, "text": " They produced a continuous, rhythmic walking pattern.", "tokens": [51554, 814, 7126, 257, 10957, 11, 46967, 4494, 5102, 13, 51689], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 163, "seek": 51130, "start": 537.94, "end": 538.46, "text": " They did.", "tokens": [51697, 814, 630, 13, 51723], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16711661080333673, "compression_ratio": 1.673003802281369, "no_speech_prob": 1.4607630426446971e-12}, {"id": 164, "seek": 53846, "start": 538.46, "end": 550.02, "text": " Graham Brown proved that isolated spinal circuits, completely cut off from peripheral sensory input, could spontaneously produce the alternating flexor-extensor patterns of walking.", "tokens": [50365, 22691, 8030, 14617, 300, 14621, 28022, 26354, 11, 2584, 1723, 766, 490, 40235, 27233, 4846, 11, 727, 47632, 5258, 264, 40062, 5896, 284, 12, 3828, 23153, 8294, 295, 4494, 13, 50943], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 165, "seek": 53846, "start": 550.4200000000001, "end": 551.84, "text": " That is just wow.", "tokens": [50963, 663, 307, 445, 6076, 13, 51034], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 166, "seek": 53846, "start": 552.0, "end": 553.7800000000001, "text": " Yeah, the rhythm didn't come from the ground.", "tokens": [51042, 865, 11, 264, 11801, 994, 380, 808, 490, 264, 2727, 13, 51131], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 167, "seek": 53846, "start": 553.9000000000001, "end": 555.4000000000001, "text": " It came from inside the spine.", "tokens": [51137, 467, 1361, 490, 1854, 264, 15395, 13, 51212], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 168, "seek": 53846, "start": 555.5600000000001, "end": 556.4200000000001, "text": " This blew my mind.", "tokens": [51220, 639, 19075, 452, 1575, 13, 51263], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 169, "seek": 53846, "start": 556.6600000000001, "end": 562.26, "text": " The spinal cord itself, sitting in a total sensory vacuum, can just generate a walking rhythm all on its own.", "tokens": [51275, 440, 28022, 12250, 2564, 11, 3798, 294, 257, 3217, 27233, 14224, 11, 393, 445, 8460, 257, 4494, 11801, 439, 322, 1080, 1065, 13, 51555], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 170, "seek": 53846, "start": 562.5, "end": 565.0, "text": " Brown proposed a half-center model to explain this.", "tokens": [51567, 8030, 10348, 257, 1922, 12, 50085, 2316, 281, 2903, 341, 13, 51692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 171, "seek": 53846, "start": 565.38, "end": 567.82, "text": " Imagine two pools of neurons in the spine.", "tokens": [51711, 11739, 732, 28688, 295, 22027, 294, 264, 15395, 13, 51833], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12248745285162405, "compression_ratio": 1.6891891891891893, "no_speech_prob": 1.3776292389841571e-12}, {"id": 172, "seek": 56782, "start": 568.5, "end": 568.6400000000001, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50399, 1033, 13, 50406], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 173, "seek": 56782, "start": 568.84, "end": 573.96, "text": " One pool controls the muscles that pull the leg up, and the other controls the muscles that push the leg down.", "tokens": [50416, 1485, 7005, 9003, 264, 9530, 300, 2235, 264, 1676, 493, 11, 293, 264, 661, 9003, 264, 9530, 300, 2944, 264, 1676, 760, 13, 50672], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 174, "seek": 56782, "start": 574.24, "end": 576.8000000000001, "text": " They are wired to mutually inhibit each other.", "tokens": [50686, 814, 366, 27415, 281, 39144, 49858, 1184, 661, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 175, "seek": 56782, "start": 576.9000000000001, "end": 577.5400000000001, "text": " So they fight.", "tokens": [50819, 407, 436, 2092, 13, 50851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 176, "seek": 56782, "start": 577.74, "end": 578.12, "text": " Basically.", "tokens": [50861, 8537, 13, 50880], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 177, "seek": 56782, "start": 578.6800000000001, "end": 582.38, "text": " When the pull-up pool fires, it actively suppresses the push-down pool.", "tokens": [50908, 1133, 264, 2235, 12, 1010, 7005, 15044, 11, 309, 13022, 26835, 279, 264, 2944, 12, 5093, 7005, 13, 51093], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 178, "seek": 56782, "start": 582.7800000000001, "end": 585.08, "text": " But eventually, the firing pool tires out.", "tokens": [51113, 583, 4728, 11, 264, 16045, 7005, 13885, 484, 13, 51228], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 179, "seek": 56782, "start": 585.3000000000001, "end": 585.9200000000001, "text": " It adapts.", "tokens": [51239, 467, 23169, 1373, 13, 51270], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 180, "seek": 56782, "start": 586.0, "end": 586.5, "text": " Oh, I see.", "tokens": [51274, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 51299], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2092819611231486, "compression_ratio": 1.6381909547738693, "no_speech_prob": 1.9969052453272518e-12}, {"id": 181, "seek": 58650, "start": 586.5, "end": 593.0, "text": " As its signal weakens, the suppression lifts, allowing the push-down pool to fire, which in turn suppresses the first pool.", "tokens": [50365, 1018, 1080, 6358, 5336, 694, 11, 264, 36807, 30501, 11, 8293, 264, 2944, 12, 5093, 7005, 281, 2610, 11, 597, 294, 1261, 26835, 279, 264, 700, 7005, 13, 50690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16939198343377365, "compression_ratio": 1.4415584415584415, "no_speech_prob": 2.012259499653557e-12}, {"id": 182, "seek": 58650, "start": 593.12, "end": 593.76, "text": " Like a seesaw.", "tokens": [50696, 1743, 257, 8194, 1607, 13, 50728], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16939198343377365, "compression_ratio": 1.4415584415584415, "no_speech_prob": 2.012259499653557e-12}, {"id": 183, "seek": 58650, "start": 593.96, "end": 594.4, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50738, 7587, 13, 50760], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16939198343377365, "compression_ratio": 1.4415584415584415, "no_speech_prob": 2.012259499653557e-12}, {"id": 184, "seek": 58650, "start": 595.1, "end": 599.92, "text": " This reciprocal suppression produces a spontaneous, endless seesaw rhythm.", "tokens": [50795, 639, 46948, 36807, 14725, 257, 32744, 11, 16144, 8194, 1607, 11801, 13, 51036], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16939198343377365, "compression_ratio": 1.4415584415584415, "no_speech_prob": 2.012259499653557e-12}, {"id": 185, "seek": 59992, "start": 599.92, "end": 606.86, "text": " And today, we call these networks central pattern generators, or CPGs for short.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 965, 11, 321, 818, 613, 9590, 5777, 5102, 38662, 11, 420, 22431, 33715, 337, 2099, 13, 50712], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20480192275274367, "compression_ratio": 1.4409937888198758, "no_speech_prob": 2.088333195607306e-12}, {"id": 186, "seek": 59992, "start": 607.18, "end": 608.52, "text": " Central pattern generators.", "tokens": [50728, 9701, 5102, 38662, 13, 50795], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20480192275274367, "compression_ratio": 1.4409937888198758, "no_speech_prob": 2.088333195607306e-12}, {"id": 187, "seek": 59992, "start": 608.66, "end": 608.8399999999999, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50802, 1033, 13, 50811], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20480192275274367, "compression_ratio": 1.4409937888198758, "no_speech_prob": 2.088333195607306e-12}, {"id": 188, "seek": 59992, "start": 608.9, "end": 613.4799999999999, "text": " I need to push back on this biological reality for a second because this is where my brain got stuck.", "tokens": [50814, 286, 643, 281, 2944, 646, 322, 341, 13910, 4103, 337, 257, 1150, 570, 341, 307, 689, 452, 3567, 658, 5541, 13, 51043], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20480192275274367, "compression_ratio": 1.4409937888198758, "no_speech_prob": 2.088333195607306e-12}, {"id": 189, "seek": 59992, "start": 613.4799999999999, "end": 613.66, "text": " Sure.", "tokens": [51043, 4894, 13, 51052], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20480192275274367, "compression_ratio": 1.4409937888198758, "no_speech_prob": 2.088333195607306e-12}, {"id": 190, "seek": 59992, "start": 613.8, "end": 614.06, "text": " Go ahead.", "tokens": [51059, 1037, 2286, 13, 51072], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20480192275274367, "compression_ratio": 1.4409937888198758, "no_speech_prob": 2.088333195607306e-12}, {"id": 191, "seek": 61406, "start": 614.06, "end": 623.4, "text": " If my spine is just blindly generating this seesaw rhythm without any sensory feedback telling it where the ground is, how on earth do I adapt to a rocky trail?", "tokens": [50365, 759, 452, 15395, 307, 445, 47744, 17746, 341, 8194, 1607, 11801, 1553, 604, 27233, 5824, 3585, 309, 689, 264, 2727, 307, 11, 577, 322, 4120, 360, 286, 6231, 281, 257, 33301, 9924, 30, 50832], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09447699902104396, "compression_ratio": 1.5229007633587786, "no_speech_prob": 1.543103318735195e-12}, {"id": 192, "seek": 61406, "start": 623.4599999999999, "end": 623.7399999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50835, 1779, 13, 50849], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09447699902104396, "compression_ratio": 1.5229007633587786, "no_speech_prob": 1.543103318735195e-12}, {"id": 193, "seek": 61406, "start": 623.8599999999999, "end": 627.0999999999999, "text": " Like, if I step on a root, my ankle adjusts instantly.", "tokens": [50855, 1743, 11, 498, 286, 1823, 322, 257, 5593, 11, 452, 21999, 4369, 82, 13518, 13, 51017], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09447699902104396, "compression_ratio": 1.5229007633587786, "no_speech_prob": 1.543103318735195e-12}, {"id": 194, "seek": 61406, "start": 627.38, "end": 637.3, "text": " If Sherrington was entirely wrong, and we were just driven by this internal rhythm, wouldn't we just walk like blind, pre-programmed wind-up toys right off the edge of a cliff?", "tokens": [51031, 759, 11789, 2937, 1756, 390, 7696, 2085, 11, 293, 321, 645, 445, 9555, 538, 341, 6920, 11801, 11, 2759, 380, 321, 445, 1792, 411, 6865, 11, 659, 12, 32726, 1912, 2468, 12, 1010, 13753, 558, 766, 264, 4691, 295, 257, 22316, 30, 51527], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09447699902104396, "compression_ratio": 1.5229007633587786, "no_speech_prob": 1.543103318735195e-12}, {"id": 195, "seek": 63730, "start": 637.3, "end": 642.24, "text": " That is the exact trap many people fall into when first learning about CPGs.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 264, 1900, 11487, 867, 561, 2100, 666, 562, 700, 2539, 466, 22431, 33715, 13, 50612], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 196, "seek": 63730, "start": 642.28, "end": 642.5799999999999, "text": " Oh, good.", "tokens": [50614, 876, 11, 665, 13, 50629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 197, "seek": 63730, "start": 642.88, "end": 643.76, "text": " I'm not the only one.", "tokens": [50644, 286, 478, 406, 264, 787, 472, 13, 50688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 198, "seek": 63730, "start": 644.0, "end": 644.62, "text": " Not at all.", "tokens": [50700, 1726, 412, 439, 13, 50731], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 199, "seek": 63730, "start": 645.24, "end": 650.1999999999999, "text": " Proving that sensory feedback doesn't generate the rhythm does not mean sensory feedback is useless.", "tokens": [50762, 1705, 798, 300, 27233, 5824, 1177, 380, 8460, 264, 11801, 775, 406, 914, 27233, 5824, 307, 14115, 13, 51010], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 200, "seek": 63730, "start": 650.4799999999999, "end": 650.76, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51024, 1033, 13, 51038], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 201, "seek": 63730, "start": 651.24, "end": 656.1999999999999, "text": " Think of the central pattern generator as the engine of a car, and sensory feedback as the steering wheel.", "tokens": [51062, 6557, 295, 264, 5777, 5102, 19265, 382, 264, 2848, 295, 257, 1032, 11, 293, 27233, 5824, 382, 264, 14823, 5589, 13, 51310], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 202, "seek": 63730, "start": 656.3599999999999, "end": 657.04, "text": " Oh, I like that.", "tokens": [51318, 876, 11, 286, 411, 300, 13, 51352], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 203, "seek": 63730, "start": 657.06, "end": 660.8, "text": " The engine provides the continuous rhythmic forward momentum.", "tokens": [51353, 440, 2848, 6417, 264, 10957, 46967, 2128, 11244, 13, 51540], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13642893104909737, "compression_ratio": 1.6857142857142857, "no_speech_prob": 2.0444947818054615e-12}, {"id": 204, "seek": 66080, "start": 660.8, "end": 670.7199999999999, "text": " You don't need the steering wheel to make the car move forward, but the sensory feedback, the vision of the cliff, the feeling of the rock under your foot that modulates the rhythm.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 500, 380, 643, 264, 14823, 5589, 281, 652, 264, 1032, 1286, 2128, 11, 457, 264, 27233, 5824, 11, 264, 5201, 295, 264, 22316, 11, 264, 2633, 295, 264, 3727, 833, 428, 2671, 300, 1072, 26192, 264, 11801, 13, 50861], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 205, "seek": 66080, "start": 670.8199999999999, "end": 671.6999999999999, "text": " It steers it.", "tokens": [50866, 467, 2126, 433, 309, 13, 50910], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 206, "seek": 66080, "start": 671.76, "end": 671.9399999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50913, 1779, 13, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 207, "seek": 66080, "start": 672.02, "end": 675.02, "text": " It tweaks the timing, shifts the weight, steers the momentum.", "tokens": [50926, 467, 46664, 264, 10822, 11, 19201, 264, 3364, 11, 2126, 433, 264, 11244, 13, 51076], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 208, "seek": 66080, "start": 675.14, "end": 675.3399999999999, "text": " Ah.", "tokens": [51082, 2438, 13, 51092], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 209, "seek": 66080, "start": 675.8399999999999, "end": 678.3399999999999, "text": " So the rhythm-generating capacity is intrinsic.", "tokens": [51117, 407, 264, 11801, 12, 21848, 990, 6042, 307, 35698, 13, 51242], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 210, "seek": 66080, "start": 678.9799999999999, "end": 679.88, "text": " The engine is running.", "tokens": [51274, 440, 2848, 307, 2614, 13, 51319], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 211, "seek": 66080, "start": 680.06, "end": 683.4399999999999, "text": " The sensory input just shapes the wave as it flows.", "tokens": [51328, 440, 27233, 4846, 445, 10854, 264, 5772, 382, 309, 12867, 13, 51497], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 212, "seek": 66080, "start": 683.64, "end": 683.92, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51507, 1079, 13, 51521], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 213, "seek": 66080, "start": 684.3399999999999, "end": 689.76, "text": " A CPG specifies a coupling relationship among neural elements and lets the pattern unfold.", "tokens": [51542, 316, 22431, 38, 1608, 11221, 257, 37447, 2480, 3654, 18161, 4959, 293, 6653, 264, 5102, 17980, 13, 51813], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11772444821143335, "compression_ratio": 1.6564625850340136, "no_speech_prob": 1.4953987484064846e-12}, {"id": 214, "seek": 68976, "start": 689.76, "end": 692.3, "text": " It never computes a static target pose.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1128, 715, 1819, 257, 13437, 3779, 10774, 13, 50492], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 215, "seek": 68976, "start": 692.58, "end": 693.62, "text": " Because it's not stop motion.", "tokens": [50506, 1436, 309, 311, 406, 1590, 5394, 13, 50558], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 216, "seek": 68976, "start": 693.78, "end": 694.2, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50566, 7587, 13, 50587], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 217, "seek": 68976, "start": 694.52, "end": 697.52, "text": " The rhythm isn't a destination the biology is trying to reach.", "tokens": [50603, 440, 11801, 1943, 380, 257, 12236, 264, 14956, 307, 1382, 281, 2524, 13, 50753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 218, "seek": 68976, "start": 697.64, "end": 699.74, "text": " It is simply what the biology does.", "tokens": [50759, 467, 307, 2935, 437, 264, 14956, 775, 13, 50864], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 219, "seek": 68976, "start": 700.18, "end": 705.76, "text": " Any physical joint trajectory you see on the outside is just a physical reading of that ongoing internal activity.", "tokens": [50886, 2639, 4001, 7225, 21512, 291, 536, 322, 264, 2380, 307, 445, 257, 4001, 3760, 295, 300, 10452, 6920, 5191, 13, 51165], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 220, "seek": 68976, "start": 706.48, "end": 709.52, "text": " Infliction makes the point that roboticists eventually caught on to this.", "tokens": [51201, 682, 3423, 4105, 1669, 264, 935, 300, 30468, 1751, 4728, 5415, 322, 281, 341, 13, 51353], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 221, "seek": 68976, "start": 709.6, "end": 709.72, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51357, 1779, 13, 51363], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 222, "seek": 68976, "start": 709.76, "end": 710.36, "text": " They did, yeah.", "tokens": [51365, 814, 630, 11, 1338, 13, 51395], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 223, "seek": 68976, "start": 710.8199999999999, "end": 717.76, "text": " They realized they didn't need to painfully compute inverse kinematics for every millisecond of a walk cycle.", "tokens": [51418, 814, 5334, 436, 994, 380, 643, 281, 1822, 2277, 14722, 17340, 15784, 37541, 337, 633, 27940, 18882, 295, 257, 1792, 6586, 13, 51765], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13813978576660157, "compression_ratio": 1.630718954248366, "no_speech_prob": 1.687529022770251e-12}, {"id": 224, "seek": 71776, "start": 717.76, "end": 722.76, "text": " They could just build mathematical engines that mimic these biological central pattern generators.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 727, 445, 1322, 18894, 12982, 300, 31075, 613, 13910, 5777, 5102, 38662, 13, 50615], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 225, "seek": 71776, "start": 723.52, "end": 723.8, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50653, 1779, 13, 50667], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 226, "seek": 71776, "start": 723.96, "end": 732.02, "text": " They reduced the messy neurology of a cat's spine into elegant mathematical models of coupled nonlinear oscillators.", "tokens": [50675, 814, 9212, 264, 16191, 28351, 88, 295, 257, 3857, 311, 15395, 666, 21117, 18894, 5245, 295, 29482, 2107, 28263, 18225, 3391, 13, 51078], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 227, "seek": 71776, "start": 732.3, "end": 735.48, "text": " And the standard math for this is the Kuramoto model, isn't it?", "tokens": [51092, 400, 264, 3832, 5221, 337, 341, 307, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 11, 1943, 380, 309, 30, 51251], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 228, "seek": 71776, "start": 735.52, "end": 735.84, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51253, 1079, 13, 51269], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 229, "seek": 71776, "start": 736.14, "end": 739.66, "text": " The standard mathematical treatment that emerged for this is the Kuramoto model.", "tokens": [51284, 440, 3832, 18894, 5032, 300, 20178, 337, 341, 307, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 13, 51460], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 230, "seek": 71776, "start": 740.48, "end": 745.04, "text": " Yoshiki Kuramoto was a physicist who wanted to understand synchronization in nature.", "tokens": [51501, 38949, 9850, 16481, 35858, 390, 257, 42466, 567, 1415, 281, 1223, 19331, 2144, 294, 3687, 13, 51729], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 231, "seek": 71776, "start": 745.26, "end": 746.14, "text": " Like fireflies.", "tokens": [51740, 1743, 2610, 24471, 13, 51784], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15733685316862883, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 2.333731515327675e-12}, {"id": 232, "seek": 74614, "start": 746.14, "end": 746.78, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50397], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 233, "seek": 74614, "start": 747.5, "end": 750.14, "text": " Have you ever seen videos of fireflies in Southeast Asia?", "tokens": [50433, 3560, 291, 1562, 1612, 2145, 295, 2610, 24471, 294, 27906, 10038, 30, 50565], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 234, "seek": 74614, "start": 750.88, "end": 756.96, "text": " Thousands of them in a forest will randomly flash, but eventually they all synchronize and flash at the exact same time.", "tokens": [50602, 40535, 295, 552, 294, 257, 6719, 486, 16979, 7319, 11, 457, 4728, 436, 439, 19331, 1125, 293, 7319, 412, 264, 1900, 912, 565, 13, 50906], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 235, "seek": 74614, "start": 757.0, "end": 757.3, "text": " Beautiful.", "tokens": [50908, 14724, 13, 50923], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 236, "seek": 74614, "start": 757.46, "end": 759.4399999999999, "text": " Or consider the pacemaker cells in your heart.", "tokens": [50931, 1610, 1949, 264, 15165, 49523, 5438, 294, 428, 1917, 13, 51030], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 237, "seek": 74614, "start": 759.68, "end": 764.54, "text": " They all have slightly different natural firing rates, but they couple together to beat as one.", "tokens": [51042, 814, 439, 362, 4748, 819, 3303, 16045, 6846, 11, 457, 436, 1916, 1214, 281, 4224, 382, 472, 13, 51285], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 238, "seek": 74614, "start": 764.8199999999999, "end": 765.12, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51299, 1779, 13, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 239, "seek": 74614, "start": 765.4, "end": 773.76, "text": " Kuramoto developed a master equation to describe how populations of oscillating things influence each other and lock into a single shared rhythm.", "tokens": [51328, 16481, 35858, 4743, 257, 4505, 5367, 281, 6786, 577, 12822, 295, 18225, 990, 721, 6503, 1184, 661, 293, 4017, 666, 257, 2167, 5507, 11801, 13, 51746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13183980283483995, "compression_ratio": 1.5935483870967742, "no_speech_prob": 2.8823341283179538e-12}, {"id": 240, "seek": 77376, "start": 773.76, "end": 776.72, "text": " So robotics engineers started using the Kuramoto model.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 34145, 11955, 1409, 1228, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 13, 50513], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15355487491773523, "compression_ratio": 1.3566433566433567, "no_speech_prob": 1.6228949607788312e-12}, {"id": 241, "seek": 77376, "start": 777.0, "end": 784.36, "text": " They would assign one mathematical oscillator, like an invisible swinging pendulum to the hip, one to the knee, one to the ankle.", "tokens": [50527, 814, 576, 6269, 472, 18894, 43859, 11, 411, 364, 14603, 29500, 44103, 281, 264, 8103, 11, 472, 281, 264, 9434, 11, 472, 281, 264, 21999, 13, 50895], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15355487491773523, "compression_ratio": 1.3566433566433567, "no_speech_prob": 1.6228949607788312e-12}, {"id": 242, "seek": 77376, "start": 784.46, "end": 784.88, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50900, 7587, 13, 50921], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15355487491773523, "compression_ratio": 1.3566433566433567, "no_speech_prob": 1.6228949607788312e-12}, {"id": 243, "seek": 78488, "start": 784.88, "end": 790.58, "text": " And by mathematically coupling these pendulums together, they could enforce a rhythm.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 538, 44003, 37447, 613, 12179, 425, 8099, 1214, 11, 436, 727, 24825, 257, 11801, 13, 50650], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1285289098631661, "compression_ratio": 1.463768115942029, "no_speech_prob": 1.668501057802696e-12}, {"id": 244, "seek": 78488, "start": 791.12, "end": 797.98, "text": " If you want a robot to hop, you couple the left leg and right leg pendulums in phase, so they swing together.", "tokens": [50677, 759, 291, 528, 257, 7881, 281, 3818, 11, 291, 1916, 264, 1411, 1676, 293, 558, 1676, 12179, 425, 8099, 294, 5574, 11, 370, 436, 11173, 1214, 13, 51020], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1285289098631661, "compression_ratio": 1.463768115942029, "no_speech_prob": 1.668501057802696e-12}, {"id": 245, "seek": 78488, "start": 798.14, "end": 798.38, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51028, 1779, 13, 51040], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1285289098631661, "compression_ratio": 1.463768115942029, "no_speech_prob": 1.668501057802696e-12}, {"id": 246, "seek": 79838, "start": 798.38, "end": 800.52, "text": " If you wanted to walk, you couple them out of phase.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 291, 1415, 281, 1792, 11, 291, 1916, 552, 484, 295, 5574, 13, 50472], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1746179055476534, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.5305416439445607e-12}, {"id": 247, "seek": 79838, "start": 800.74, "end": 802.86, "text": " You aren't coding lift leg four inches.", "tokens": [50483, 509, 3212, 380, 17720, 5533, 1676, 1451, 8478, 13, 50589], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1746179055476534, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.5305416439445607e-12}, {"id": 248, "seek": 79838, "start": 803.34, "end": 809.72, "text": " You were just spinning these mathematical pendulums in the software and letting the physical motors of the robot drag behind the math.", "tokens": [50613, 509, 645, 445, 15640, 613, 18894, 12179, 425, 8099, 294, 264, 4722, 293, 8295, 264, 4001, 25035, 295, 264, 7881, 5286, 2261, 264, 5221, 13, 50932], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1746179055476534, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.5305416439445607e-12}, {"id": 249, "seek": 79838, "start": 809.9399999999999, "end": 812.66, "text": " It is a vastly more efficient way to generate locomotion.", "tokens": [50943, 467, 307, 257, 41426, 544, 7148, 636, 281, 8460, 36369, 19228, 13, 51079], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1746179055476534, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.5305416439445607e-12}, {"id": 250, "seek": 81266, "start": 812.66, "end": 816.36, "text": " But here is where Fliction's paper takes a massive leap.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 510, 307, 689, 3235, 4105, 311, 3035, 2516, 257, 5994, 19438, 13, 50550], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 251, "seek": 81266, "start": 816.62, "end": 816.66, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50563, 1033, 13, 50565], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 252, "seek": 81266, "start": 816.9599999999999, "end": 821.74, "text": " CPGs and Kuramoto oscillators prove that intrinsic rhythms drive movement.", "tokens": [50580, 22431, 33715, 293, 16481, 35858, 18225, 3391, 7081, 300, 35698, 44892, 3332, 3963, 13, 50819], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 253, "seek": 81266, "start": 822.2199999999999, "end": 828.3199999999999, "text": " But how do we describe the actual physical shape of those rhythmic trajectories in three-dimensional space?", "tokens": [50843, 583, 577, 360, 321, 6786, 264, 3539, 4001, 3909, 295, 729, 46967, 18257, 2083, 294, 1045, 12, 18759, 1901, 30, 51148], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 254, "seek": 81266, "start": 828.36, "end": 830.54, "text": " Right, because a pendulum in a computer isn't a leg.", "tokens": [51150, 1779, 11, 570, 257, 44103, 294, 257, 3820, 1943, 380, 257, 1676, 13, 51259], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 255, "seek": 81266, "start": 830.74, "end": 831.24, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51269, 7587, 13, 51294], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 256, "seek": 81266, "start": 831.92, "end": 839.76, "text": " To bridge the gap between the spinning math and the physical leg, Fliction introduces a concept from complex geometry called the amplet twist.", "tokens": [51328, 1407, 7283, 264, 7417, 1296, 264, 15640, 5221, 293, 264, 4001, 1676, 11, 3235, 4105, 31472, 257, 3410, 490, 3997, 18426, 1219, 264, 669, 14657, 8203, 13, 51720], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 257, "seek": 81266, "start": 840.14, "end": 841.74, "text": " Okay, here's where it gets really interesting.", "tokens": [51739, 1033, 11, 510, 311, 689, 309, 2170, 534, 1880, 13, 51819], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16129692462312073, "compression_ratio": 1.603225806451613, "no_speech_prob": 1.4668386947788714e-12}, {"id": 258, "seek": 84174, "start": 841.74, "end": 849.38, "text": " When I hit the section on the amplet twist, I had to read it three times, but once it clicked, it felt like discovering a Rosetta Stone.", "tokens": [50365, 1133, 286, 2045, 264, 3541, 322, 264, 669, 14657, 8203, 11, 286, 632, 281, 1401, 309, 1045, 1413, 11, 457, 1564, 309, 23370, 11, 309, 2762, 411, 24773, 257, 11144, 16593, 15012, 13, 50747], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11572357616593353, "compression_ratio": 1.5758620689655172, "no_speech_prob": 1.319893738575828e-12}, {"id": 259, "seek": 84174, "start": 849.6, "end": 851.1800000000001, "text": " It really ties it all together.", "tokens": [50758, 467, 534, 14039, 309, 439, 1214, 13, 50837], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11572357616593353, "compression_ratio": 1.5758620689655172, "no_speech_prob": 1.319893738575828e-12}, {"id": 260, "seek": 84174, "start": 851.5, "end": 858.0600000000001, "text": " To explain this, we have to dip our toes into complex numbers, but I promise we'll keep it grounded for you listening.", "tokens": [50853, 1407, 2903, 341, 11, 321, 362, 281, 10460, 527, 14681, 666, 3997, 3547, 11, 457, 286, 6228, 321, 603, 1066, 309, 23535, 337, 291, 4764, 13, 51181], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11572357616593353, "compression_ratio": 1.5758620689655172, "no_speech_prob": 1.319893738575828e-12}, {"id": 261, "seek": 84174, "start": 858.78, "end": 864.1, "text": " Fliction cites a mathematician named Tristan Needham who wrote a book called Visual Complex Analysis.", "tokens": [51217, 3235, 4105, 269, 3324, 257, 48281, 4926, 1765, 7559, 16984, 4822, 567, 4114, 257, 1446, 1219, 23187, 41184, 38172, 13, 51483], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11572357616593353, "compression_ratio": 1.5758620689655172, "no_speech_prob": 1.319893738575828e-12}, {"id": 262, "seek": 84174, "start": 864.3, "end": 864.84, "text": " A classic.", "tokens": [51493, 316, 7230, 13, 51520], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11572357616593353, "compression_ratio": 1.5758620689655172, "no_speech_prob": 1.319893738575828e-12}, {"id": 263, "seek": 84174, "start": 865.2, "end": 868.46, "text": " Needham looked at how complex functions transform space,", "tokens": [51538, 16984, 4822, 2956, 412, 577, 3997, 6828, 4088, 1901, 11, 51701], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11572357616593353, "compression_ratio": 1.5758620689655172, "no_speech_prob": 1.319893738575828e-12}, {"id": 264, "seek": 86846, "start": 868.46, "end": 876.96, "text": " and he realized you can break down any local instantaneous transformation into two incredibly simple physical actions.", "tokens": [50365, 293, 415, 5334, 291, 393, 1821, 760, 604, 2654, 45596, 9887, 666, 732, 6252, 2199, 4001, 5909, 13, 50790], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17461607330723813, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722642813740471e-12}, {"id": 265, "seek": 86846, "start": 877.38, "end": 879.3000000000001, "text": " A scaling and a rotation.", "tokens": [50811, 316, 21589, 293, 257, 12447, 13, 50907], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17461607330723813, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722642813740471e-12}, {"id": 266, "seek": 86846, "start": 879.52, "end": 879.72, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50918, 1779, 13, 50928], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17461607330723813, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722642813740471e-12}, {"id": 267, "seek": 86846, "start": 879.9000000000001, "end": 884.76, "text": " Needham called the scaling an amplification, literally stretching or shrinking the space.", "tokens": [50937, 16984, 4822, 1219, 264, 21589, 364, 9731, 3774, 11, 3736, 19632, 420, 41684, 264, 1901, 13, 51180], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17461607330723813, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722642813740471e-12}, {"id": 268, "seek": 86846, "start": 884.96, "end": 887.0, "text": " And he called the rotation a twist.", "tokens": [51190, 400, 415, 1219, 264, 12447, 257, 8203, 13, 51292], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17461607330723813, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722642813740471e-12}, {"id": 269, "seek": 86846, "start": 887.24, "end": 888.76, "text": " Put them together and you get an ampliwis.", "tokens": [51304, 4935, 552, 1214, 293, 291, 483, 364, 9731, 72, 86, 271, 13, 51380], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17461607330723813, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.3722642813740471e-12}, {"id": 270, "seek": 88876, "start": 888.76, "end": 889.2, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18758365382318912, "compression_ratio": 1.6255707762557077, "no_speech_prob": 1.4266196730894354e-12}, {"id": 271, "seek": 88876, "start": 889.56, "end": 892.02, "text": " Mathematically, it's represented by a single complex number.", "tokens": [50405, 15776, 40197, 11, 309, 311, 10379, 538, 257, 2167, 3997, 1230, 13, 50528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18758365382318912, "compression_ratio": 1.6255707762557077, "no_speech_prob": 1.4266196730894354e-12}, {"id": 272, "seek": 88876, "start": 892.56, "end": 896.36, "text": " It has an amplitude, which we'll call R, representing the scale of the stretch.", "tokens": [50555, 467, 575, 364, 27433, 11, 597, 321, 603, 818, 497, 11, 13460, 264, 4373, 295, 264, 5985, 13, 50745], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18758365382318912, "compression_ratio": 1.6255707762557077, "no_speech_prob": 1.4266196730894354e-12}, {"id": 273, "seek": 88876, "start": 896.52, "end": 896.66, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50753, 1033, 13, 50760], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18758365382318912, "compression_ratio": 1.6255707762557077, "no_speech_prob": 1.4266196730894354e-12}, {"id": 274, "seek": 88876, "start": 896.8, "end": 901.14, "text": " And it has a phase angle, which we'll call CI, representing the direction of the twist.", "tokens": [50767, 400, 309, 575, 257, 5574, 5802, 11, 597, 321, 603, 818, 37777, 11, 13460, 264, 3513, 295, 264, 8203, 13, 50984], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18758365382318912, "compression_ratio": 1.6255707762557077, "no_speech_prob": 1.4266196730894354e-12}, {"id": 275, "seek": 88876, "start": 901.64, "end": 909.12, "text": " Every microscopic fraction of a movement can be described purely by amplifying it by R and twisting it by CI-SI.", "tokens": [51009, 2048, 47897, 14135, 295, 257, 3963, 393, 312, 7619, 17491, 538, 9731, 5489, 309, 538, 497, 293, 34491, 309, 538, 37777, 12, 20262, 13, 51383], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18758365382318912, "compression_ratio": 1.6255707762557077, "no_speech_prob": 1.4266196730894354e-12}, {"id": 276, "seek": 90912, "start": 909.12, "end": 912.14, "text": " So the ampliwis doesn't care about the global path.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 264, 9731, 72, 86, 271, 1177, 380, 1127, 466, 264, 4338, 3100, 13, 50516], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18160234798084607, "compression_ratio": 1.5203619909502262, "no_speech_prob": 2.100147096159577e-12}, {"id": 277, "seek": 90912, "start": 912.5, "end": 914.88, "text": " It doesn't know you are walking to the grocery store.", "tokens": [50534, 467, 1177, 380, 458, 291, 366, 4494, 281, 264, 14410, 3531, 13, 50653], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18160234798084607, "compression_ratio": 1.5203619909502262, "no_speech_prob": 2.100147096159577e-12}, {"id": 278, "seek": 90912, "start": 914.98, "end": 915.6, "text": " Not at all.", "tokens": [50658, 1726, 412, 439, 13, 50689], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18160234798084607, "compression_ratio": 1.5203619909502262, "no_speech_prob": 2.100147096159577e-12}, {"id": 279, "seek": 90912, "start": 915.78, "end": 918.34, "text": " It just dictates the instantaneous law of motion.", "tokens": [50698, 467, 445, 12569, 1024, 264, 45596, 2101, 295, 5394, 13, 50826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18160234798084607, "compression_ratio": 1.5203619909502262, "no_speech_prob": 2.100147096159577e-12}, {"id": 280, "seek": 90912, "start": 918.5, "end": 925.66, "text": " Like right at this very millisecond, the mathematical rule generating this movement is amplifying by R and twisting by CI.", "tokens": [50834, 1743, 558, 412, 341, 588, 27940, 18882, 11, 264, 18894, 4978, 17746, 341, 3963, 307, 9731, 5489, 538, 497, 293, 34491, 538, 37777, 13, 51192], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18160234798084607, "compression_ratio": 1.5203619909502262, "no_speech_prob": 2.100147096159577e-12}, {"id": 281, "seek": 90912, "start": 926.04, "end": 928.14, "text": " And this is where fliction connects the dots.", "tokens": [51211, 400, 341, 307, 689, 932, 4105, 16967, 264, 15026, 13, 51316], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18160234798084607, "compression_ratio": 1.5203619909502262, "no_speech_prob": 2.100147096159577e-12}, {"id": 282, "seek": 92814, "start": 928.14, "end": 941.6, "text": " In the Kuramoto model of coupled oscillators, the math running our robotic CPGs, scientists already use a specific variable called a complex order parameter to track how perfectly synchronized all the pendulums are.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 295, 29482, 18225, 3391, 11, 264, 5221, 2614, 527, 30468, 22431, 33715, 11, 7708, 1217, 764, 257, 2685, 7006, 1219, 257, 3997, 1668, 13075, 281, 2837, 577, 6239, 19331, 1602, 439, 264, 12179, 425, 8099, 366, 13, 51038], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08790823687677798, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.076630967878801e-12}, {"id": 283, "seek": 92814, "start": 941.9399999999999, "end": 948.88, "text": " And the equation for this order parameter happens to be Z of T equals R of T times E to the ICI of T.", "tokens": [51055, 400, 264, 5367, 337, 341, 1668, 13075, 2314, 281, 312, 1176, 295, 314, 6915, 497, 295, 314, 1413, 462, 281, 264, 14360, 40, 295, 314, 13, 51402], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08790823687677798, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.076630967878801e-12}, {"id": 284, "seek": 92814, "start": 949.1999999999999, "end": 949.4399999999999, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51418, 1079, 13, 51430], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08790823687677798, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.076630967878801e-12}, {"id": 285, "seek": 92814, "start": 949.54, "end": 951.98, "text": " Which are the exact same variables, R and CII.", "tokens": [51435, 3013, 366, 264, 1900, 912, 9102, 11, 497, 293, 37777, 40, 13, 51557], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08790823687677798, "compression_ratio": 1.5185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 2.076630967878801e-12}, {"id": 286, "seek": 95198, "start": 951.98, "end": 952.46, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50389], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1430175204236968, "compression_ratio": 1.6795774647887325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6490406045885364e-12}, {"id": 287, "seek": 95198, "start": 952.7, "end": 958.74, "text": " What's fascinating here is that in the Kuramoto model, the amplitude R represents the degree of phase synchronization.", "tokens": [50401, 708, 311, 10343, 510, 307, 300, 294, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 11, 264, 27433, 497, 8855, 264, 4314, 295, 5574, 19331, 2144, 13, 50703], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1430175204236968, "compression_ratio": 1.6795774647887325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6490406045885364e-12}, {"id": 288, "seek": 95198, "start": 958.94, "end": 959.1800000000001, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50713, 1033, 13, 50725], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1430175204236968, "compression_ratio": 1.6795774647887325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6490406045885364e-12}, {"id": 289, "seek": 95198, "start": 959.38, "end": 965.08, "text": " It's a number from zero to one that tells you how perfectly aligned all the fireflies or all the robotic joints are.", "tokens": [50735, 467, 311, 257, 1230, 490, 4018, 281, 472, 300, 5112, 291, 577, 6239, 17962, 439, 264, 2610, 24471, 420, 439, 264, 30468, 19949, 366, 13, 51020], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1430175204236968, "compression_ratio": 1.6795774647887325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6490406045885364e-12}, {"id": 290, "seek": 95198, "start": 965.58, "end": 969.48, "text": " And size I represents the mean phase, the common direction they are all heading.", "tokens": [51045, 400, 2744, 286, 8855, 264, 914, 5574, 11, 264, 2689, 3513, 436, 366, 439, 9864, 13, 51240], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1430175204236968, "compression_ratio": 1.6795774647887325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6490406045885364e-12}, {"id": 291, "seek": 95198, "start": 969.9, "end": 976.6800000000001, "text": " Fliction's thesis is that this Kuramoto order parameter isn't just analogous to an amplitwist.", "tokens": [51261, 3235, 4105, 311, 22288, 307, 300, 341, 16481, 35858, 1668, 13075, 1943, 380, 445, 16660, 563, 281, 364, 9731, 270, 86, 468, 13, 51600], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1430175204236968, "compression_ratio": 1.6795774647887325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6490406045885364e-12}, {"id": 292, "seek": 95198, "start": 977.02, "end": 980.72, "text": " It is an amplitwist operator without any modification.", "tokens": [51617, 467, 307, 364, 9731, 270, 86, 468, 12973, 1553, 604, 26747, 13, 51802], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1430175204236968, "compression_ratio": 1.6795774647887325, "no_speech_prob": 1.6490406045885364e-12}, {"id": 293, "seek": 98072, "start": 980.72, "end": 983.0, "text": " I tried to visualize this with an analogy.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 3031, 281, 23273, 341, 365, 364, 21663, 13, 50479], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 294, "seek": 98072, "start": 983.5, "end": 984.2, "text": " Tell me if this works.", "tokens": [50504, 5115, 385, 498, 341, 1985, 13, 50539], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 295, "seek": 98072, "start": 984.6600000000001, "end": 985.78, "text": " Imagine a marching band.", "tokens": [50562, 11739, 257, 30523, 4116, 13, 50618], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 296, "seek": 98072, "start": 986.44, "end": 991.1, "text": " Let's say the individual joints and muscles in a robot's leg are the members of the band.", "tokens": [50651, 961, 311, 584, 264, 2609, 19949, 293, 9530, 294, 257, 7881, 311, 1676, 366, 264, 2679, 295, 264, 4116, 13, 50884], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 297, "seek": 98072, "start": 991.1800000000001, "end": 991.38, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50888, 1033, 13, 50898], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 298, "seek": 98072, "start": 991.48, "end": 991.86, "text": " I like that.", "tokens": [50903, 286, 411, 300, 13, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 299, "seek": 98072, "start": 991.94, "end": 996.6, "text": " The twist, the scius is the direction of the music, the underlying beat of the march.", "tokens": [50926, 440, 8203, 11, 264, 2180, 301, 307, 264, 3513, 295, 264, 1318, 11, 264, 14217, 4224, 295, 264, 8368, 13, 51159], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 300, "seek": 98072, "start": 996.96, "end": 1003.1600000000001, "text": " The amplitude, the R, is how perfectly synchronized every single band member is stepping in time with each other.", "tokens": [51177, 440, 27433, 11, 264, 497, 11, 307, 577, 6239, 19331, 1602, 633, 2167, 4116, 4006, 307, 16821, 294, 565, 365, 1184, 661, 13, 51487], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 301, "seek": 98072, "start": 1003.24, "end": 1003.52, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51491, 1779, 13, 51505], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 302, "seek": 98072, "start": 1003.86, "end": 1008.1600000000001, "text": " If half the band is on the left foot and half is wandering around on the right, it's total chaos.", "tokens": [51522, 759, 1922, 264, 4116, 307, 322, 264, 1411, 2671, 293, 1922, 307, 26396, 926, 322, 264, 558, 11, 309, 311, 3217, 14158, 13, 51737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 303, "seek": 98072, "start": 1008.1600000000001, "end": 1009.94, "text": " The amplitude, R, is close to zero.", "tokens": [51737, 440, 27433, 11, 497, 11, 307, 1998, 281, 4018, 13, 51826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14881428569352545, "compression_ratio": 1.7419354838709677, "no_speech_prob": 1.610600758664149e-12}, {"id": 304, "seek": 101072, "start": 1010.72, "end": 1014.96, "text": " But if they are perfectly locked in step, stepping is one single unit, R goes up to one.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 498, 436, 366, 6239, 9376, 294, 1823, 11, 16821, 307, 472, 2167, 4985, 11, 497, 1709, 493, 281, 472, 13, 50577], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12486995475879614, "compression_ratio": 1.4628571428571429, "no_speech_prob": 1.5425372567809403e-12}, {"id": 305, "seek": 101072, "start": 1015.1600000000001, "end": 1022.08, "text": " The marching band works, but to make it fit the physics of the math, imagine if the band members were physically bound to one another with bungee cords.", "tokens": [50587, 440, 30523, 4116, 1985, 11, 457, 281, 652, 309, 3318, 264, 10649, 295, 264, 5221, 11, 3811, 498, 264, 4116, 2679, 645, 9762, 5472, 281, 472, 1071, 365, 6702, 31577, 36302, 13, 50933], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12486995475879614, "compression_ratio": 1.4628571428571429, "no_speech_prob": 1.5425372567809403e-12}, {"id": 306, "seek": 101072, "start": 1022.1800000000001, "end": 1022.86, "text": " Oh, wow.", "tokens": [50938, 876, 11, 6076, 13, 50972], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12486995475879614, "compression_ratio": 1.4628571428571429, "no_speech_prob": 1.5425372567809403e-12}, {"id": 307, "seek": 101072, "start": 1023.1800000000001, "end": 1023.44, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50988, 1033, 13, 51001], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12486995475879614, "compression_ratio": 1.4628571428571429, "no_speech_prob": 1.5425372567809403e-12}, {"id": 308, "seek": 102344, "start": 1023.44, "end": 1030.18, "text": " Because in the math, as the coupling strength increases, as those bungee cords get tighter and tighter, they force everyone into line.", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 294, 264, 5221, 11, 382, 264, 37447, 3800, 8637, 11, 382, 729, 6702, 31577, 36302, 483, 30443, 293, 30443, 11, 436, 3464, 1518, 666, 1622, 13, 50702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13698305085647938, "compression_ratio": 1.5251141552511416, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014856762432527e-12}, {"id": 309, "seek": 102344, "start": 1030.5800000000002, "end": 1031.6200000000001, "text": " The variance collapses.", "tokens": [50722, 440, 21977, 48765, 13, 50774], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13698305085647938, "compression_ratio": 1.5251141552511416, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014856762432527e-12}, {"id": 310, "seek": 102344, "start": 1031.8400000000001, "end": 1033.42, "text": " The amplitude, R, approaches one.", "tokens": [50785, 440, 27433, 11, 497, 11, 11587, 472, 13, 50864], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13698305085647938, "compression_ratio": 1.5251141552511416, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014856762432527e-12}, {"id": 311, "seek": 102344, "start": 1033.68, "end": 1033.98, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50877, 1779, 13, 50892], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13698305085647938, "compression_ratio": 1.5251141552511416, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014856762432527e-12}, {"id": 312, "seek": 102344, "start": 1034.24, "end": 1037.74, "text": " And what happens physically to the leg when the band locks perfectly?", "tokens": [50905, 400, 437, 2314, 9762, 281, 264, 1676, 562, 264, 4116, 20703, 6239, 30, 51080], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13698305085647938, "compression_ratio": 1.5251141552511416, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014856762432527e-12}, {"id": 313, "seek": 102344, "start": 1037.96, "end": 1041.04, "text": " It becomes a rigid, fully synchronized gate.", "tokens": [51091, 467, 3643, 257, 22195, 11, 4498, 19331, 1602, 8539, 13, 51245], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13698305085647938, "compression_ratio": 1.5251141552511416, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014856762432527e-12}, {"id": 314, "seek": 102344, "start": 1041.18, "end": 1042.18, "text": " So they act as one.", "tokens": [51252, 407, 436, 605, 382, 472, 13, 51302], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13698305085647938, "compression_ratio": 1.5251141552511416, "no_speech_prob": 1.5014856762432527e-12}, {"id": 315, "seek": 104218, "start": 1042.18, "end": 1042.8200000000002, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50397], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21528464097243089, "compression_ratio": 1.5666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487951412166857e-12}, {"id": 316, "seek": 104218, "start": 1043.18, "end": 1046.2, "text": " The entire population of oscillators acts as one.", "tokens": [50415, 440, 2302, 4415, 295, 18225, 3391, 10672, 382, 472, 13, 50566], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21528464097243089, "compression_ratio": 1.5666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487951412166857e-12}, {"id": 317, "seek": 104218, "start": 1046.6200000000001, "end": 1050.1000000000001, "text": " The population amplitwist degenerates into pure rotation.", "tokens": [50587, 440, 4415, 9731, 270, 86, 468, 40520, 1024, 666, 6075, 12447, 13, 50761], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21528464097243089, "compression_ratio": 1.5666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487951412166857e-12}, {"id": 318, "seek": 104218, "start": 1050.64, "end": 1052.72, "text": " Your marching band isn't just a metaphor.", "tokens": [50788, 2260, 30523, 4116, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 19157, 13, 50892], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21528464097243089, "compression_ratio": 1.5666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487951412166857e-12}, {"id": 319, "seek": 104218, "start": 1053.24, "end": 1059.7, "text": " The mathematical measure of their synchronization literally acts as the geometric scaling and rotation of the physical leg.", "tokens": [50918, 440, 18894, 3481, 295, 641, 19331, 2144, 3736, 10672, 382, 264, 33246, 21589, 293, 12447, 295, 264, 4001, 1676, 13, 51241], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.21528464097243089, "compression_ratio": 1.5666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.6487951412166857e-12}, {"id": 320, "seek": 105970, "start": 1059.7, "end": 1060.8400000000001, "text": " That is stunning.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 18550, 13, 50422], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 321, "seek": 105970, "start": 1061.5800000000002, "end": 1067.1200000000001, "text": " The synchronization of the biological network directly maps onto the geometric shape of the physical movement.", "tokens": [50459, 440, 19331, 2144, 295, 264, 13910, 3209, 3838, 11317, 3911, 264, 33246, 3909, 295, 264, 4001, 3963, 13, 50736], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 322, "seek": 105970, "start": 1067.44, "end": 1067.88, "text": " It does.", "tokens": [50752, 467, 775, 13, 50774], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 323, "seek": 105970, "start": 1068.16, "end": 1073.18, "text": " But the paper does include a technical caveat here about where this amplitude, R, comes from.", "tokens": [50788, 583, 264, 3035, 775, 4090, 257, 6191, 43012, 510, 466, 689, 341, 27433, 11, 497, 11, 1487, 490, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 324, "seek": 105970, "start": 1073.26, "end": 1073.44, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51043, 1779, 13, 51052], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 325, "seek": 105970, "start": 1073.54, "end": 1077.4, "text": " Specifically warning robotics engineers not to confuse it with another variable.", "tokens": [51057, 26058, 9164, 34145, 11955, 406, 281, 28584, 309, 365, 1071, 7006, 13, 51250], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 326, "seek": 105970, "start": 1077.5800000000002, "end": 1079.18, "text": " It's a necessary clarification.", "tokens": [51259, 467, 311, 257, 4818, 34449, 13, 51339], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 327, "seek": 105970, "start": 1080.06, "end": 1086.04, "text": " In applied robotics, engineers often model the individual pendulums using something called a Hopf normal form.", "tokens": [51383, 682, 6456, 34145, 11, 11955, 2049, 2316, 264, 2609, 12179, 425, 8099, 1228, 746, 1219, 257, 13438, 69, 2710, 1254, 13, 51682], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.158434821564017, "compression_ratio": 1.6041666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.889939160032439e-12}, {"id": 328, "seek": 108604, "start": 1086.04, "end": 1091.42, "text": " Without getting bogged down in the equations, a Hopf oscillator has its own internal amplitude.", "tokens": [50365, 9129, 1242, 26132, 3004, 760, 294, 264, 11787, 11, 257, 13438, 69, 43859, 575, 1080, 1065, 6920, 27433, 13, 50634], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 329, "seek": 108604, "start": 1092.0, "end": 1095.48, "text": " It describes how wide the individual pendulum swings back and forth.", "tokens": [50663, 467, 15626, 577, 4874, 264, 2609, 44103, 32386, 646, 293, 5220, 13, 50837], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 330, "seek": 108604, "start": 1095.6, "end": 1096.94, "text": " Like how far you pull a swing back.", "tokens": [50843, 1743, 577, 1400, 291, 2235, 257, 11173, 646, 13, 50910], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 331, "seek": 108604, "start": 1097.1399999999999, "end": 1097.6, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50920, 7587, 13, 50943], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 332, "seek": 108604, "start": 1098.2, "end": 1105.2, "text": " Fliction strictly clarifies that the R in the amplitwist theory is not the amplitude of a single pendulum swing.", "tokens": [50973, 3235, 4105, 20792, 6093, 11221, 300, 264, 497, 294, 264, 9731, 270, 86, 468, 5261, 307, 406, 264, 27433, 295, 257, 2167, 44103, 11173, 13, 51323], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 333, "seek": 108604, "start": 1105.5, "end": 1108.68, "text": " It is strictly the population level coherence.", "tokens": [51338, 467, 307, 20792, 264, 4415, 1496, 26528, 655, 13, 51497], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 334, "seek": 108604, "start": 1109.24, "end": 1113.28, "text": " It only measures how tightly the whole group of pendulums is locked together.", "tokens": [51525, 467, 787, 8000, 577, 21952, 264, 1379, 1594, 295, 12179, 425, 8099, 307, 9376, 1214, 13, 51727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 335, "seek": 108604, "start": 1113.46, "end": 1113.8799999999999, "text": " Got it.", "tokens": [51736, 5803, 309, 13, 51757], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18753652657027794, "compression_ratio": 1.691449814126394, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111093137360146e-12}, {"id": 336, "seek": 111388, "start": 1113.88, "end": 1121.72, "text": " So it's the tightness of the bungee cords holding the marching band together, not how high one specific trumpet player is lifting his knees.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 309, 311, 264, 4524, 1287, 295, 264, 6702, 31577, 36302, 5061, 264, 30523, 4116, 1214, 11, 406, 577, 1090, 472, 2685, 35160, 4256, 307, 15798, 702, 10546, 13, 50757], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 337, "seek": 111388, "start": 1121.8400000000001, "end": 1122.8000000000002, "text": " A vital distinction.", "tokens": [50763, 316, 11707, 16844, 13, 50811], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 338, "seek": 111388, "start": 1123.5400000000002, "end": 1129.8600000000001, "text": " Okay, so now we have this incredibly elegant mathematical language for a single limb acting like a synchronized marching band.", "tokens": [50848, 1033, 11, 370, 586, 321, 362, 341, 6252, 21117, 18894, 2856, 337, 257, 2167, 30390, 6577, 411, 257, 19331, 1602, 30523, 4116, 13, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 339, "seek": 111388, "start": 1130.2600000000002, "end": 1132.66, "text": " But a body isn't just one limb.", "tokens": [51184, 583, 257, 1772, 1943, 380, 445, 472, 30390, 13, 51304], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 340, "seek": 111388, "start": 1132.94, "end": 1133.8000000000002, "text": " We have a whole parade.", "tokens": [51318, 492, 362, 257, 1379, 26128, 13, 51361], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 341, "seek": 111388, "start": 1134.1000000000001, "end": 1134.64, "text": " We do.", "tokens": [51376, 492, 360, 13, 51403], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 342, "seek": 111388, "start": 1134.8400000000001, "end": 1138.3600000000001, "text": " How do the limbs talk to each other to coordinate a full body movement?", "tokens": [51413, 1012, 360, 264, 29315, 751, 281, 1184, 661, 281, 15670, 257, 1577, 1772, 3963, 30, 51589], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 343, "seek": 111388, "start": 1138.68, "end": 1142.18, "text": " This introduces Fliction's concept of hierarchical composition.", "tokens": [51605, 639, 31472, 3235, 4105, 311, 3410, 295, 35250, 804, 12686, 13, 51780], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12660319118176477, "compression_ratio": 1.591503267973856, "no_speech_prob": 1.81110909689558e-12}, {"id": 344, "seek": 114218, "start": 1142.18, "end": 1144.1200000000001, "text": " Biology isn't flat.", "tokens": [50365, 48132, 1943, 380, 4962, 13, 50462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 345, "seek": 114218, "start": 1144.28, "end": 1144.8600000000001, "text": " It's stacked.", "tokens": [50470, 467, 311, 28867, 13, 50499], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 346, "seek": 114218, "start": 1145.1200000000001, "end": 1145.44, "text": " Stacked.", "tokens": [50512, 745, 25949, 13, 50528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 347, "seek": 114218, "start": 1145.8, "end": 1149.96, "text": " A single joint, say, your ankle is driven by a local population of oscillators.", "tokens": [50546, 316, 2167, 7225, 11, 584, 11, 428, 21999, 307, 9555, 538, 257, 2654, 4415, 295, 18225, 3391, 13, 50754], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 348, "seek": 114218, "start": 1150.3200000000002, "end": 1154.28, "text": " Then your whole leg couples the ankle, knee, and hip populations together.", "tokens": [50772, 1396, 428, 1379, 1676, 20368, 264, 21999, 11, 9434, 11, 293, 8103, 12822, 1214, 13, 50970], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 349, "seek": 114218, "start": 1154.72, "end": 1158.2, "text": " Finally, a whole body gait couples the left leg and the right leg together.", "tokens": [50992, 6288, 11, 257, 1379, 1772, 290, 1001, 20368, 264, 1411, 1676, 293, 264, 558, 1676, 1214, 13, 51166], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 350, "seek": 114218, "start": 1158.28, "end": 1159.4, "text": " It's turtles all the way down.", "tokens": [51170, 467, 311, 32422, 439, 264, 636, 760, 13, 51226], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 351, "seek": 114218, "start": 1159.68, "end": 1160.04, "text": " Basically.", "tokens": [51240, 8537, 13, 51258], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 352, "seek": 114218, "start": 1160.46, "end": 1165.96, "text": " At each level of this hierarchy, the population below supplies its amplitwist, its coherence, and phase,", "tokens": [51279, 1711, 1184, 1496, 295, 341, 22333, 11, 264, 4415, 2507, 11768, 1080, 9731, 270, 86, 468, 11, 1080, 26528, 655, 11, 293, 5574, 11, 51554], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15366712109795932, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.8321834934637016e-12}, {"id": 353, "seek": 116596, "start": 1165.96, "end": 1169.3600000000001, "text": " and that becomes the raw input fed into the level above it.", "tokens": [50365, 293, 300, 3643, 264, 8936, 4846, 4636, 666, 264, 1496, 3673, 309, 13, 50535], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16644905805587767, "compression_ratio": 1.4793814432989691, "no_speech_prob": 1.506808458388853e-12}, {"id": 354, "seek": 116596, "start": 1169.58, "end": 1171.68, "text": " And Fliction calls this an amplitwist chain.", "tokens": [50546, 400, 3235, 4105, 5498, 341, 364, 9731, 270, 86, 468, 5021, 13, 50651], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16644905805587767, "compression_ratio": 1.4793814432989691, "no_speech_prob": 1.506808458388853e-12}, {"id": 355, "seek": 116596, "start": 1171.8, "end": 1172.1200000000001, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50657, 1079, 13, 50673], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16644905805587767, "compression_ratio": 1.4793814432989691, "no_speech_prob": 1.506808458388853e-12}, {"id": 356, "seek": 116596, "start": 1172.4, "end": 1179.9, "text": " To move up the chain from the joints to the whole body, the author introduces a mathematical rule called the gait-specifying coupling functional,", "tokens": [50687, 1407, 1286, 493, 264, 5021, 490, 264, 19949, 281, 264, 1379, 1772, 11, 264, 3793, 31472, 257, 18894, 4978, 1219, 264, 290, 1001, 12, 7053, 66, 5489, 37447, 11745, 11, 51062], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16644905805587767, "compression_ratio": 1.4793814432989691, "no_speech_prob": 1.506808458388853e-12}, {"id": 357, "seek": 116596, "start": 1180.4, "end": 1181.48, "text": " denoted as the letter C.", "tokens": [51087, 1441, 23325, 382, 264, 5063, 383, 13, 51141], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16644905805587767, "compression_ratio": 1.4793814432989691, "no_speech_prob": 1.506808458388853e-12}, {"id": 358, "seek": 116596, "start": 1181.64, "end": 1181.8600000000001, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51149, 1779, 13, 51160], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16644905805587767, "compression_ratio": 1.4793814432989691, "no_speech_prob": 1.506808458388853e-12}, {"id": 359, "seek": 118186, "start": 1181.86, "end": 1186.1399999999999, "text": " This is basically the formula that says, take the rhythms from the individual joints below,", "tokens": [50365, 639, 307, 1936, 264, 8513, 300, 1619, 11, 747, 264, 44892, 490, 264, 2609, 19949, 2507, 11, 50579], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13689138534221243, "compression_ratio": 1.582995951417004, "no_speech_prob": 2.176294951541924e-12}, {"id": 360, "seek": 118186, "start": 1186.74, "end": 1191.5, "text": " treat them as single units, and compute a new, higher-level marching band rhythm.", "tokens": [50609, 2387, 552, 382, 2167, 6815, 11, 293, 14722, 257, 777, 11, 2946, 12, 12418, 30523, 4116, 11801, 13, 50847], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13689138534221243, "compression_ratio": 1.582995951417004, "no_speech_prob": 2.176294951541924e-12}, {"id": 361, "seek": 118186, "start": 1191.76, "end": 1198.74, "text": " And tracing how many times you have to apply that functional C gives us a fascinating metric called the assembly index.", "tokens": [50860, 400, 25262, 577, 867, 1413, 291, 362, 281, 3079, 300, 11745, 383, 2709, 505, 257, 10343, 20678, 1219, 264, 12103, 8186, 13, 51209], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13689138534221243, "compression_ratio": 1.582995951417004, "no_speech_prob": 2.176294951541924e-12}, {"id": 362, "seek": 118186, "start": 1198.9599999999998, "end": 1200.54, "text": " Oh, denoted as A.", "tokens": [51220, 876, 11, 1441, 23325, 382, 316, 13, 51299], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13689138534221243, "compression_ratio": 1.582995951417004, "no_speech_prob": 2.176294951541924e-12}, {"id": 363, "seek": 118186, "start": 1200.6, "end": 1200.9799999999998, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51302, 1079, 13, 51321], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13689138534221243, "compression_ratio": 1.582995951417004, "no_speech_prob": 2.176294951541924e-12}, {"id": 364, "seek": 118186, "start": 1201.54, "end": 1205.4399999999998, "text": " The assembly index measures the anatomical depth of the control hierarchy.", "tokens": [51349, 440, 12103, 8186, 8000, 264, 21618, 298, 804, 7161, 295, 264, 1969, 22333, 13, 51544], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13689138534221243, "compression_ratio": 1.582995951417004, "no_speech_prob": 2.176294951541924e-12}, {"id": 365, "seek": 120544, "start": 1205.44, "end": 1209.96, "text": " It's a way to mathematically quantify the complexity of an organism's movement.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 257, 636, 281, 44003, 40421, 264, 14024, 295, 364, 24128, 311, 3963, 13, 50591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 366, "seek": 120544, "start": 1210.66, "end": 1217.38, "text": " So a simple bipedal robot where you just have two legs feeding directly into one main body would have an assembly index of one", "tokens": [50626, 407, 257, 2199, 19016, 292, 304, 7881, 689, 291, 445, 362, 732, 5668, 12919, 3838, 666, 472, 2135, 1772, 576, 362, 364, 12103, 8186, 295, 472, 50962], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 367, "seek": 120544, "start": 1217.38, "end": 1221.1200000000001, "text": " because you only apply the coupling rule once to join the two legs.", "tokens": [50962, 570, 291, 787, 3079, 264, 37447, 4978, 1564, 281, 3917, 264, 732, 5668, 13, 51149], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 368, "seek": 120544, "start": 1221.56, "end": 1221.8200000000002, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51171, 1079, 13, 51184], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 369, "seek": 120544, "start": 1222.22, "end": 1226.22, "text": " But a quadruped, like a dog or a horse, has more causal depth.", "tokens": [51204, 583, 257, 10787, 894, 3452, 11, 411, 257, 3000, 420, 257, 6832, 11, 575, 544, 38755, 7161, 13, 51404], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 370, "seek": 120544, "start": 1226.56, "end": 1229.8400000000001, "text": " The joints form a leg, and then the forelegs form a gait.", "tokens": [51421, 440, 19949, 1254, 257, 1676, 11, 293, 550, 264, 2091, 6363, 82, 1254, 257, 290, 1001, 13, 51585], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 371, "seek": 120544, "start": 1230.22, "end": 1232.6200000000001, "text": " That's an intermediate limb-level operator.", "tokens": [51604, 663, 311, 364, 19376, 30390, 12, 12418, 12973, 13, 51724], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 372, "seek": 120544, "start": 1232.72, "end": 1235.3, "text": " So a horse has an assembly index of two.", "tokens": [51729, 407, 257, 6832, 575, 364, 12103, 8186, 295, 732, 13, 51858], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13332340121269226, "compression_ratio": 1.6782006920415224, "no_speech_prob": 1.9970826208026704e-12}, {"id": 373, "seek": 123544, "start": 1235.54, "end": 1235.94, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50370, 7587, 13, 50390], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11721301275836535, "compression_ratio": 1.5638629283489096, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898043736166766e-12}, {"id": 374, "seek": 123544, "start": 1236.28, "end": 1242.68, "text": " And if you factor in a higher layer for postural corrections, like the vestibular system keeping the horse's head perfectly level", "tokens": [50407, 400, 498, 291, 5952, 294, 257, 2946, 4583, 337, 2183, 1807, 36406, 11, 411, 264, 15814, 897, 1040, 1185, 5145, 264, 6832, 311, 1378, 6239, 1496, 50727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11721301275836535, "compression_ratio": 1.5638629283489096, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898043736166766e-12}, {"id": 375, "seek": 123544, "start": 1242.68, "end": 1246.74, "text": " while it gallops over rough terrain, the index increases to three.", "tokens": [50727, 1339, 309, 8527, 3370, 670, 5903, 17674, 11, 264, 8186, 8637, 281, 1045, 13, 50930], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11721301275836535, "compression_ratio": 1.5638629283489096, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898043736166766e-12}, {"id": 376, "seek": 123544, "start": 1247.3, "end": 1252.06, "text": " I love this because it means the complexity of movement isn't just about counting how many muscles an animal has.", "tokens": [50958, 286, 959, 341, 570, 309, 1355, 264, 14024, 295, 3963, 1943, 380, 445, 466, 13251, 577, 867, 9530, 364, 5496, 575, 13, 51196], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11721301275836535, "compression_ratio": 1.5638629283489096, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898043736166766e-12}, {"id": 377, "seek": 123544, "start": 1252.0800000000002, "end": 1252.52, "text": " Got it all.", "tokens": [51197, 5803, 309, 439, 13, 51219], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11721301275836535, "compression_ratio": 1.5638629283489096, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898043736166766e-12}, {"id": 378, "seek": 123544, "start": 1252.52, "end": 1258.22, "text": " Like a millipede has hundreds of legs, but its assembly index might actually be quite low", "tokens": [51219, 1743, 257, 1728, 647, 4858, 575, 6779, 295, 5668, 11, 457, 1080, 12103, 8186, 1062, 767, 312, 1596, 2295, 51504], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11721301275836535, "compression_ratio": 1.5638629283489096, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898043736166766e-12}, {"id": 379, "seek": 123544, "start": 1258.22, "end": 1262.5, "text": " if all those legs are just daisy-chained into one simple repeating wave pattern.", "tokens": [51504, 498, 439, 729, 5668, 366, 445, 1120, 14169, 12, 339, 3563, 666, 472, 2199, 18617, 5772, 5102, 13, 51718], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11721301275836535, "compression_ratio": 1.5638629283489096, "no_speech_prob": 1.4898043736166766e-12}, {"id": 380, "seek": 126250, "start": 1262.5, "end": 1265.6, "text": " It measures the hierarchy of control, not the hardware.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 8000, 264, 22333, 295, 1969, 11, 406, 264, 8837, 13, 50520], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15311318752812406, "compression_ratio": 1.4834437086092715, "no_speech_prob": 2.096511332594364e-12}, {"id": 381, "seek": 126250, "start": 1265.9, "end": 1270.08, "text": " It is a brilliant way to compress biological complexity into a measurable index.", "tokens": [50535, 467, 307, 257, 10248, 636, 281, 14778, 13910, 14024, 666, 257, 43615, 8186, 13, 50744], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15311318752812406, "compression_ratio": 1.4834437086092715, "no_speech_prob": 2.096511332594364e-12}, {"id": 382, "seek": 126250, "start": 1270.44, "end": 1276.14, "text": " But the true power of this hierarchical chain relies on another variable, the matrix K.", "tokens": [50762, 583, 264, 2074, 1347, 295, 341, 35250, 804, 5021, 30910, 322, 1071, 7006, 11, 264, 8141, 591, 13, 51047], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15311318752812406, "compression_ratio": 1.4834437086092715, "no_speech_prob": 2.096511332594364e-12}, {"id": 383, "seek": 127614, "start": 1276.14, "end": 1277.48, "text": " The target phase offsets.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3779, 5574, 39457, 1385, 13, 50432], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18075454711914063, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 2.375995884415505e-12}, {"id": 384, "seek": 127614, "start": 1277.48, "end": 1281.0, "text": " This was the part of the paper that made me literally sit back in my chair.", "tokens": [50432, 639, 390, 264, 644, 295, 264, 3035, 300, 1027, 385, 3736, 1394, 646, 294, 452, 6090, 13, 50608], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18075454711914063, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 2.375995884415505e-12}, {"id": 385, "seek": 127614, "start": 1281.98, "end": 1283.8600000000001, "text": " Flickshund talks about law realism.", "tokens": [50657, 3235, 618, 2716, 997, 6686, 466, 2101, 38484, 13, 50751], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18075454711914063, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 2.375995884415505e-12}, {"id": 386, "seek": 127614, "start": 1284.8000000000002, "end": 1292.88, "text": " Now visually, a horse walking, a horse trotting, and a horse galloping look like three completely different physical mechanics.", "tokens": [50798, 823, 19622, 11, 257, 6832, 4494, 11, 257, 6832, 504, 310, 783, 11, 293, 257, 6832, 8527, 26125, 574, 411, 1045, 2584, 819, 4001, 12939, 13, 51202], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18075454711914063, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 2.375995884415505e-12}, {"id": 387, "seek": 127614, "start": 1292.94, "end": 1294.0400000000002, "text": " They look totally different.", "tokens": [51205, 814, 574, 3879, 819, 13, 51260], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18075454711914063, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 2.375995884415505e-12}, {"id": 388, "seek": 129404, "start": 1294.04, "end": 1298.56, "text": " It feels like the horse's brain would need three separate software programs to run them.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 3417, 411, 264, 6832, 311, 3567, 576, 643, 1045, 4994, 4722, 4268, 281, 1190, 552, 13, 50591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12477799887969115, "compression_ratio": 1.6370106761565837, "no_speech_prob": 1.9204030726749366e-12}, {"id": 389, "seek": 129404, "start": 1299.22, "end": 1306.58, "text": " But law realism argues that the fundamental mathematical law of coupling the master equation C running the nervous system", "tokens": [50624, 583, 2101, 38484, 38218, 300, 264, 8088, 18894, 2101, 295, 37447, 264, 4505, 5367, 383, 2614, 264, 6296, 1185, 50992], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12477799887969115, "compression_ratio": 1.6370106761565837, "no_speech_prob": 1.9204030726749366e-12}, {"id": 390, "seek": 129404, "start": 1306.58, "end": 1309.2, "text": " does not change at all when the horse changes gates.", "tokens": [50992, 775, 406, 1319, 412, 439, 562, 264, 6832, 2962, 19792, 13, 51123], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12477799887969115, "compression_ratio": 1.6370106761565837, "no_speech_prob": 1.9204030726749366e-12}, {"id": 391, "seek": 129404, "start": 1309.48, "end": 1311.3999999999999, "text": " The master equation is entirely fixed.", "tokens": [51137, 440, 4505, 5367, 307, 7696, 6806, 13, 51233], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12477799887969115, "compression_ratio": 1.6370106761565837, "no_speech_prob": 1.9204030726749366e-12}, {"id": 392, "seek": 129404, "start": 1311.62, "end": 1316.2, "text": " The only thing that changes are the target phase offsets fed into the matrix K.", "tokens": [51244, 440, 787, 551, 300, 2962, 366, 264, 3779, 5574, 39457, 1385, 4636, 666, 264, 8141, 591, 13, 51473], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12477799887969115, "compression_ratio": 1.6370106761565837, "no_speech_prob": 1.9204030726749366e-12}, {"id": 393, "seek": 129404, "start": 1316.5, "end": 1317.76, "text": " Okay, so what is K really?", "tokens": [51488, 1033, 11, 370, 437, 307, 591, 534, 30, 51551], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12477799887969115, "compression_ratio": 1.6370106761565837, "no_speech_prob": 1.9204030726749366e-12}, {"id": 394, "seek": 129404, "start": 1318.0, "end": 1322.0, "text": " Think of K as a volume knob with specific detents.", "tokens": [51563, 6557, 295, 591, 382, 257, 5523, 26759, 365, 2685, 1141, 791, 13, 51763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12477799887969115, "compression_ratio": 1.6370106761565837, "no_speech_prob": 1.9204030726749366e-12}, {"id": 395, "seek": 132200, "start": 1322.0, "end": 1328.84, "text": " In a trot, the diagonal legs, the front left and back right, are commanded to be perfectly in phase with each other.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 257, 504, 310, 11, 264, 21539, 5668, 11, 264, 1868, 1411, 293, 646, 558, 11, 366, 34359, 281, 312, 6239, 294, 5574, 365, 1184, 661, 13, 50707], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1055944855533429, "compression_ratio": 1.7728937728937728, "no_speech_prob": 2.0927051324476365e-12}, {"id": 396, "seek": 132200, "start": 1329.04, "end": 1329.18, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50717, 1779, 13, 50724], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1055944855533429, "compression_ratio": 1.7728937728937728, "no_speech_prob": 2.0927051324476365e-12}, {"id": 397, "seek": 132200, "start": 1329.6, "end": 1333.82, "text": " In a pacing gate, the lateral legs, the left front and left back, are in phase.", "tokens": [50745, 682, 257, 43285, 8539, 11, 264, 25128, 5668, 11, 264, 1411, 1868, 293, 1411, 646, 11, 366, 294, 5574, 13, 50956], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1055944855533429, "compression_ratio": 1.7728937728937728, "no_speech_prob": 2.0927051324476365e-12}, {"id": 398, "seek": 132200, "start": 1334.1, "end": 1339.22, "text": " In a galloping bound, the two front legs act together and the two back legs act together.", "tokens": [50970, 682, 257, 8527, 26125, 5472, 11, 264, 732, 1868, 5668, 605, 1214, 293, 264, 732, 646, 5668, 605, 1214, 13, 51226], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1055944855533429, "compression_ratio": 1.7728937728937728, "no_speech_prob": 2.0927051324476365e-12}, {"id": 399, "seek": 132200, "start": 1339.36, "end": 1346.08, "text": " So wait, if a horse transitions from a trot to a gallop, its brain isn't loading up an entirely new gallop.exe file.", "tokens": [51233, 407, 1699, 11, 498, 257, 6832, 23767, 490, 257, 504, 310, 281, 257, 8527, 404, 11, 1080, 3567, 1943, 380, 15114, 493, 364, 7696, 777, 8527, 404, 13, 3121, 68, 3991, 13, 51569], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1055944855533429, "compression_ratio": 1.7728937728937728, "no_speech_prob": 2.0927051324476365e-12}, {"id": 400, "seek": 132200, "start": 1346.3, "end": 1346.8, "text": " Not at all.", "tokens": [51580, 1726, 412, 439, 13, 51605], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1055944855533429, "compression_ratio": 1.7728937728937728, "no_speech_prob": 2.0927051324476365e-12}, {"id": 401, "seek": 132200, "start": 1346.92, "end": 1350.14, "text": " It's just tweaking a single parameter in the master equation.", "tokens": [51611, 467, 311, 445, 6986, 2456, 257, 2167, 13075, 294, 264, 4505, 5367, 13, 51772], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1055944855533429, "compression_ratio": 1.7728937728937728, "no_speech_prob": 2.0927051324476365e-12}, {"id": 402, "seek": 135014, "start": 1350.14, "end": 1353.0200000000002, "text": " Exactly. It is the ultimate biological economy.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 467, 307, 264, 9705, 13910, 5010, 13, 50509], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12519961840485874, "compression_ratio": 1.5049019607843137, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892603209665234e-12}, {"id": 403, "seek": 135014, "start": 1353.2, "end": 1356.74, "text": " You don't need a separate mathematical law for every conceivable gate.", "tokens": [50518, 509, 500, 380, 643, 257, 4994, 18894, 2101, 337, 633, 10413, 34376, 8539, 13, 50695], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12519961840485874, "compression_ratio": 1.5049019607843137, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892603209665234e-12}, {"id": 404, "seek": 135014, "start": 1356.9, "end": 1357.5800000000002, "text": " That's wild.", "tokens": [50703, 663, 311, 4868, 13, 50737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12519961840485874, "compression_ratio": 1.5049019607843137, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892603209665234e-12}, {"id": 405, "seek": 135014, "start": 1357.8000000000002, "end": 1367.2, "text": " A walk and a trot are just two different stable fixed points of the exact same coupled oscillator system under two different phase offset targets.", "tokens": [50748, 316, 1792, 293, 257, 504, 310, 366, 445, 732, 819, 8351, 6806, 2793, 295, 264, 1900, 912, 29482, 43859, 1185, 833, 732, 819, 5574, 18687, 12911, 13, 51218], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12519961840485874, "compression_ratio": 1.5049019607843137, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892603209665234e-12}, {"id": 406, "seek": 135014, "start": 1367.3000000000002, "end": 1368.5, "text": " So the equation is the same.", "tokens": [51223, 407, 264, 5367, 307, 264, 912, 13, 51283], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12519961840485874, "compression_ratio": 1.5049019607843137, "no_speech_prob": 1.4892603209665234e-12}, {"id": 407, "seek": 136850, "start": 1368.5, "end": 1372.36, "text": " The coupling functional C is real and it persists.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 37447, 11745, 383, 307, 957, 293, 309, 868, 1751, 13, 50558], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13414510365190177, "compression_ratio": 1.4175824175824177, "no_speech_prob": 1.6548971394636514e-12}, {"id": 408, "seek": 136850, "start": 1372.8, "end": 1376.02, "text": " Only the specific instantiation of the offsets changes.", "tokens": [50580, 5686, 264, 2685, 9836, 6642, 295, 264, 39457, 1385, 2962, 13, 50741], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13414510365190177, "compression_ratio": 1.4175824175824177, "no_speech_prob": 1.6548971394636514e-12}, {"id": 409, "seek": 136850, "start": 1376.86, "end": 1386.04, "text": " I mean, why would evolution painfully design 10 different neural circuits for 10 gates when it could evolve one robust circuit with an adjustable dial?", "tokens": [50783, 286, 914, 11, 983, 576, 9303, 1822, 2277, 1715, 1266, 819, 18161, 26354, 337, 1266, 19792, 562, 309, 727, 16693, 472, 13956, 9048, 365, 364, 27804, 5502, 30, 51242], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13414510365190177, "compression_ratio": 1.4175824175824177, "no_speech_prob": 1.6548971394636514e-12}, {"id": 410, "seek": 138604, "start": 1386.04, "end": 1392.82, "text": " It's breathtakingly simple. But this stacked continuous equation doesn't just simplify how we understand gates.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 48393, 356, 2199, 13, 583, 341, 28867, 10957, 5367, 1177, 380, 445, 20460, 577, 321, 1223, 19792, 13, 50704], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15444051569158382, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.6678748226278683e-12}, {"id": 411, "seek": 138604, "start": 1393.1399999999999, "end": 1393.26, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50720, 865, 13, 50726], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15444051569158382, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.6678748226278683e-12}, {"id": 412, "seek": 138604, "start": 1393.36, "end": 1399.48, "text": " If movement is just a continuously running equation, it completely shatters how we conventionally define balance.", "tokens": [50731, 759, 3963, 307, 445, 257, 15684, 2614, 5367, 11, 309, 2584, 402, 37690, 577, 321, 10286, 379, 6964, 4772, 13, 51037], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15444051569158382, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.6678748226278683e-12}, {"id": 413, "seek": 138604, "start": 1399.6, "end": 1400.22, "text": " It does.", "tokens": [51043, 467, 775, 13, 51074], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15444051569158382, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.6678748226278683e-12}, {"id": 414, "seek": 138604, "start": 1400.54, "end": 1403.1599999999999, "text": " The paper has a whole section titled The Myth of Achieving Balance.", "tokens": [51090, 440, 3035, 575, 257, 1379, 3541, 19841, 440, 26371, 295, 15847, 30244, 41899, 13, 51221], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15444051569158382, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.6678748226278683e-12}, {"id": 415, "seek": 138604, "start": 1403.68, "end": 1408.24, "text": " Because if you accept the amplitwist chain, then balance is not a state achieved once and held.", "tokens": [51247, 1436, 498, 291, 3241, 264, 9731, 270, 86, 468, 5021, 11, 550, 4772, 307, 406, 257, 1785, 11042, 1564, 293, 5167, 13, 51475], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15444051569158382, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.6678748226278683e-12}, {"id": 416, "seek": 138604, "start": 1408.6599999999999, "end": 1411.68, "text": " There is no stored quantity of balance that a robot achieves.", "tokens": [51496, 821, 307, 572, 12187, 11275, 295, 4772, 300, 257, 7881, 3538, 977, 13, 51647], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15444051569158382, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.6678748226278683e-12}, {"id": 417, "seek": 141168, "start": 1411.68, "end": 1415.04, "text": " It goes back to our discussion of stop motion versus the fluid brush stroke.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1709, 646, 281, 527, 5017, 295, 1590, 5394, 5717, 264, 9113, 5287, 12403, 13, 50533], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 418, "seek": 141168, "start": 1415.3200000000002, "end": 1419.6200000000001, "text": " Flixing defines balance as continuously regenerated coherence.", "tokens": [50547, 3235, 970, 278, 23122, 4772, 382, 15684, 26358, 770, 26528, 655, 13, 50762], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 419, "seek": 141168, "start": 1419.88, "end": 1420.02, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50775, 865, 13, 50782], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 420, "seek": 141168, "start": 1420.54, "end": 1423.3600000000001, "text": " Remember the amplitude R from our marching band?", "tokens": [50808, 5459, 264, 27433, 497, 490, 527, 30523, 4116, 30, 50949], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 421, "seek": 141168, "start": 1423.44, "end": 1423.6000000000001, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50953, 865, 13, 50961], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 422, "seek": 141168, "start": 1423.8, "end": 1426.0800000000002, "text": " It measures how synchronized the system is.", "tokens": [50971, 467, 8000, 577, 19331, 1602, 264, 1185, 307, 13, 51085], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 423, "seek": 141168, "start": 1426.16, "end": 1426.54, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51089, 1079, 13, 51108], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 424, "seek": 141168, "start": 1426.64, "end": 1435.64, "text": " At the highest level of the chain, the whole body level, as long as that R value is kept above a certain minimum mathematical threshold, the system is balanced.", "tokens": [51113, 1711, 264, 6343, 1496, 295, 264, 5021, 11, 264, 1379, 1772, 1496, 11, 382, 938, 382, 300, 497, 2158, 307, 4305, 3673, 257, 1629, 7285, 18894, 14678, 11, 264, 1185, 307, 13902, 13, 51563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15435359992232978, "compression_ratio": 1.55893536121673, "no_speech_prob": 2.0845660267387878e-12}, {"id": 425, "seek": 143564, "start": 1435.64, "end": 1446.48, "text": " The phase relationships of all the tiny joints and limbs at the lower levels are continuously spinning, recomputing, and feeding their rhythms into that top level R at every single millisecond.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 5574, 6159, 295, 439, 264, 5870, 19949, 293, 29315, 412, 264, 3126, 4358, 366, 15684, 15640, 11, 23334, 2582, 278, 11, 293, 12919, 641, 44892, 666, 300, 1192, 1496, 497, 412, 633, 2167, 27940, 18882, 13, 50907], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.05983829122828686, "compression_ratio": 1.6847133757961783, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011363021360304e-12}, {"id": 426, "seek": 143564, "start": 1446.6200000000001, "end": 1451.3600000000001, "text": " So what does this all mean? When I read continuously regenerated coherence, I thought of juggling.", "tokens": [50914, 407, 437, 775, 341, 439, 914, 30, 1133, 286, 1401, 15684, 26358, 770, 26528, 655, 11, 286, 1194, 295, 361, 29921, 13, 51151], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.05983829122828686, "compression_ratio": 1.6847133757961783, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011363021360304e-12}, {"id": 427, "seek": 143564, "start": 1451.5800000000002, "end": 1451.8400000000001, "text": " Juggling.", "tokens": [51162, 508, 29921, 13, 51175], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.05983829122828686, "compression_ratio": 1.6847133757961783, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011363021360304e-12}, {"id": 428, "seek": 143564, "start": 1452.1000000000001, "end": 1459.22, "text": " Yeah. You don't achieve a juggled state. Put your hands in your pockets and just freeze. If you freeze, the balls drop and the system collapses.", "tokens": [51188, 865, 13, 509, 500, 380, 4584, 257, 361, 3562, 1493, 1785, 13, 4935, 428, 2377, 294, 428, 16491, 293, 445, 15959, 13, 759, 291, 15959, 11, 264, 9803, 3270, 293, 264, 1185, 48765, 13, 51544], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.05983829122828686, "compression_ratio": 1.6847133757961783, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011363021360304e-12}, {"id": 429, "seek": 143564, "start": 1459.3600000000001, "end": 1460.1000000000001, "text": " Oh, I see.", "tokens": [51551, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 51588], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.05983829122828686, "compression_ratio": 1.6847133757961783, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011363021360304e-12}, {"id": 430, "seek": 143564, "start": 1460.16, "end": 1463.6000000000001, "text": " The balance is the ongoing continuous action of throwing and catching.", "tokens": [51591, 440, 4772, 307, 264, 10452, 10957, 3069, 295, 10238, 293, 16124, 13, 51763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.05983829122828686, "compression_ratio": 1.6847133757961783, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011363021360304e-12}, {"id": 431, "seek": 146360, "start": 1463.6, "end": 1470.06, "text": " That is a much more accurate visualization than a static pose. The balance is constituted by the ongoing coupling.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 257, 709, 544, 8559, 25801, 813, 257, 13437, 10774, 13, 440, 4772, 307, 23079, 4866, 538, 264, 10452, 37447, 13, 50688], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08861948462093577, "compression_ratio": 1.6463878326996197, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011370610775511e-12}, {"id": 432, "seek": 146360, "start": 1470.2199999999998, "end": 1470.4199999999998, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50696, 1779, 13, 50706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08861948462093577, "compression_ratio": 1.6463878326996197, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011370610775511e-12}, {"id": 433, "seek": 146360, "start": 1470.6399999999999, "end": 1480.02, "text": " The threshold of R isn't a physical posture you aim at. It's simply a mathematical boundary below which the internal coherence stops counting as stable walking.", "tokens": [50717, 440, 14678, 295, 497, 1943, 380, 257, 4001, 18502, 291, 5939, 412, 13, 467, 311, 2935, 257, 18894, 12866, 2507, 597, 264, 6920, 26528, 655, 10094, 13251, 382, 8351, 4494, 13, 51186], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08861948462093577, "compression_ratio": 1.6463878326996197, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011370610775511e-12}, {"id": 434, "seek": 146360, "start": 1480.3999999999999, "end": 1488.8799999999999, "text": " But there is a massive technical hurdle here for bipedal walking, human walking. The paper calls it the antiphase problem.", "tokens": [51205, 583, 456, 307, 257, 5994, 6191, 47423, 510, 337, 19016, 292, 304, 4494, 11, 1952, 4494, 13, 440, 3035, 5498, 309, 264, 2511, 24595, 651, 1154, 13, 51629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08861948462093577, "compression_ratio": 1.6463878326996197, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011370610775511e-12}, {"id": 435, "seek": 146360, "start": 1489.02, "end": 1490.74, "text": " Yes, the antiphase problem.", "tokens": [51636, 1079, 11, 264, 2511, 24595, 651, 1154, 13, 51722], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08861948462093577, "compression_ratio": 1.6463878326996197, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011370610775511e-12}, {"id": 436, "seek": 149074, "start": 1490.74, "end": 1501.86, "text": " If human walking is just a two-level chain, two legs combining into one gate, and the legs are doing the exact opposite things, doesn't the math accidentally destroy itself?", "tokens": [50365, 759, 1952, 4494, 307, 445, 257, 732, 12, 12418, 5021, 11, 732, 5668, 21928, 666, 472, 8539, 11, 293, 264, 5668, 366, 884, 264, 1900, 6182, 721, 11, 1177, 380, 264, 5221, 15715, 5293, 2564, 30, 50921], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09501384496688843, "compression_ratio": 1.511111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.661728046831179e-12}, {"id": 437, "seek": 149074, "start": 1502.1, "end": 1514.34, "text": " This highlights the rigor of Fluxian's geometry. In normal, healthy human walking, your left leg and right leg are out of phase by exactly pi radians, or 180 degrees.", "tokens": [50933, 639, 14254, 264, 42191, 295, 3235, 2449, 952, 311, 18426, 13, 682, 2710, 11, 4627, 1952, 4494, 11, 428, 1411, 1676, 293, 558, 1676, 366, 484, 295, 5574, 538, 2293, 3895, 2843, 2567, 11, 420, 11971, 5310, 13, 51545], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09501384496688843, "compression_ratio": 1.511111111111111, "no_speech_prob": 1.661728046831179e-12}, {"id": 438, "seek": 151434, "start": 1514.34, "end": 1523.0, "text": " When your right foot is planted behind you pushing off, your left foot is swinging forward in the air. They are doing the exact opposite motions.", "tokens": [50365, 1133, 428, 558, 2671, 307, 17395, 2261, 291, 7380, 766, 11, 428, 1411, 2671, 307, 29500, 2128, 294, 264, 1988, 13, 814, 366, 884, 264, 1900, 6182, 27500, 13, 50798], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12696624096528983, "compression_ratio": 1.592760180995475, "no_speech_prob": 1.774946834474933e-12}, {"id": 439, "seek": 151434, "start": 1523.1799999999998, "end": 1523.86, "text": " So if you add them?", "tokens": [50807, 407, 498, 291, 909, 552, 30, 50841], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12696624096528983, "compression_ratio": 1.592760180995475, "no_speech_prob": 1.774946834474933e-12}, {"id": 440, "seek": 151434, "start": 1524.02, "end": 1530.74, "text": " If you naively add those two opposite mathematical phases together in the Kuramoto model, they completely cancel each other out.", "tokens": [50849, 759, 291, 1667, 3413, 909, 729, 732, 6182, 18894, 18764, 1214, 294, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 11, 436, 2584, 10373, 1184, 661, 484, 13, 51185], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12696624096528983, "compression_ratio": 1.592760180995475, "no_speech_prob": 1.774946834474933e-12}, {"id": 441, "seek": 151434, "start": 1531.08, "end": 1534.5, "text": " The equation would output a coherence R of absolute zero.", "tokens": [51202, 440, 5367, 576, 5598, 257, 26528, 655, 497, 295, 8236, 4018, 13, 51373], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12696624096528983, "compression_ratio": 1.592760180995475, "no_speech_prob": 1.774946834474933e-12}, {"id": 442, "seek": 153450, "start": 1534.5, "end": 1542.24, "text": " Which mathematically would mean the system is in total chaos and collapsing, even though physically you are executing a perfectly balanced, healthy walk.", "tokens": [50365, 3013, 44003, 576, 914, 264, 1185, 307, 294, 3217, 14158, 293, 45339, 11, 754, 1673, 9762, 291, 366, 32368, 257, 6239, 13902, 11, 4627, 1792, 13, 50752], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09838242397130093, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.460451985041411e-12}, {"id": 443, "seek": 153450, "start": 1542.3, "end": 1548.24, "text": " Exactly the problem. So Fluxian introduces the necessary correction, the offset corrected order parameter.", "tokens": [50755, 7587, 264, 1154, 13, 407, 3235, 2449, 952, 31472, 264, 4818, 19984, 11, 264, 18687, 31687, 1668, 13075, 13, 51052], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09838242397130093, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.460451985041411e-12}, {"id": 444, "seek": 153450, "start": 1548.28, "end": 1549.12, "text": " Okay, what does that do?", "tokens": [51054, 1033, 11, 437, 775, 300, 360, 30, 51096], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09838242397130093, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.460451985041411e-12}, {"id": 445, "seek": 153450, "start": 1549.4, "end": 1555.66, "text": " When computing the overall coherence of the walking gate, the system doesn't ask, are the legs doing the same thing?", "tokens": [51110, 1133, 15866, 264, 4787, 26528, 655, 295, 264, 4494, 8539, 11, 264, 1185, 1177, 380, 1029, 11, 366, 264, 5668, 884, 264, 912, 551, 30, 51423], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09838242397130093, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.460451985041411e-12}, {"id": 446, "seek": 153450, "start": 1555.72, "end": 1558.16, "text": " It asks, are the legs hitting their assigned offset?", "tokens": [51426, 467, 8962, 11, 366, 264, 5668, 8850, 641, 13279, 18687, 30, 51548], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09838242397130093, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.460451985041411e-12}, {"id": 447, "seek": 153450, "start": 1558.54, "end": 1559.16, "text": " Oh, I see.", "tokens": [51567, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 51598], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09838242397130093, "compression_ratio": 1.6762589928057554, "no_speech_prob": 1.460451985041411e-12}, {"id": 448, "seek": 155916, "start": 1559.16, "end": 1563.92, "text": " You mathematically rotate one leg's phase by 180 degrees before adding them up.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 44003, 13121, 472, 1676, 311, 5574, 538, 11971, 5310, 949, 5127, 552, 493, 13, 50603], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13652908161122312, "compression_ratio": 1.547244094488189, "no_speech_prob": 2.4370555486846746e-12}, {"id": 449, "seek": 155916, "start": 1564.16, "end": 1566.72, "text": " I thought about this like a two-cylinder engine and a motorcycle.", "tokens": [50615, 286, 1194, 466, 341, 411, 257, 732, 12, 1344, 75, 5669, 2848, 293, 257, 20554, 13, 50743], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13652908161122312, "compression_ratio": 1.547244094488189, "no_speech_prob": 2.4370555486846746e-12}, {"id": 450, "seek": 155916, "start": 1567.28, "end": 1577.24, "text": " If both pistons fired at the exact same time perfectly in phase, the physical force would cancel out and probably shatter the engine block.", "tokens": [50771, 759, 1293, 12273, 892, 11777, 412, 264, 1900, 912, 565, 6239, 294, 5574, 11, 264, 4001, 3464, 576, 10373, 484, 293, 1391, 402, 1161, 264, 2848, 3461, 13, 51269], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13652908161122312, "compression_ratio": 1.547244094488189, "no_speech_prob": 2.4370555486846746e-12}, {"id": 451, "seek": 155916, "start": 1577.3600000000001, "end": 1578.44, "text": " It would be a disaster.", "tokens": [51275, 467, 576, 312, 257, 11293, 13, 51329], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13652908161122312, "compression_ratio": 1.547244094488189, "no_speech_prob": 2.4370555486846746e-12}, {"id": 452, "seek": 155916, "start": 1578.72, "end": 1583.16, "text": " Right. They have to fire exactly out of phase to generate continuous forward power.", "tokens": [51343, 1779, 13, 814, 362, 281, 2610, 2293, 484, 295, 5574, 281, 8460, 10957, 2128, 1347, 13, 51565], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13652908161122312, "compression_ratio": 1.547244094488189, "no_speech_prob": 2.4370555486846746e-12}, {"id": 453, "seek": 158316, "start": 1583.16, "end": 1591.1200000000001, "text": " The offset corrected parameter basically checks if the pistons are firing at their perfectly opposite assigned times.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 18687, 31687, 13075, 1936, 13834, 498, 264, 12273, 892, 366, 16045, 412, 641, 6239, 6182, 13279, 1413, 13, 50763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16022374678631218, "compression_ratio": 1.6076923076923078, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179266685763862e-12}, {"id": 454, "seek": 158316, "start": 1591.28, "end": 1592.1000000000001, "text": " That's a great analogy.", "tokens": [50771, 663, 311, 257, 869, 21663, 13, 50812], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16022374678631218, "compression_ratio": 1.6076923076923078, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179266685763862e-12}, {"id": 455, "seek": 158316, "start": 1592.3600000000001, "end": 1597.42, "text": " If they are, the coherence shoots back up to one, correctly identifying a state of perfect balance.", "tokens": [50825, 759, 436, 366, 11, 264, 26528, 655, 20704, 646, 493, 281, 472, 11, 8944, 16696, 257, 1785, 295, 2176, 4772, 13, 51078], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16022374678631218, "compression_ratio": 1.6076923076923078, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179266685763862e-12}, {"id": 456, "seek": 158316, "start": 1597.72, "end": 1601.46, "text": " It's a mechanism that ensures the mathematics accurately reflects the physics.", "tokens": [51093, 467, 311, 257, 7513, 300, 28111, 264, 18666, 20095, 18926, 264, 10649, 13, 51280], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16022374678631218, "compression_ratio": 1.6076923076923078, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179266685763862e-12}, {"id": 457, "seek": 158316, "start": 1602.02, "end": 1607.22, "text": " And it leads Fluxian to touch on a broader philosophical concept called autopoiesis.", "tokens": [51308, 400, 309, 6689, 3235, 2449, 952, 281, 2557, 322, 257, 13227, 25066, 3410, 1219, 31090, 78, 530, 271, 13, 51568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16022374678631218, "compression_ratio": 1.6076923076923078, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179266685763862e-12}, {"id": 458, "seek": 158316, "start": 1607.64, "end": 1608.3200000000002, "text": " Autopoiesis.", "tokens": [51589, 6049, 404, 78, 530, 271, 13, 51623], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16022374678631218, "compression_ratio": 1.6076923076923078, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179266685763862e-12}, {"id": 459, "seek": 160832, "start": 1608.32, "end": 1614.8799999999999, "text": " Yes. Autopoietic systems are systems that maintain themselves by continuously regenerating the components of their own operation.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 6049, 404, 78, 1684, 299, 3652, 366, 3652, 300, 6909, 2969, 538, 15684, 26358, 990, 264, 6677, 295, 641, 1065, 6916, 13, 50693], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08802085337431534, "compression_ratio": 1.7215189873417722, "no_speech_prob": 1.927919195815475e-12}, {"id": 460, "seek": 160832, "start": 1615.58, "end": 1617.48, "text": " Biological cells are autopoietic.", "tokens": [50728, 13007, 4383, 5438, 366, 31090, 78, 1684, 299, 13, 50823], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08802085337431534, "compression_ratio": 1.7215189873417722, "no_speech_prob": 1.927919195815475e-12}, {"id": 461, "seek": 160832, "start": 1617.72, "end": 1624.3, "text": " Now, Fluxian is very careful to state that a walking robot running this math isn't alive in the biological sense.", "tokens": [50835, 823, 11, 3235, 2449, 952, 307, 588, 5026, 281, 1785, 300, 257, 4494, 7881, 2614, 341, 5221, 1943, 380, 5465, 294, 264, 13910, 2020, 13, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08802085337431534, "compression_ratio": 1.7215189873417722, "no_speech_prob": 1.927919195815475e-12}, {"id": 462, "seek": 160832, "start": 1624.9399999999998, "end": 1626.98, "text": " But the structural pattern is identical.", "tokens": [51196, 583, 264, 15067, 5102, 307, 14800, 13, 51298], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08802085337431534, "compression_ratio": 1.7215189873417722, "no_speech_prob": 1.927919195815475e-12}, {"id": 463, "seek": 160832, "start": 1627.56, "end": 1632.6799999999998, "text": " The operation of the system produces the conditions for the system to continue operating.", "tokens": [51327, 440, 6916, 295, 264, 1185, 14725, 264, 4487, 337, 264, 1185, 281, 2354, 7447, 13, 51583], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08802085337431534, "compression_ratio": 1.7215189873417722, "no_speech_prob": 1.927919195815475e-12}, {"id": 464, "seek": 163268, "start": 1632.68, "end": 1637.3, "text": " This is why Fluxian is so pedantic about using the word histories instead of trajectories, right?", "tokens": [50365, 639, 307, 983, 3235, 2449, 952, 307, 370, 5670, 7128, 466, 1228, 264, 1349, 30631, 2602, 295, 18257, 2083, 11, 558, 30, 50596], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09933618198741566, "compression_ratio": 1.6729323308270676, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130317788589198e-12}, {"id": 465, "seek": 163268, "start": 1637.76, "end": 1639.8400000000001, "text": " Because a trajectory is just a path over time.", "tokens": [50619, 1436, 257, 21512, 307, 445, 257, 3100, 670, 565, 13, 50723], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09933618198741566, "compression_ratio": 1.6729323308270676, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130317788589198e-12}, {"id": 466, "seek": 163268, "start": 1640.3200000000002, "end": 1645.04, "text": " You can plot the trajectory of a thrown baseball, but the baseball isn't generating its own flight.", "tokens": [50747, 509, 393, 7542, 264, 21512, 295, 257, 11732, 14323, 11, 457, 264, 14323, 1943, 380, 17746, 1080, 1065, 7018, 13, 50983], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09933618198741566, "compression_ratio": 1.6729323308270676, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130317788589198e-12}, {"id": 467, "seek": 163268, "start": 1645.16, "end": 1645.78, "text": " Yeah, or it's passive.", "tokens": [50989, 865, 11, 420, 309, 311, 14975, 13, 51020], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09933618198741566, "compression_ratio": 1.6729323308270676, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130317788589198e-12}, {"id": 468, "seek": 163268, "start": 1646.2, "end": 1655.48, "text": " But a history in this framework is a path where the future depends intrinsically on the ongoing self-regenerating coupling of the past.", "tokens": [51041, 583, 257, 2503, 294, 341, 8388, 307, 257, 3100, 689, 264, 2027, 5946, 28621, 984, 322, 264, 10452, 2698, 12, 265, 21848, 990, 37447, 295, 264, 1791, 13, 51505], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09933618198741566, "compression_ratio": 1.6729323308270676, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130317788589198e-12}, {"id": 469, "seek": 163268, "start": 1655.96, "end": 1658.16, "text": " The history is writing itself as it goes.", "tokens": [51529, 440, 2503, 307, 3579, 2564, 382, 309, 1709, 13, 51639], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09933618198741566, "compression_ratio": 1.6729323308270676, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130317788589198e-12}, {"id": 470, "seek": 165816, "start": 1658.16, "end": 1662.8600000000001, "text": " The trajectory is just the physical artifact left behind by this self-regenerating history.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 21512, 307, 445, 264, 4001, 34806, 1411, 2261, 538, 341, 2698, 12, 265, 21848, 990, 2503, 13, 50600], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 471, "seek": 165816, "start": 1663.1200000000001, "end": 1665.5400000000002, "text": " Okay, we have built this beautiful, elegant theory.", "tokens": [50613, 1033, 11, 321, 362, 3094, 341, 2238, 11, 21117, 5261, 13, 50734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 472, "seek": 165816, "start": 1666.0400000000002, "end": 1670.42, "text": " It connects the biological ghosts in the spine to the complex geometry of scaling and twisting,", "tokens": [50759, 467, 16967, 264, 13910, 21744, 294, 264, 15395, 281, 264, 3997, 18426, 295, 21589, 293, 34491, 11, 50978], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 473, "seek": 165816, "start": 1670.78, "end": 1674.16, "text": " and it simplifies complex gates down to a single dial.", "tokens": [50996, 293, 309, 6883, 11221, 3997, 19792, 760, 281, 257, 2167, 5502, 13, 51165], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 474, "seek": 165816, "start": 1674.3600000000001, "end": 1674.8600000000001, "text": " We have.", "tokens": [51175, 492, 362, 13, 51200], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 475, "seek": 165816, "start": 1675.0600000000002, "end": 1676.26, "text": " But elegance isn't science.", "tokens": [51210, 583, 14459, 719, 1943, 380, 3497, 13, 51270], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 476, "seek": 165816, "start": 1676.8600000000001, "end": 1678.28, "text": " A theory has to be testable.", "tokens": [51300, 316, 5261, 575, 281, 312, 1500, 712, 13, 51371], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 477, "seek": 165816, "start": 1678.8200000000002, "end": 1681.6000000000001, "text": " And this is where my respect for this monograph went through the roof.", "tokens": [51398, 400, 341, 307, 689, 452, 3104, 337, 341, 1108, 3108, 1437, 807, 264, 8418, 13, 51537], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 478, "seek": 165816, "start": 1681.76, "end": 1683.3400000000001, "text": " Because of the falsification section.", "tokens": [51545, 1436, 295, 264, 16720, 3774, 3541, 13, 51624], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 479, "seek": 165816, "start": 1683.72, "end": 1684.0600000000002, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51643, 1079, 13, 51660], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15800927896968653, "compression_ratio": 1.6232876712328768, "no_speech_prob": 1.4103025388137458e-12}, {"id": 480, "seek": 168406, "start": 1684.06, "end": 1686.56, "text": " Flexion doesn't just propose a theory.", "tokens": [50365, 29208, 313, 1177, 380, 445, 17421, 257, 5261, 13, 50490], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 481, "seek": 168406, "start": 1687.0, "end": 1689.34, "text": " They dedicate an entire section to falsification.", "tokens": [50512, 814, 30718, 364, 2302, 3541, 281, 16720, 3774, 13, 50629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 482, "seek": 168406, "start": 1689.84, "end": 1692.6599999999999, "text": " They lay out exactly how to prove the theory wrong.", "tokens": [50654, 814, 2360, 484, 2293, 577, 281, 7081, 264, 5261, 2085, 13, 50795], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 483, "seek": 168406, "start": 1693.54, "end": 1696.06, "text": " Flexion sets out three explicit failure modes.", "tokens": [50839, 29208, 313, 6352, 484, 1045, 13691, 7763, 14068, 13, 50965], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 484, "seek": 168406, "start": 1696.94, "end": 1699.6599999999999, "text": " If the framework fails any of these three tests,", "tokens": [51009, 759, 264, 8388, 18199, 604, 295, 613, 1045, 6921, 11, 51145], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 485, "seek": 168406, "start": 1700.1, "end": 1704.08, "text": " the author boldly states the geometric interpretation should be entirely abandoned.", "tokens": [51167, 264, 3793, 11928, 356, 4368, 264, 33246, 14174, 820, 312, 7696, 13732, 13, 51366], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 486, "seek": 168406, "start": 1704.58, "end": 1704.96, "text": " Love that.", "tokens": [51391, 5956, 300, 13, 51410], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 487, "seek": 168406, "start": 1705.04, "end": 1707.58, "text": " So the first test is the compactness criterion.", "tokens": [51414, 407, 264, 700, 1500, 307, 264, 14679, 1287, 46691, 13, 51541], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 488, "seek": 168406, "start": 1708.1399999999999, "end": 1708.46, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51569, 1779, 13, 51585], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23765923579533896, "compression_ratio": 1.6218487394957983, "no_speech_prob": 1.0814906912723354e-12}, {"id": 489, "seek": 170846, "start": 1708.46, "end": 1712.88, "text": " Because the whole point of this operator-generated history is that it's supposed to be computationally", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 264, 1379, 935, 295, 341, 12973, 12, 21848, 770, 2503, 307, 300, 309, 311, 3442, 281, 312, 24903, 379, 50586], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1542666480654762, "compression_ratio": 1.596026490066225, "no_speech_prob": 1.6035417351595305e-12}, {"id": 490, "seek": 170846, "start": 1712.88, "end": 1719.06, "text": " cheaper and more efficient than calculating millions of individual joint angles with inverse kinematics.", "tokens": [50586, 12284, 293, 544, 7148, 813, 28258, 6803, 295, 2609, 7225, 14708, 365, 17340, 15784, 37541, 13, 50895], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1542666480654762, "compression_ratio": 1.596026490066225, "no_speech_prob": 1.6035417351595305e-12}, {"id": 491, "seek": 170846, "start": 1719.06, "end": 1723.82, "text": " If describing a walk using this Amplit-Wist math requires more parameters,", "tokens": [50895, 759, 16141, 257, 1792, 1228, 341, 2012, 564, 270, 12, 54, 468, 5221, 7029, 544, 9834, 11, 51133], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1542666480654762, "compression_ratio": 1.596026490066225, "no_speech_prob": 1.6035417351595305e-12}, {"id": 492, "seek": 170846, "start": 1724.3400000000001, "end": 1729.9, "text": " thicker coupling terms, or a deeper hierarchy than just using conventional state-centric math,", "tokens": [51159, 18142, 37447, 2115, 11, 420, 257, 7731, 22333, 813, 445, 1228, 16011, 1785, 12, 45300, 5221, 11, 51437], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1542666480654762, "compression_ratio": 1.596026490066225, "no_speech_prob": 1.6035417351595305e-12}, {"id": 493, "seek": 170846, "start": 1730.1200000000001, "end": 1732.5, "text": " then the theory fails its first test.", "tokens": [51448, 550, 264, 5261, 18199, 1080, 700, 1500, 13, 51567], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1542666480654762, "compression_ratio": 1.596026490066225, "no_speech_prob": 1.6035417351595305e-12}, {"id": 494, "seek": 170846, "start": 1732.72, "end": 1735.68, "text": " Elegance is scientifically useless if it balloons the data budget.", "tokens": [51578, 462, 6363, 719, 307, 39719, 14115, 498, 309, 26193, 264, 1412, 4706, 13, 51726], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1542666480654762, "compression_ratio": 1.596026490066225, "no_speech_prob": 1.6035417351595305e-12}, {"id": 495, "seek": 173568, "start": 1735.68, "end": 1741.74, "text": " It would mean the Amplit-Wist is just a bloated, expensive way to describe something we already know how to describe cheaply.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 576, 914, 264, 2012, 564, 270, 12, 54, 468, 307, 445, 257, 1749, 770, 11, 5124, 636, 281, 6786, 746, 321, 1217, 458, 577, 281, 6786, 7084, 356, 13, 50668], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 496, "seek": 173568, "start": 1741.94, "end": 1745.9, "text": " But Flexion seems confident it will pass the compactness test for steady gates.", "tokens": [50678, 583, 29208, 313, 2544, 6679, 309, 486, 1320, 264, 14679, 1287, 1500, 337, 13211, 19792, 13, 50876], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 497, "seek": 173568, "start": 1746.4, "end": 1749.8, "text": " It's the second failure mode that seems like a massive, violent hurdle.", "tokens": [50901, 467, 311, 264, 1150, 7763, 4391, 300, 2544, 411, 257, 5994, 11, 11867, 47423, 13, 51071], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 498, "seek": 173568, "start": 1749.94, "end": 1751.8200000000002, "text": " Around contact discontinuities.", "tokens": [51078, 17633, 3385, 31420, 84, 1088, 13, 51172], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 499, "seek": 173568, "start": 1752.2, "end": 1752.52, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51191, 1079, 13, 51207], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 500, "seek": 173568, "start": 1752.94, "end": 1754.46, "text": " When I read this, I immediately thought,", "tokens": [51228, 1133, 286, 1401, 341, 11, 286, 4258, 1194, 11, 51304], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 501, "seek": 173568, "start": 1754.8, "end": 1755.78, "text": " this breaks the math.", "tokens": [51321, 341, 9857, 264, 5221, 13, 51370], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 502, "seek": 173568, "start": 1755.96, "end": 1759.54, "text": " It is the most critical threat to the smooth mathematics we've been discussing.", "tokens": [51379, 467, 307, 264, 881, 4924, 4734, 281, 264, 5508, 18666, 321, 600, 668, 10850, 13, 51558], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 503, "seek": 173568, "start": 1759.98, "end": 1762.18, "text": " The Kuramoto model, the Amplit-Wist,", "tokens": [51580, 440, 16481, 35858, 2316, 11, 264, 2012, 564, 270, 12, 54, 468, 11, 51690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13397219708857647, "compression_ratio": 1.6143790849673203, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888043035348746e-12}, {"id": 504, "seek": 176218, "start": 1762.18, "end": 1765.22, "text": " all of it assumes smooth, continuous flow.", "tokens": [50365, 439, 295, 309, 37808, 5508, 11, 10957, 3095, 13, 50517], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 505, "seek": 176218, "start": 1765.92, "end": 1769.38, "text": " The phases evolve like a smooth wave.", "tokens": [50552, 440, 18764, 16693, 411, 257, 5508, 5772, 13, 50725], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 506, "seek": 176218, "start": 1769.5600000000002, "end": 1771.28, "text": " But walking is not a smooth wave.", "tokens": [50734, 583, 4494, 307, 406, 257, 5508, 5772, 13, 50820], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 507, "seek": 176218, "start": 1771.72, "end": 1776.46, "text": " Every single time your foot hits the ground, it is a violent, discrete collision.", "tokens": [50842, 2048, 2167, 565, 428, 2671, 8664, 264, 2727, 11, 309, 307, 257, 11867, 11, 27706, 24644, 13, 51079], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 508, "seek": 176218, "start": 1776.92, "end": 1777.48, "text": " It is.", "tokens": [51102, 467, 307, 13, 51130], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 509, "seek": 176218, "start": 1777.66, "end": 1783.3600000000001, "text": " The physical constraint structure of your limb changes instantly from swinging freely in the air", "tokens": [51139, 440, 4001, 25534, 3877, 295, 428, 30390, 2962, 13518, 490, 29500, 16433, 294, 264, 1988, 51424], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 510, "seek": 176218, "start": 1783.3600000000001, "end": 1785.72, "text": " to being slammed into a movable concrete.", "tokens": [51424, 281, 885, 50196, 666, 257, 2402, 712, 9859, 13, 51542], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 511, "seek": 176218, "start": 1785.98, "end": 1786.38, "text": " Hang on.", "tokens": [51555, 14070, 322, 13, 51575], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19354911380343967, "compression_ratio": 1.588235294117647, "no_speech_prob": 1.7144712299160814e-12}, {"id": 512, "seek": 178638, "start": 1786.38, "end": 1792.0, "text": " You're slamming your heel into the pavement, which completely shatters the smooth marching band rhythm.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 434, 25617, 2810, 428, 9430, 666, 264, 38305, 11, 597, 2584, 402, 37690, 264, 5508, 30523, 4116, 11801, 13, 50646], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13498487385041122, "compression_ratio": 1.6480263157894737, "no_speech_prob": 2.1503881574708172e-12}, {"id": 513, "seek": 178638, "start": 1792.5600000000002, "end": 1796.5800000000002, "text": " Are you telling me multiplying a complex number suddenly fixes a physical collision?", "tokens": [50674, 2014, 291, 3585, 385, 30955, 257, 3997, 1230, 5800, 32539, 257, 4001, 24644, 30, 50875], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13498487385041122, "compression_ratio": 1.6480263157894737, "no_speech_prob": 2.1503881574708172e-12}, {"id": 514, "seek": 178638, "start": 1797.0, "end": 1801.18, "text": " Well, Flexion claims this can be solved using something called hybrid dynamical systems.", "tokens": [50896, 1042, 11, 29208, 313, 9441, 341, 393, 312, 13041, 1228, 746, 1219, 13051, 5999, 804, 3652, 13, 51105], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13498487385041122, "compression_ratio": 1.6480263157894737, "no_speech_prob": 2.1503881574708172e-12}, {"id": 515, "seek": 178638, "start": 1801.6000000000001, "end": 1804.6000000000001, "text": " I need a better explanation of that because it sounds like math magic.", "tokens": [51126, 286, 643, 257, 1101, 10835, 295, 300, 570, 309, 3263, 411, 5221, 5585, 13, 51276], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13498487385041122, "compression_ratio": 1.6480263157894737, "no_speech_prob": 2.1503881574708172e-12}, {"id": 516, "seek": 178638, "start": 1804.8400000000001, "end": 1806.8000000000002, "text": " Let's unpack the hybrid dynamical system.", "tokens": [51288, 961, 311, 26699, 264, 13051, 5999, 804, 1185, 13, 51386], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13498487385041122, "compression_ratio": 1.6480263157894737, "no_speech_prob": 2.1503881574708172e-12}, {"id": 517, "seek": 178638, "start": 1807.0, "end": 1813.1200000000001, "text": " In mathematics, this is a system where a continuous, smooth flow is interrupted by a discrete guard condition.", "tokens": [51396, 682, 18666, 11, 341, 307, 257, 1185, 689, 257, 10957, 11, 5508, 3095, 307, 30329, 538, 257, 27706, 6290, 4188, 13, 51702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13498487385041122, "compression_ratio": 1.6480263157894737, "no_speech_prob": 2.1503881574708172e-12}, {"id": 518, "seek": 181312, "start": 1813.12, "end": 1817.02, "text": " In locomotion, the smooth flow is the legs swinging through the air.", "tokens": [50365, 682, 36369, 19228, 11, 264, 5508, 3095, 307, 264, 5668, 29500, 807, 264, 1988, 13, 50560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11862321333451704, "compression_ratio": 1.6853146853146854, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045729198457814e-12}, {"id": 519, "seek": 181312, "start": 1817.4799999999998, "end": 1821.58, "text": " The guard condition is the physical elevation of the foot hitting zero of the ground.", "tokens": [50583, 440, 6290, 4188, 307, 264, 4001, 25827, 295, 264, 2671, 8850, 4018, 295, 264, 2727, 13, 50788], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11862321333451704, "compression_ratio": 1.6853146853146854, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045729198457814e-12}, {"id": 520, "seek": 181312, "start": 1821.9399999999998, "end": 1826.86, "text": " Okay, but what actually happens to the internal math at the exact microsecond of impact?", "tokens": [50806, 1033, 11, 457, 437, 767, 2314, 281, 264, 6920, 5221, 412, 264, 1900, 3123, 37841, 18882, 295, 2712, 30, 51052], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11862321333451704, "compression_ratio": 1.6853146853146854, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045729198457814e-12}, {"id": 521, "seek": 181312, "start": 1827.1999999999998, "end": 1828.9199999999998, "text": " This is Flexion's conjecture one.", "tokens": [51069, 639, 307, 29208, 313, 311, 416, 1020, 540, 472, 13, 51155], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11862321333451704, "compression_ratio": 1.6853146853146854, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045729198457814e-12}, {"id": 522, "seek": 181312, "start": 1829.36, "end": 1833.7399999999998, "text": " The author proposes that the physical impact of the heel strike acts as a reset map.", "tokens": [51177, 440, 3793, 2365, 4201, 300, 264, 4001, 2712, 295, 264, 9430, 9302, 10672, 382, 257, 14322, 4471, 13, 51396], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11862321333451704, "compression_ratio": 1.6853146853146854, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045729198457814e-12}, {"id": 523, "seek": 181312, "start": 1834.32, "end": 1842.2199999999998, "text": " And crucially, this reset map must act as a single instantaneous Amplit-Wist operator applied to the pre-impact rhythm.", "tokens": [51425, 400, 5140, 1909, 11, 341, 14322, 4471, 1633, 605, 382, 257, 2167, 45596, 2012, 564, 270, 12, 54, 468, 12973, 6456, 281, 264, 659, 12, 8814, 578, 11801, 13, 51820], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11862321333451704, "compression_ratio": 1.6853146853146854, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045729198457814e-12}, {"id": 524, "seek": 184222, "start": 1842.22, "end": 1847.14, "text": " Really, meaning you just take the complex number representing the rhythm right before the heel strikes,", "tokens": [50365, 4083, 11, 3620, 291, 445, 747, 264, 3997, 1230, 13460, 264, 11801, 558, 949, 264, 9430, 16750, 11, 50611], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11810107941323138, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.7349392322091317e-12}, {"id": 525, "seek": 184222, "start": 1847.6000000000001, "end": 1854.34, "text": " and you multiply it by one specific impact complex number, and that instantly spits out the correct post-impact rhythm.", "tokens": [50634, 293, 291, 12972, 309, 538, 472, 2685, 2712, 3997, 1230, 11, 293, 300, 13518, 637, 1208, 484, 264, 3006, 2183, 12, 8814, 578, 11801, 13, 50971], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11810107941323138, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.7349392322091317e-12}, {"id": 526, "seek": 184222, "start": 1854.5, "end": 1854.78, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50979, 1079, 13, 50993], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11810107941323138, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.7349392322091317e-12}, {"id": 527, "seek": 184222, "start": 1855.42, "end": 1862.88, "text": " The physical shockwave traveling up your bones and muscles is mathematically compressed into a single sudden scaling and rotation of the internal rhythm.", "tokens": [51025, 440, 4001, 5588, 35461, 9712, 493, 428, 10491, 293, 9530, 307, 44003, 30353, 666, 257, 2167, 3990, 21589, 293, 12447, 295, 264, 6920, 11801, 13, 51398], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11810107941323138, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.7349392322091317e-12}, {"id": 528, "seek": 184222, "start": 1863.08, "end": 1864.88, "text": " That is a wildly bold bet.", "tokens": [51408, 663, 307, 257, 34731, 11928, 778, 13, 51498], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11810107941323138, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.7349392322091317e-12}, {"id": 529, "seek": 184222, "start": 1864.92, "end": 1865.58, "text": " Very bold.", "tokens": [51500, 4372, 11928, 13, 51533], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11810107941323138, "compression_ratio": 1.6535433070866141, "no_speech_prob": 1.7349392322091317e-12}, {"id": 530, "seek": 186558, "start": 1865.58, "end": 1875.08, "text": " If the physics of bone, muscle, and pavement colliding requires math that is even slightly more complicated than a simple complex multiplication to reset the rhythm, the theory dies right there.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 264, 10649, 295, 9026, 11, 8679, 11, 293, 38305, 1263, 2819, 7029, 5221, 300, 307, 754, 4748, 544, 6179, 813, 257, 2199, 3997, 27290, 281, 14322, 264, 11801, 11, 264, 5261, 2714, 558, 456, 13, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11312155101610266, "compression_ratio": 1.5555555555555556, "no_speech_prob": 1.4155191775666598e-12}, {"id": 531, "seek": 186558, "start": 1875.3, "end": 1875.8999999999999, "text": " It does.", "tokens": [50851, 467, 775, 13, 50881], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11312155101610266, "compression_ratio": 1.5555555555555556, "no_speech_prob": 1.4155191775666598e-12}, {"id": 532, "seek": 186558, "start": 1876.12, "end": 1879.48, "text": " And Flexion admits this is a strict, highly falsifiable claim.", "tokens": [50892, 400, 29208, 313, 46682, 341, 307, 257, 10910, 11, 5405, 16720, 30876, 3932, 13, 51060], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11312155101610266, "compression_ratio": 1.5555555555555556, "no_speech_prob": 1.4155191775666598e-12}, {"id": 533, "seek": 186558, "start": 1879.96, "end": 1887.02, "text": " They restrict this conjecture to planar single-point contact just to give it a fair trial in a controlled environment.", "tokens": [51084, 814, 7694, 341, 416, 1020, 540, 281, 1393, 289, 2167, 12, 6053, 3385, 445, 281, 976, 309, 257, 3143, 7308, 294, 257, 10164, 2823, 13, 51437], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11312155101610266, "compression_ratio": 1.5555555555555556, "no_speech_prob": 1.4155191775666598e-12}, {"id": 534, "seek": 186558, "start": 1887.3, "end": 1887.54, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51451, 1779, 13, 51463], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11312155101610266, "compression_ratio": 1.5555555555555556, "no_speech_prob": 1.4155191775666598e-12}, {"id": 535, "seek": 188754, "start": 1887.54, "end": 1894.08, "text": " But if it fails to elegantly compress the collision even in that restricted setting, the geometry is abandoned.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 498, 309, 18199, 281, 14459, 3627, 14778, 264, 24644, 754, 294, 300, 20608, 3287, 11, 264, 18426, 307, 13732, 13, 50692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11533804784847211, "compression_ratio": 1.5635593220338984, "no_speech_prob": 1.8528772266490634e-12}, {"id": 536, "seek": 188754, "start": 1894.62, "end": 1906.42, "text": " If a mathematical framework only works in the air during the swing phase and requires completely unrelated clunky machinery to handle the foot strike, it isn't a grand theory of locomotion.", "tokens": [50719, 759, 257, 18894, 8388, 787, 1985, 294, 264, 1988, 1830, 264, 11173, 5574, 293, 7029, 2584, 38967, 596, 25837, 27302, 281, 4813, 264, 2671, 9302, 11, 309, 1943, 380, 257, 2697, 5261, 295, 36369, 19228, 13, 51309], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11533804784847211, "compression_ratio": 1.5635593220338984, "no_speech_prob": 1.8528772266490634e-12}, {"id": 537, "seek": 188754, "start": 1906.78, "end": 1910.48, "text": " Okay, so the heel strike is a violent but predictable interruption.", "tokens": [51327, 1033, 11, 370, 264, 9430, 9302, 307, 257, 11867, 457, 27737, 728, 11266, 13, 51512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11533804784847211, "compression_ratio": 1.5635593220338984, "no_speech_prob": 1.8528772266490634e-12}, {"id": 538, "seek": 191048, "start": 1910.48, "end": 1913.46, "text": " The system expects the ground to be there.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 1185, 33280, 264, 2727, 281, 312, 456, 13, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 539, "seek": 191048, "start": 1914.1200000000001, "end": 1916.16, "text": " But what happens when the unexpected occurs?", "tokens": [50547, 583, 437, 2314, 562, 264, 13106, 11843, 30, 50649], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 540, "seek": 191048, "start": 1916.32, "end": 1917.18, "text": " That's the real test.", "tokens": [50657, 663, 311, 264, 957, 1500, 13, 50700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 541, "seek": 191048, "start": 1917.3, "end": 1919.96, "text": " What happens when the system is shoved to the brink of total failure?", "tokens": [50706, 708, 2314, 562, 264, 1185, 307, 2223, 937, 281, 264, 738, 475, 295, 3217, 7763, 30, 50839], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 542, "seek": 191048, "start": 1920.3600000000001, "end": 1924.66, "text": " Say you're walking and you hit a patch of black ice or someone physically shoves you from behind.", "tokens": [50859, 6463, 291, 434, 4494, 293, 291, 2045, 257, 9972, 295, 2211, 4435, 420, 1580, 9762, 2223, 977, 291, 490, 2261, 13, 51074], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 543, "seek": 191048, "start": 1925.02, "end": 1928.82, "text": " That brings us to the third and decisive test, the stumble test.", "tokens": [51092, 663, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 2636, 293, 34998, 1500, 11, 264, 41302, 1500, 13, 51282], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 544, "seek": 191048, "start": 1929.1200000000001, "end": 1931.58, "text": " Steady gait and predictable foot strikes are one thing.", "tokens": [51297, 3592, 880, 290, 1001, 293, 27737, 2671, 16750, 366, 472, 551, 13, 51420], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 545, "seek": 191048, "start": 1932.02, "end": 1937.56, "text": " But balanced recovery, surviving a stumble, forces the body into a chaotic, transient response.", "tokens": [51442, 583, 13902, 8597, 11, 24948, 257, 41302, 11, 5874, 264, 1772, 666, 257, 27013, 11, 41998, 4134, 13, 51719], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1404356409291752, "compression_ratio": 1.7152777777777777, "no_speech_prob": 1.7485558357135944e-12}, {"id": 546, "seek": 193756, "start": 1937.56, "end": 1943.6599999999999, "text": " A person flailing their arms and scrambling their legs to stay upright doesn't look like any normal periodic gait.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 954, 932, 23315, 641, 5812, 293, 5918, 19391, 641, 5668, 281, 1754, 27405, 1177, 380, 574, 411, 604, 2710, 27790, 290, 1001, 13, 50670], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19123512186029906, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 2.3525419893394295e-12}, {"id": 547, "seek": 193756, "start": 1944.06, "end": 1945.1799999999998, "text": " No, it looks like panic.", "tokens": [50690, 883, 11, 309, 1542, 411, 14783, 13, 50746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19123512186029906, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 2.3525419893394295e-12}, {"id": 548, "seek": 193756, "start": 1946.3799999999999, "end": 1948.3799999999999, "text": " So how does the amplet whist handle a shove?", "tokens": [50806, 407, 577, 775, 264, 669, 14657, 315, 468, 4813, 257, 35648, 30, 50906], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19123512186029906, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 2.3525419893394295e-12}, {"id": 549, "seek": 193756, "start": 1948.76, "end": 1949.74, "text": " This is conjecture two.", "tokens": [50925, 639, 307, 416, 1020, 540, 732, 13, 50974], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19123512186029906, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 2.3525419893394295e-12}, {"id": 550, "seek": 193756, "start": 1950.7, "end": 1953.04, "text": " Coherence collapse as a recovery signature.", "tokens": [51022, 3066, 511, 655, 15584, 382, 257, 8597, 13397, 13, 51139], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19123512186029906, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 2.3525419893394295e-12}, {"id": 551, "seek": 193756, "start": 1953.3999999999999, "end": 1956.26, "text": " And this is the concept I mentioned at the very beginning of the deep dive.", "tokens": [51157, 400, 341, 307, 264, 3410, 286, 2835, 412, 264, 588, 2863, 295, 264, 2452, 9192, 13, 51300], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19123512186029906, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 2.3525419893394295e-12}, {"id": 552, "seek": 193756, "start": 1956.3999999999999, "end": 1956.54, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51307, 1779, 13, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19123512186029906, "compression_ratio": 1.5227272727272727, "no_speech_prob": 2.3525419893394295e-12}, {"id": 553, "seek": 195654, "start": 1956.54, "end": 1972.0, "text": " Collection hypothesizes that when balance is threatened, the internal mathematical coherence, the R value at the highest level of the chain, must drop sharply and measurably before any visible loss of balance occurs externally.", "tokens": [50365, 30981, 14276, 5660, 300, 562, 4772, 307, 18268, 11, 264, 6920, 18894, 26528, 655, 11, 264, 497, 2158, 412, 264, 6343, 1496, 295, 264, 5021, 11, 1633, 3270, 42893, 293, 5731, 374, 1188, 949, 604, 8974, 4470, 295, 4772, 11843, 40899, 13, 51138], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10311959100806195, "compression_ratio": 1.4367088607594938, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011341337316854e-12}, {"id": 554, "seek": 197200, "start": 1972.0, "end": 1976.86, "text": " The internal phase synchronization among the neural oscillators breaks down first.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 6920, 5574, 19331, 2144, 3654, 264, 18161, 18225, 3391, 9857, 760, 700, 13, 50608], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12531957211701766, "compression_ratio": 1.683168316831683, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130352483058718e-12}, {"id": 555, "seek": 197200, "start": 1977.34, "end": 1979.62, "text": " The marching band loses its rhythm internally.", "tokens": [50632, 440, 30523, 4116, 18293, 1080, 11801, 19501, 13, 50746], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12531957211701766, "compression_ratio": 1.683168316831683, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130352483058718e-12}, {"id": 556, "seek": 197200, "start": 1980.16, "end": 1981.26, "text": " The bungee cords snap.", "tokens": [50773, 440, 6702, 31577, 36302, 13650, 13, 50828], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12531957211701766, "compression_ratio": 1.683168316831683, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130352483058718e-12}, {"id": 557, "seek": 197200, "start": 1981.74, "end": 1990.4, "text": " And then recovery is marked by the phase relocking the R value increasing monotonically back toward one as the system figures out how to stand up straight again.", "tokens": [50852, 400, 550, 8597, 307, 12658, 538, 264, 5574, 319, 4102, 278, 264, 497, 2158, 5662, 1108, 27794, 984, 646, 7361, 472, 382, 264, 1185, 9624, 484, 577, 281, 1463, 493, 2997, 797, 13, 51285], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12531957211701766, "compression_ratio": 1.683168316831683, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130352483058718e-12}, {"id": 558, "seek": 197200, "start": 1990.84, "end": 1993.22, "text": " So it's like a neurological seismic warning system.", "tokens": [51307, 407, 309, 311, 411, 257, 48185, 40159, 299, 9164, 1185, 13, 51426], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12531957211701766, "compression_ratio": 1.683168316831683, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130352483058718e-12}, {"id": 559, "seek": 197200, "start": 1993.38, "end": 1993.48, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51434, 865, 13, 51439], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12531957211701766, "compression_ratio": 1.683168316831683, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130352483058718e-12}, {"id": 560, "seek": 197200, "start": 1993.58, "end": 2000.04, "text": " The internal rhythm starts to desynchronize and shatter before gravity actually pulls the physical center of mass over the tipping point.", "tokens": [51444, 440, 6920, 11801, 3719, 281, 730, 36420, 1125, 293, 402, 1161, 949, 12110, 767, 16982, 264, 4001, 3056, 295, 2758, 670, 264, 41625, 935, 13, 51767], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12531957211701766, "compression_ratio": 1.683168316831683, "no_speech_prob": 1.5130352483058718e-12}, {"id": 561, "seek": 200004, "start": 2000.04, "end": 2002.2, "text": " This raises an important question, though.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 19658, 364, 1021, 1168, 11, 1673, 13, 50473], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 562, "seek": 200004, "start": 2002.3, "end": 2002.6599999999999, "text": " Which is...", "tokens": [50478, 3013, 307, 485, 50496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 563, "seek": 200004, "start": 2002.6599999999999, "end": 2008.26, "text": " If researchers check the tape and don't see that internal drop precede the physical fall, the theory is wrong.", "tokens": [50496, 759, 10309, 1520, 264, 7314, 293, 500, 380, 536, 300, 6920, 3270, 16969, 68, 264, 4001, 2100, 11, 264, 5261, 307, 2085, 13, 50776], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 564, "seek": 200004, "start": 2008.3999999999999, "end": 2009.42, "text": " Out the window entirely.", "tokens": [50783, 5925, 264, 4910, 7696, 13, 50834], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 565, "seek": 200004, "start": 2009.74, "end": 2010.1, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50850, 1079, 13, 50868], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 566, "seek": 200004, "start": 2010.8999999999999, "end": 2021.72, "text": " If the coherent signal R remains perfectly steady right up until the exact moment the body physically tips over, then the amplet whist is only a description of steady, happy walking.", "tokens": [50908, 759, 264, 36239, 6358, 497, 7023, 6239, 13211, 558, 493, 1826, 264, 1900, 1623, 264, 1772, 9762, 6082, 670, 11, 550, 264, 669, 14657, 315, 468, 307, 787, 257, 3855, 295, 13211, 11, 2055, 4494, 13, 51449], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 567, "seek": 200004, "start": 2022.54, "end": 2026.28, "text": " It cannot claim to govern the true dynamics of stability and balance.", "tokens": [51490, 467, 2644, 3932, 281, 1980, 264, 2074, 15679, 295, 11826, 293, 4772, 13, 51677], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 568, "seek": 200004, "start": 2026.6399999999999, "end": 2029.7, "text": " But testing this sounded incredibly expensive to me at first.", "tokens": [51695, 583, 4997, 341, 17714, 6252, 5124, 281, 385, 412, 700, 13, 51848], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15440508097159764, "compression_ratio": 1.59375, "no_speech_prob": 1.9582668819850824e-12}, {"id": 569, "seek": 202970, "start": 2029.7, "end": 2037.18, "text": " Do we have to build millions of dollars worth of new robots or wire up thousands of humans with invasive spinal probes to prove this?", "tokens": [50365, 1144, 321, 362, 281, 1322, 6803, 295, 3808, 3163, 295, 777, 14733, 420, 6234, 493, 5383, 295, 6255, 365, 30894, 28022, 1239, 279, 281, 7081, 341, 30, 50739], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09842361838130628, "compression_ratio": 1.7239057239057238, "no_speech_prob": 1.75475595425717e-12}, {"id": 570, "seek": 202970, "start": 2037.44, "end": 2039.82, "text": " That is the genius of Fliction's proposal.", "tokens": [50752, 663, 307, 264, 14017, 295, 3235, 4105, 311, 11494, 13, 50871], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09842361838130628, "compression_ratio": 1.7239057239057238, "no_speech_prob": 1.75475595425717e-12}, {"id": 571, "seek": 202970, "start": 2040.0, "end": 2043.76, "text": " We don't need invasive probes and we don't need a dime of new data collection.", "tokens": [50880, 492, 500, 380, 643, 30894, 1239, 279, 293, 321, 500, 380, 643, 257, 36330, 295, 777, 1412, 5765, 13, 51068], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09842361838130628, "compression_ratio": 1.7239057239057238, "no_speech_prob": 1.75475595425717e-12}, {"id": 572, "seek": 202970, "start": 2044.04, "end": 2044.32, "text": " Really?", "tokens": [51082, 4083, 30, 51096], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09842361838130628, "compression_ratio": 1.7239057239057238, "no_speech_prob": 1.75475595425717e-12}, {"id": 573, "seek": 202970, "start": 2044.6200000000001, "end": 2050.7, "text": " Fliction proposes a minimal experiment using data that is already sitting on hard drives right now.", "tokens": [51111, 3235, 4105, 2365, 4201, 257, 13206, 5120, 1228, 1412, 300, 307, 1217, 3798, 322, 1152, 11754, 558, 586, 13, 51415], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09842361838130628, "compression_ratio": 1.7239057239057238, "no_speech_prob": 1.75475595425717e-12}, {"id": 574, "seek": 202970, "start": 2051.36, "end": 2058.88, "text": " Biomechanics databases are full of thousands of recordings of human subjects walking on force plate treadmills while wearing motion capture markers.", "tokens": [51448, 13007, 423, 3484, 1167, 22380, 366, 1577, 295, 5383, 295, 25162, 295, 1952, 13066, 4494, 322, 3464, 5924, 28286, 76, 2565, 1339, 4769, 5394, 7983, 19175, 13, 51824], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09842361838130628, "compression_ratio": 1.7239057239057238, "no_speech_prob": 1.75475595425717e-12}, {"id": 575, "seek": 205888, "start": 2058.88, "end": 2060.12, "text": " Oh, I've seen these studies.", "tokens": [50365, 876, 11, 286, 600, 1612, 613, 5313, 13, 50427], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10895929513154207, "compression_ratio": 1.6140350877192982, "no_speech_prob": 2.100921867032035e-12}, {"id": 576, "seek": 205888, "start": 2060.6400000000003, "end": 2066.6400000000003, "text": " The researchers put the subject in a safety harness and literally jerked the treadmill bolt out from under them to force a stumble.", "tokens": [50453, 440, 10309, 829, 264, 3983, 294, 257, 4514, 19700, 293, 3736, 25197, 292, 264, 46374, 13436, 484, 490, 833, 552, 281, 3464, 257, 41302, 13, 50753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10895929513154207, "compression_ratio": 1.6140350877192982, "no_speech_prob": 2.100921867032035e-12}, {"id": 577, "seek": 205888, "start": 2066.78, "end": 2067.2400000000002, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50760, 7587, 13, 50783], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10895929513154207, "compression_ratio": 1.6140350877192982, "no_speech_prob": 2.100921867032035e-12}, {"id": 578, "seek": 205888, "start": 2067.44, "end": 2071.12, "text": " We already have the high fidelity joint angle time series from those experiments.", "tokens": [50793, 492, 1217, 362, 264, 1090, 46404, 7225, 5802, 565, 2638, 490, 729, 12050, 13, 50977], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10895929513154207, "compression_ratio": 1.6140350877192982, "no_speech_prob": 2.100921867032035e-12}, {"id": 579, "seek": 205888, "start": 2071.46, "end": 2074.94, "text": " We know exactly what the hips, knees, and ankles were doing at every millisecond.", "tokens": [50994, 492, 458, 2293, 437, 264, 15233, 11, 10546, 11, 293, 40962, 645, 884, 412, 633, 27940, 18882, 13, 51168], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10895929513154207, "compression_ratio": 1.6140350877192982, "no_speech_prob": 2.100921867032035e-12}, {"id": 580, "seek": 205888, "start": 2075.04, "end": 2075.92, "text": " So what's the challenge?", "tokens": [51173, 407, 437, 311, 264, 3430, 30, 51217], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10895929513154207, "compression_ratio": 1.6140350877192982, "no_speech_prob": 2.100921867032035e-12}, {"id": 581, "seek": 205888, "start": 2076.2400000000002, "end": 2083.1600000000003, "text": " The challenge is extracting the hidden internal rhythm, the phase, from that raw physical angle data.", "tokens": [51233, 440, 3430, 307, 49844, 264, 7633, 6920, 11801, 11, 264, 5574, 11, 490, 300, 8936, 4001, 5802, 1412, 13, 51579], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10895929513154207, "compression_ratio": 1.6140350877192982, "no_speech_prob": 2.100921867032035e-12}, {"id": 582, "seek": 208316, "start": 2083.16, "end": 2087.14, "text": " And how do we do that without plugging a USB cable into their spine?", "tokens": [50365, 400, 577, 360, 321, 360, 300, 1553, 42975, 257, 10109, 8220, 666, 641, 15395, 30, 50564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1251653035481771, "compression_ratio": 1.5912408759124088, "no_speech_prob": 1.768526189209474e-12}, {"id": 583, "seek": 208316, "start": 2087.52, "end": 2090.54, "text": " By applying a mathematical tool called the Hilbert Transform.", "tokens": [50583, 3146, 9275, 257, 18894, 2290, 1219, 264, 19914, 4290, 27938, 13, 50734], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1251653035481771, "compression_ratio": 1.5912408759124088, "no_speech_prob": 1.768526189209474e-12}, {"id": 584, "seek": 208316, "start": 2090.7799999999997, "end": 2093.6, "text": " Okay, I need a lot of coffee to get through the Hilbert Transform section.", "tokens": [50746, 1033, 11, 286, 643, 257, 688, 295, 4982, 281, 483, 807, 264, 19914, 4290, 27938, 3541, 13, 50887], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1251653035481771, "compression_ratio": 1.5912408759124088, "no_speech_prob": 1.768526189209474e-12}, {"id": 585, "seek": 208316, "start": 2094.3799999999997, "end": 2098.12, "text": " How does it extract a hidden rhythm from a static physical angle?", "tokens": [50926, 1012, 775, 309, 8947, 257, 7633, 11801, 490, 257, 13437, 4001, 5802, 30, 51113], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1251653035481771, "compression_ratio": 1.5912408759124088, "no_speech_prob": 1.768526189209474e-12}, {"id": 586, "seek": 208316, "start": 2098.74, "end": 2100.7, "text": " Think of a pendulum swinging back and forth.", "tokens": [51144, 6557, 295, 257, 44103, 29500, 646, 293, 5220, 13, 51242], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1251653035481771, "compression_ratio": 1.5912408759124088, "no_speech_prob": 1.768526189209474e-12}, {"id": 587, "seek": 208316, "start": 2100.98, "end": 2105.42, "text": " If you just record its angle, you get a one-dimensional line oscillating up and down over time.", "tokens": [51256, 759, 291, 445, 2136, 1080, 5802, 11, 291, 483, 257, 472, 12, 18759, 1622, 18225, 990, 493, 293, 760, 670, 565, 13, 51478], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1251653035481771, "compression_ratio": 1.5912408759124088, "no_speech_prob": 1.768526189209474e-12}, {"id": 588, "seek": 208316, "start": 2105.52, "end": 2106.3999999999996, "text": " Okay, I'm picturing it.", "tokens": [51483, 1033, 11, 286, 478, 2317, 1345, 309, 13, 51527], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1251653035481771, "compression_ratio": 1.5912408759124088, "no_speech_prob": 1.768526189209474e-12}, {"id": 589, "seek": 210640, "start": 2106.4, "end": 2112.14, "text": " But the Hilbert Transform treats that one-dimensional line as just the shadow of a circle.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 264, 19914, 4290, 27938, 19566, 300, 472, 12, 18759, 1622, 382, 445, 264, 8576, 295, 257, 6329, 13, 50652], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0834804849887113, "compression_ratio": 1.6142857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549729472791318e-12}, {"id": 590, "seek": 210640, "start": 2112.4, "end": 2113.36, "text": " The shadow of a circle.", "tokens": [50665, 440, 8576, 295, 257, 6329, 13, 50713], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0834804849887113, "compression_ratio": 1.6142857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549729472791318e-12}, {"id": 591, "seek": 210640, "start": 2113.5, "end": 2120.28, "text": " It mathematically projects that real signal into the imaginary complex plane, creating an analytic signal.", "tokens": [50720, 467, 44003, 4455, 300, 957, 6358, 666, 264, 26164, 3997, 5720, 11, 4084, 364, 40358, 6358, 13, 51059], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0834804849887113, "compression_ratio": 1.6142857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549729472791318e-12}, {"id": 592, "seek": 210640, "start": 2120.42, "end": 2120.9, "text": " Oh, wow.", "tokens": [51066, 876, 11, 6076, 13, 51090], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0834804849887113, "compression_ratio": 1.6142857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549729472791318e-12}, {"id": 593, "seek": 210640, "start": 2121.14, "end": 2130.78, "text": " By doing this, it calculates the instantaneous phase where exactly the pendulum is in its 360-degree cycle at any given microsecond, independent of its physical amplitude.", "tokens": [51102, 3146, 884, 341, 11, 309, 4322, 1024, 264, 45596, 5574, 689, 2293, 264, 44103, 307, 294, 1080, 13898, 12, 34368, 6586, 412, 604, 2212, 3123, 37841, 18882, 11, 6695, 295, 1080, 4001, 27433, 13, 51584], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0834804849887113, "compression_ratio": 1.6142857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549729472791318e-12}, {"id": 594, "seek": 210640, "start": 2131.06, "end": 2134.26, "text": " Ah, it rebuilds the 2D circle from the 1D shadow.", "tokens": [51598, 2438, 11, 309, 16877, 82, 264, 568, 35, 6329, 490, 264, 502, 35, 8576, 13, 51758], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0834804849887113, "compression_ratio": 1.6142857142857143, "no_speech_prob": 1.5549729472791318e-12}, {"id": 595, "seek": 213426, "start": 2134.26, "end": 2146.46, "text": " Yes. And by applying the Hilbert Transform to the raw joint angles of a stumbling human, we can extract an empirical estimator of the internal coherence, which Fliction denotes as R-hat.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 400, 538, 9275, 264, 19914, 4290, 27938, 281, 264, 8936, 7225, 14708, 295, 257, 342, 14188, 1952, 11, 321, 393, 8947, 364, 31886, 8017, 1639, 295, 264, 6920, 26528, 655, 11, 597, 3235, 4105, 1441, 17251, 382, 497, 12, 15178, 13, 50975], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08484336189601732, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.2015978489987589e-12}, {"id": 596, "seek": 213426, "start": 2146.76, "end": 2150.6000000000004, "text": " So the minimal experiment is just running this math on the old treadmill videos.", "tokens": [50990, 407, 264, 13206, 5120, 307, 445, 2614, 341, 5221, 322, 264, 1331, 46374, 2145, 13, 51182], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08484336189601732, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.2015978489987589e-12}, {"id": 597, "seek": 213426, "start": 2150.96, "end": 2163.7200000000003, "text": " You align the data to the exact timestamp where the treadmill was jerked, and you look to see if the extracted R-hat value plummets before the person's biomechanical center of mass crosses the physical margin of stability.", "tokens": [51200, 509, 7975, 264, 1412, 281, 264, 1900, 49108, 1215, 689, 264, 46374, 390, 25197, 292, 11, 293, 291, 574, 281, 536, 498, 264, 34086, 497, 12, 15178, 2158, 25854, 76, 1385, 949, 264, 954, 311, 3228, 423, 3484, 804, 3056, 295, 2758, 28467, 264, 4001, 10270, 295, 11826, 13, 51838], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08484336189601732, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.2015978489987589e-12}, {"id": 598, "seek": 216372, "start": 2163.72, "end": 2172.7599999999998, "text": " Right. The margin of stability is the physical point of no return. If your center of mass crosses outside the boundary of where your feet are planted, gravity wins. You fall.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 440, 10270, 295, 11826, 307, 264, 4001, 935, 295, 572, 2736, 13, 759, 428, 3056, 295, 2758, 28467, 2380, 264, 12866, 295, 689, 428, 3521, 366, 17395, 11, 12110, 10641, 13, 509, 2100, 13, 50817], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0764754630149679, "compression_ratio": 1.7095435684647302, "no_speech_prob": 1.668231091461747e-12}, {"id": 599, "seek": 216372, "start": 2172.9599999999996, "end": 2173.22, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50827, 1033, 13, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0764754630149679, "compression_ratio": 1.7095435684647302, "no_speech_prob": 1.668231091461747e-12}, {"id": 600, "seek": 216372, "start": 2173.54, "end": 2185.58, "text": " The stumble test demands that the mathematical collapse precedes the physical point of no return. It puts the ball entirely in the court of empirical biomechanists. The theory is sitting there, waiting to be decapitated or crowned.", "tokens": [50856, 440, 41302, 1500, 15107, 300, 264, 18894, 15584, 16969, 279, 264, 4001, 935, 295, 572, 2736, 13, 467, 8137, 264, 2594, 7696, 294, 264, 4753, 295, 31886, 3228, 423, 3484, 1751, 13, 440, 5261, 307, 3798, 456, 11, 3806, 281, 312, 368, 9485, 18266, 420, 11841, 292, 13, 51458], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0764754630149679, "compression_ratio": 1.7095435684647302, "no_speech_prob": 1.668231091461747e-12}, {"id": 601, "seek": 218558, "start": 2185.58, "end": 2191.5, "text": " If the R-hat doesn't drop before the visible fall, the strongest claim of the essay falls apart.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 264, 497, 12, 15178, 1177, 380, 3270, 949, 264, 8974, 2100, 11, 264, 16595, 3932, 295, 264, 16238, 8804, 4936, 13, 50661], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0725213149925331, "compression_ratio": 1.5291479820627802, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179341495713763e-12}, {"id": 602, "seek": 218558, "start": 2191.66, "end": 2204.98, "text": " But let's play out the hypothetical. Let's say empirical testing proves Fliction right. The internal coherence does collapse first. If this theory survives the stumble test, its implications have to ripple outward, right?", "tokens": [50669, 583, 718, 311, 862, 484, 264, 33053, 13, 961, 311, 584, 31886, 4997, 25019, 3235, 4105, 558, 13, 440, 6920, 26528, 655, 775, 15584, 700, 13, 759, 341, 5261, 46231, 264, 41302, 1500, 11, 1080, 16602, 362, 281, 40688, 26914, 11, 558, 30, 51335], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0725213149925331, "compression_ratio": 1.5291479820627802, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179341495713763e-12}, {"id": 603, "seek": 218558, "start": 2205.0, "end": 2205.92, "text": " They absolutely would.", "tokens": [51336, 814, 3122, 576, 13, 51382], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0725213149925331, "compression_ratio": 1.5291479820627802, "no_speech_prob": 1.8179341495713763e-12}, {"id": 604, "seek": 220592, "start": 2205.92, "end": 2213.32, "text": " If this geometry truly dictates how systems organize balance, does it apply to fields that have absolutely nothing to do with legs?", "tokens": [50365, 759, 341, 18426, 4908, 12569, 1024, 577, 3652, 13859, 4772, 11, 775, 309, 3079, 281, 7909, 300, 362, 3122, 1825, 281, 360, 365, 5668, 30, 50735], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08612463209364149, "compression_ratio": 1.549645390070922, "no_speech_prob": 2.5242813481846094e-12}, {"id": 605, "seek": 220592, "start": 2214.02, "end": 2227.48, "text": " Fliction briefly explores this in Section 8. If the structural pattern holds that complex systems are controlled by selecting higher-level generative operators rather than micromanaging specific states, we see echoes of it everywhere.", "tokens": [50770, 3235, 4105, 10515, 45473, 341, 294, 21804, 1649, 13, 759, 264, 15067, 5102, 9190, 300, 3997, 3652, 366, 10164, 538, 18182, 2946, 12, 12418, 1337, 1166, 19077, 2831, 813, 3123, 81, 4277, 3568, 2685, 4368, 11, 321, 536, 47051, 295, 309, 5315, 13, 51443], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08612463209364149, "compression_ratio": 1.549645390070922, "no_speech_prob": 2.5242813481846094e-12}, {"id": 606, "seek": 220592, "start": 2227.76, "end": 2228.2200000000003, "text": " Like where?", "tokens": [51457, 1743, 689, 30, 51480], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08612463209364149, "compression_ratio": 1.549645390070922, "no_speech_prob": 2.5242813481846094e-12}, {"id": 607, "seek": 220592, "start": 2228.38, "end": 2231.4, "text": " Take hierarchical keyboard interfaces and software design.", "tokens": [51488, 3664, 35250, 804, 10186, 28416, 293, 4722, 1715, 13, 51639], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08612463209364149, "compression_ratio": 1.549645390070922, "no_speech_prob": 2.5242813481846094e-12}, {"id": 608, "seek": 223140, "start": 2231.4, "end": 2238.84, "text": " Oh, this reminded me of using old-school terminal programs. Instead of explicitly typing out every single command, you press a leader key.", "tokens": [50365, 876, 11, 341, 15920, 385, 295, 1228, 1331, 12, 22779, 14709, 4268, 13, 7156, 295, 20803, 18444, 484, 633, 2167, 5622, 11, 291, 1886, 257, 5263, 2141, 13, 50737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09733423785628559, "compression_ratio": 1.5858585858585859, "no_speech_prob": 1.965937829195852e-12}, {"id": 609, "seek": 223140, "start": 2239.04, "end": 2239.26, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50747, 1779, 13, 50758], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09733423785628559, "compression_ratio": 1.5858585858585859, "no_speech_prob": 1.965937829195852e-12}, {"id": 610, "seek": 223140, "start": 2239.38, "end": 2248.4, "text": " The leader key doesn't type a letter. It shifts the keyboard into a new behavior class. It selects a generative process rather than specifying a final state.", "tokens": [50764, 440, 5263, 2141, 1177, 380, 2010, 257, 5063, 13, 467, 19201, 264, 10186, 666, 257, 777, 5223, 1508, 13, 467, 3048, 82, 257, 1337, 1166, 1399, 2831, 813, 1608, 5489, 257, 2572, 1785, 13, 51215], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09733423785628559, "compression_ratio": 1.5858585858585859, "no_speech_prob": 1.965937829195852e-12}, {"id": 611, "seek": 223140, "start": 2248.78, "end": 2257.94, "text": " Fliction leaves it open whether software interfaces strictly admit an Amplit-WIST interpretation, but the hierarchical operator-driven structure is undeniably similar.", "tokens": [51234, 3235, 4105, 5510, 309, 1269, 1968, 4722, 28416, 20792, 9796, 364, 2012, 564, 270, 12, 54, 19756, 14174, 11, 457, 264, 35250, 804, 12973, 12, 25456, 3877, 307, 674, 15711, 1188, 2531, 13, 51692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09733423785628559, "compression_ratio": 1.5858585858585859, "no_speech_prob": 1.965937829195852e-12}, {"id": 612, "seek": 225794, "start": 2257.94, "end": 2266.54, "text": " But the application that truly caught my eye was auditory scene analysis. Specifically, the cocktail party problem.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 264, 3861, 300, 4908, 5415, 452, 3313, 390, 17748, 827, 4145, 5215, 13, 26058, 11, 264, 26382, 3595, 1154, 13, 50795], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08977760515714947, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 2.092413915744107e-12}, {"id": 613, "seek": 225794, "start": 2266.7000000000003, "end": 2268.76, "text": " Yes, that is a fascinating connection.", "tokens": [50803, 1079, 11, 300, 307, 257, 10343, 4984, 13, 50906], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08977760515714947, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 2.092413915744107e-12}, {"id": 614, "seek": 225794, "start": 2268.96, "end": 2275.02, "text": " It's how computers and our own brains separate overlapping voices in a crowded, noisy room.", "tokens": [50916, 467, 311, 577, 10807, 293, 527, 1065, 15442, 4994, 33535, 9802, 294, 257, 21634, 11, 24518, 1808, 13, 51219], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08977760515714947, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 2.092413915744107e-12}, {"id": 615, "seek": 225794, "start": 2275.46, "end": 2282.32, "text": " It's a notoriously difficult problem. If two people are talking at the exact same time, their voices overlap in the same frequency bands.", "tokens": [51241, 467, 311, 257, 46772, 8994, 2252, 1154, 13, 759, 732, 561, 366, 1417, 412, 264, 1900, 912, 565, 11, 641, 9802, 19959, 294, 264, 912, 7893, 13543, 13, 51584], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08977760515714947, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 2.092413915744107e-12}, {"id": 616, "seek": 225794, "start": 2282.46, "end": 2283.54, "text": " So you can't just filter them.", "tokens": [51591, 407, 291, 393, 380, 445, 6608, 552, 13, 51645], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08977760515714947, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 2.092413915744107e-12}, {"id": 617, "seek": 228354, "start": 2283.54, "end": 2292.04, "text": " No. If a computer just tries to slice the audio up by frequency, like adjusting a graphic equalizer, it fails completely. It just muffles both voices.", "tokens": [50365, 883, 13, 759, 257, 3820, 445, 9898, 281, 13153, 264, 6278, 493, 538, 7893, 11, 411, 23559, 257, 14089, 2681, 6545, 11, 309, 18199, 2584, 13, 467, 445, 22635, 904, 1293, 9802, 13, 50790], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11015182537036938, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 1.7410991268521081e-12}, {"id": 618, "seek": 228354, "start": 2292.2, "end": 2293.84, "text": " So how do modern algorithms solve it?", "tokens": [50798, 407, 577, 360, 4363, 14642, 5039, 309, 30, 50880], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11015182537036938, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 1.7410991268521081e-12}, {"id": 619, "seek": 228354, "start": 2294.2799999999997, "end": 2298.3, "text": " By utilizing the exact same synchronization mathematics we've been discussing.", "tokens": [50902, 3146, 26775, 264, 1900, 912, 19331, 2144, 18666, 321, 600, 668, 10850, 13, 51103], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11015182537036938, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 1.7410991268521081e-12}, {"id": 620, "seek": 228354, "start": 2298.66, "end": 2306.2599999999998, "text": " Advanced audio algorithms group sound components by driving them into phase synchrony with other components originating from the same source.", "tokens": [51121, 26951, 6278, 14642, 1594, 1626, 6677, 538, 4840, 552, 666, 5574, 19331, 88, 365, 661, 6677, 4957, 990, 490, 264, 912, 4009, 13, 51501], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11015182537036938, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 1.7410991268521081e-12}, {"id": 621, "seek": 228354, "start": 2306.4, "end": 2306.72, "text": " Whoa.", "tokens": [51508, 7521, 13, 51524], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11015182537036938, "compression_ratio": 1.583969465648855, "no_speech_prob": 1.7410991268521081e-12}, {"id": 622, "seek": 230672, "start": 2306.72, "end": 2310.58, "text": " And then pushing them out of synchrony with components from the background noise.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 550, 7380, 552, 484, 295, 19331, 88, 365, 6677, 490, 264, 3678, 5658, 13, 50558], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15317757924397787, "compression_ratio": 1.6359649122807018, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888051708966126e-12}, {"id": 623, "seek": 230672, "start": 2310.58, "end": 2314.8799999999997, "text": " They literally use the Kuramoto order parameter to isolate the voice.", "tokens": [50558, 814, 3736, 764, 264, 16481, 35858, 1668, 13075, 281, 25660, 264, 3177, 13, 50773], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15317757924397787, "compression_ratio": 1.6359649122807018, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888051708966126e-12}, {"id": 624, "seek": 230672, "start": 2315.2599999999998, "end": 2320.14, "text": " The distinct speaker emerges from the noise as a mathematical coherence cluster.", "tokens": [50792, 440, 10644, 8145, 38965, 490, 264, 5658, 382, 257, 18894, 26528, 655, 13630, 13, 51036], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15317757924397787, "compression_ratio": 1.6359649122807018, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888051708966126e-12}, {"id": 625, "seek": 230672, "start": 2320.3799999999997, "end": 2328.66, "text": " It absolutely blows my mind that the exact same mathematical dynamic that governs a horse seamlessly transitioning from a trot into a gallop", "tokens": [51048, 467, 3122, 18458, 452, 1575, 300, 264, 1900, 912, 18894, 8546, 300, 1980, 82, 257, 6832, 38083, 33777, 490, 257, 504, 310, 666, 257, 8527, 404, 51462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15317757924397787, "compression_ratio": 1.6359649122807018, "no_speech_prob": 1.9888051708966126e-12}, {"id": 626, "seek": 232866, "start": 2328.66, "end": 2334.54, "text": " might be the exact same math a computer uses to pick my voice out of a noisy restaurant.", "tokens": [50365, 1062, 312, 264, 1900, 912, 5221, 257, 3820, 4960, 281, 1888, 452, 3177, 484, 295, 257, 24518, 6383, 13, 50659], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16849917676075396, "compression_ratio": 1.5350877192982457, "no_speech_prob": 2.0280283528906207e-12}, {"id": 627, "seek": 232866, "start": 2335.18, "end": 2336.62, "text": " It's incredible to think about.", "tokens": [50691, 467, 311, 4651, 281, 519, 466, 13, 50763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16849917676075396, "compression_ratio": 1.5350877192982457, "no_speech_prob": 2.0280283528906207e-12}, {"id": 628, "seek": 232866, "start": 2336.8199999999997, "end": 2340.96, "text": " The geometry of a galloping leg is the geometry of a separated sound wave.", "tokens": [50773, 440, 18426, 295, 257, 8527, 26125, 1676, 307, 264, 18426, 295, 257, 12005, 1626, 5772, 13, 50980], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16849917676075396, "compression_ratio": 1.5350877192982457, "no_speech_prob": 2.0280283528906207e-12}, {"id": 629, "seek": 232866, "start": 2341.08, "end": 2345.5, "text": " It is a profound structural connection across entirely different domains of physics.", "tokens": [50986, 467, 307, 257, 14382, 15067, 4984, 2108, 7696, 819, 25514, 295, 10649, 13, 51207], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16849917676075396, "compression_ratio": 1.5350877192982457, "no_speech_prob": 2.0280283528906207e-12}, {"id": 630, "seek": 232866, "start": 2346.22, "end": 2350.16, "text": " However, Blexian maintains strict scientific discipline here.", "tokens": [51243, 2908, 11, 363, 2021, 952, 33385, 10910, 8134, 13635, 510, 13, 51440], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16849917676075396, "compression_ratio": 1.5350877192982457, "no_speech_prob": 2.0280283528906207e-12}, {"id": 631, "seek": 232866, "start": 2350.3199999999997, "end": 2350.74, "text": " How so?", "tokens": [51448, 1012, 370, 30, 51469], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16849917676075396, "compression_ratio": 1.5350877192982457, "no_speech_prob": 2.0280283528906207e-12}, {"id": 632, "seek": 235074, "start": 2350.74, "end": 2356.4399999999996, "text": " The paper mentions the cocktail party problem merely to demonstrate that the Kuramoto model is highly versatile.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 3035, 23844, 264, 26382, 3595, 1154, 17003, 281, 11698, 300, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 307, 5405, 25057, 13, 50650], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09322475368141109, "compression_ratio": 1.6987179487179487, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827644742396398e-12}, {"id": 633, "seek": 235074, "start": 2357.2, "end": 2364.22, "text": " It deliberately avoids making the grand sweeping claim that locomotion theory proves anything about human auditory processing.", "tokens": [50688, 467, 23506, 3641, 3742, 1455, 264, 2697, 33285, 3932, 300, 36369, 19228, 5261, 25019, 1340, 466, 1952, 17748, 827, 9007, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09322475368141109, "compression_ratio": 1.6987179487179487, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827644742396398e-12}, {"id": 634, "seek": 235074, "start": 2364.7, "end": 2366.66, "text": " The discipline of this author is really refreshing.", "tokens": [51063, 440, 13635, 295, 341, 3793, 307, 534, 19772, 13, 51161], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09322475368141109, "compression_ratio": 1.6987179487179487, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827644742396398e-12}, {"id": 635, "seek": 235074, "start": 2367.06, "end": 2368.9599999999996, "text": " Blexian doesn't claim to have a theory of everything.", "tokens": [51181, 363, 2021, 952, 1177, 380, 3932, 281, 362, 257, 5261, 295, 1203, 13, 51276], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09322475368141109, "compression_ratio": 1.6987179487179487, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827644742396398e-12}, {"id": 636, "seek": 235074, "start": 2369.5, "end": 2373.64, "text": " The paper explicitly calls out its own blind spots in the open problems section.", "tokens": [51303, 440, 3035, 20803, 5498, 484, 1080, 1065, 6865, 10681, 294, 264, 1269, 2740, 3541, 13, 51510], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09322475368141109, "compression_ratio": 1.6987179487179487, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827644742396398e-12}, {"id": 637, "seek": 235074, "start": 2373.7599999999998, "end": 2374.4799999999996, "text": " It does.", "tokens": [51516, 467, 775, 13, 51552], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09322475368141109, "compression_ratio": 1.6987179487179487, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827644742396398e-12}, {"id": 638, "seek": 235074, "start": 2374.56, "end": 2378.74, "text": " And the biggest blind spot seems to be, well, what happens when we aren't moving rhythmically?", "tokens": [51556, 400, 264, 3880, 6865, 4008, 2544, 281, 312, 11, 731, 11, 437, 2314, 562, 321, 3212, 380, 2684, 11801, 984, 30, 51765], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09322475368141109, "compression_ratio": 1.6987179487179487, "no_speech_prob": 1.7827644742396398e-12}, {"id": 639, "seek": 237874, "start": 2378.74, "end": 2380.8399999999997, "text": " Right, because locomotion is periodic.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 11, 570, 36369, 19228, 307, 27790, 13, 50470], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 640, "seek": 237874, "start": 2381.2599999999998, "end": 2382.72, "text": " Walking is a repeating cycle.", "tokens": [50491, 26964, 307, 257, 18617, 6586, 13, 50564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 641, "seek": 237874, "start": 2383.2599999999998, "end": 2388.8599999999997, "text": " The entire Kuramoto model presupposes a population of oscillating elements that possess a rhythm.", "tokens": [50591, 440, 2302, 16481, 35858, 2316, 1183, 10504, 4201, 257, 4415, 295, 18225, 990, 4959, 300, 17490, 257, 11801, 13, 50871], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 642, "seek": 237874, "start": 2389.2, "end": 2392.3199999999997, "text": " But what if you were simply reaching out to pick up a coffee mug?", "tokens": [50888, 583, 437, 498, 291, 645, 2935, 9906, 484, 281, 1888, 493, 257, 4982, 23610, 30, 51044], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 643, "seek": 237874, "start": 2392.4599999999996, "end": 2392.9399999999996, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51051, 7587, 13, 51075], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 644, "seek": 237874, "start": 2393.2, "end": 2395.3599999999997, "text": " Reaching for a mug is a discrete action.", "tokens": [51088, 1300, 2834, 337, 257, 23610, 307, 257, 27706, 3069, 13, 51196], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 645, "seek": 237874, "start": 2395.9199999999996, "end": 2398.04, "text": " It has a definitive start and a definitive end.", "tokens": [51224, 467, 575, 257, 28152, 722, 293, 257, 28152, 917, 13, 51330], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 646, "seek": 237874, "start": 2398.3799999999997, "end": 2399.18, "text": " It doesn't repeat.", "tokens": [51347, 467, 1177, 380, 7149, 13, 51387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 647, "seek": 237874, "start": 2399.7, "end": 2401.9599999999996, "text": " There is no ongoing rhythm to synchronize.", "tokens": [51413, 821, 307, 572, 10452, 11801, 281, 19331, 1125, 13, 51526], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 648, "seek": 237874, "start": 2402.3799999999997, "end": 2406.18, "text": " So how does the Ampeluus chain handle a discrete reach?", "tokens": [51547, 407, 577, 775, 264, 2012, 20071, 84, 301, 5021, 4813, 257, 27706, 2524, 30, 51737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16049181620279948, "compression_ratio": 1.6173285198555956, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920909339148248e-12}, {"id": 649, "seek": 240618, "start": 2406.18, "end": 2409.52, "text": " The Amist answer from the paper is, we don't know yet.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 2012, 468, 1867, 490, 264, 3035, 307, 11, 321, 500, 380, 458, 1939, 13, 50532], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 650, "seek": 240618, "start": 2409.8399999999997, "end": 2412.0, "text": " It is left as a major open problem.", "tokens": [50548, 467, 307, 1411, 382, 257, 2563, 1269, 1154, 13, 50656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 651, "seek": 240618, "start": 2412.16, "end": 2413.24, "text": " But they have a guess, right?", "tokens": [50664, 583, 436, 362, 257, 2041, 11, 558, 30, 50718], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 652, "seek": 240618, "start": 2413.54, "end": 2415.64, "text": " Fliction does offer a tentative guess.", "tokens": [50733, 3235, 4105, 775, 2626, 257, 7054, 1166, 2041, 13, 50838], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 653, "seek": 240618, "start": 2416.06, "end": 2421.5, "text": " The author suggests that a single discrete movement might act as a mathematically degenerate case", "tokens": [50859, 440, 3793, 13409, 300, 257, 2167, 27706, 3963, 1062, 605, 382, 257, 44003, 40520, 473, 1389, 51131], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 654, "seek": 240618, "start": 2421.5, "end": 2427.04, "text": " where the population size of the oscillators, n, is reduced to exactly one.", "tokens": [51131, 689, 264, 4415, 2744, 295, 264, 18225, 3391, 11, 297, 11, 307, 9212, 281, 2293, 472, 13, 51408], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 655, "seek": 240618, "start": 2427.2, "end": 2427.58, "text": " Oh.", "tokens": [51416, 876, 13, 51435], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 656, "seek": 240618, "start": 2428.1, "end": 2429.3799999999997, "text": " So there is no population.", "tokens": [51461, 407, 456, 307, 572, 4415, 13, 51525], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 657, "seek": 240618, "start": 2429.52, "end": 2431.18, "text": " There's no marching band to synchronize.", "tokens": [51532, 821, 311, 572, 30523, 4116, 281, 19331, 1125, 13, 51615], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17107582092285156, "compression_ratio": 1.5458015267175573, "no_speech_prob": 1.5796968767800568e-12}, {"id": 658, "seek": 243118, "start": 2431.18, "end": 2431.62, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50365, 7587, 13, 50387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 659, "seek": 243118, "start": 2432.2999999999997, "end": 2435.98, "text": " If n equals 1, there is no population coherence to speak of.", "tokens": [50421, 759, 297, 6915, 502, 11, 456, 307, 572, 4415, 26528, 655, 281, 1710, 295, 13, 50605], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 660, "seek": 243118, "start": 2436.3399999999997, "end": 2442.46, "text": " The entire complex operation collapses into a single, instantaneous scaling and rotation of the hands approach vector.", "tokens": [50623, 440, 2302, 3997, 6916, 48765, 666, 257, 2167, 11, 45596, 21589, 293, 12447, 295, 264, 2377, 3109, 8062, 13, 50929], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 661, "seek": 243118, "start": 2442.6, "end": 2444.96, "text": " It's just one guy in a marching band playing a single note.", "tokens": [50936, 467, 311, 445, 472, 2146, 294, 257, 30523, 4116, 2433, 257, 2167, 3637, 13, 51054], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 662, "seek": 243118, "start": 2445.12, "end": 2445.3999999999996, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51062, 1779, 13, 51076], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 663, "seek": 243118, "start": 2445.72, "end": 2450.12, "text": " But it's a hypothesis left entirely for future researchers to prove or disprove.", "tokens": [51092, 583, 309, 311, 257, 17291, 1411, 7696, 337, 2027, 10309, 281, 7081, 420, 717, 46955, 13, 51312], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 664, "seek": 243118, "start": 2450.56, "end": 2453.8399999999997, "text": " Another fascinating open problem was about the assembly index,", "tokens": [51334, 3996, 10343, 1269, 1154, 390, 466, 264, 12103, 8186, 11, 51498], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 665, "seek": 243118, "start": 2454.56, "end": 2458.0, "text": " the mathematical depth of the control hierarchy we talked about earlier,", "tokens": [51534, 264, 18894, 7161, 295, 264, 1969, 22333, 321, 2825, 466, 3071, 11, 51706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 666, "seek": 243118, "start": 2458.18, "end": 2460.68, "text": " where a biped is 1 and a quadruped is 2.", "tokens": [51715, 689, 257, 19016, 292, 307, 502, 293, 257, 10787, 894, 3452, 307, 568, 13, 51840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1303990271783644, "compression_ratio": 1.6234177215189873, "no_speech_prob": 1.5671604639000414e-12}, {"id": 667, "seek": 246068, "start": 2460.68, "end": 2462.08, "text": " Yes, the assembly index.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 11, 264, 12103, 8186, 13, 50435], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12219143805102767, "compression_ratio": 1.7647058823529411, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359704389790064e-12}, {"id": 668, "seek": 246068, "start": 2462.24, "end": 2468.54, "text": " Does the mathematical depth of that hierarchy mirror the actual historical evolution of the animal?", "tokens": [50443, 4402, 264, 18894, 7161, 295, 300, 22333, 8013, 264, 3539, 8584, 9303, 295, 264, 5496, 30, 50758], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12219143805102767, "compression_ratio": 1.7647058823529411, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359704389790064e-12}, {"id": 669, "seek": 246068, "start": 2468.7, "end": 2469.6, "text": " That's a great question.", "tokens": [50766, 663, 311, 257, 869, 1168, 13, 50811], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12219143805102767, "compression_ratio": 1.7647058823529411, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359704389790064e-12}, {"id": 670, "seek": 246068, "start": 2470.18, "end": 2475.3399999999997, "text": " Did biology build the assembly index up layer by layer over millions of years of evolution?", "tokens": [50840, 2589, 14956, 1322, 264, 12103, 8186, 493, 4583, 538, 4583, 670, 6803, 295, 924, 295, 9303, 30, 51098], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12219143805102767, "compression_ratio": 1.7647058823529411, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359704389790064e-12}, {"id": 671, "seek": 246068, "start": 2476.2, "end": 2481.1, "text": " Or does the hierarchy mirror the developmental stages of an embryo growing in the womb?", "tokens": [51141, 1610, 775, 264, 22333, 8013, 264, 30160, 10232, 295, 364, 31588, 78, 4194, 294, 264, 34310, 30, 51386], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12219143805102767, "compression_ratio": 1.7647058823529411, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359704389790064e-12}, {"id": 672, "seek": 246068, "start": 2481.3999999999996, "end": 2481.7, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51401, 1779, 13, 51416], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12219143805102767, "compression_ratio": 1.7647058823529411, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359704389790064e-12}, {"id": 673, "seek": 246068, "start": 2482.04, "end": 2489.72, "text": " Fliction treats the hierarchy synchronically, meaning the paper only analyzes the control structure as it exists right now in the adult animal.", "tokens": [51433, 3235, 4105, 19566, 264, 22333, 19331, 984, 11, 3620, 264, 3035, 787, 6459, 12214, 264, 1969, 3877, 382, 309, 8198, 558, 586, 294, 264, 5075, 5496, 13, 51817], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12219143805102767, "compression_ratio": 1.7647058823529411, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359704389790064e-12}, {"id": 674, "seek": 248972, "start": 2489.72, "end": 2490.9599999999996, "text": " So they don't look at the past?", "tokens": [50365, 407, 436, 500, 380, 574, 412, 264, 1791, 30, 50427], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11464005774194068, "compression_ratio": 1.5440613026819923, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956328276555242e-12}, {"id": 675, "seek": 248972, "start": 2491.22, "end": 2491.62, "text": " No.", "tokens": [50440, 883, 13, 50460], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11464005774194068, "compression_ratio": 1.5440613026819923, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956328276555242e-12}, {"id": 676, "seek": 248972, "start": 2492.24, "end": 2500.48, "text": " Whether that deep mathematical structure is a compressed physical trace of evolutionary history is a massive, unanswered question for evolutionary biologists.", "tokens": [50491, 8503, 300, 2452, 18894, 3877, 307, 257, 30353, 4001, 13508, 295, 27567, 2503, 307, 257, 5994, 11, 517, 43904, 292, 1168, 337, 27567, 3228, 12256, 13, 50903], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11464005774194068, "compression_ratio": 1.5440613026819923, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956328276555242e-12}, {"id": 677, "seek": 248972, "start": 2500.72, "end": 2502.9399999999996, "text": " Well, we have covered a massive amount of ground today.", "tokens": [50915, 1042, 11, 321, 362, 5343, 257, 5994, 2372, 295, 2727, 965, 13, 51026], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11464005774194068, "compression_ratio": 1.5440613026819923, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956328276555242e-12}, {"id": 678, "seek": 248972, "start": 2503.2799999999997, "end": 2506.8399999999997, "text": " We started back in 1911 with Graham Brown's deferent cats,", "tokens": [51043, 492, 1409, 646, 294, 1294, 5348, 365, 22691, 8030, 311, 25704, 317, 11111, 11, 51221], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11464005774194068, "compression_ratio": 1.5440613026819923, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956328276555242e-12}, {"id": 679, "seek": 248972, "start": 2507.2799999999997, "end": 2512.02, "text": " proving that the spine generates its own continuous rhythms without needing sensory triggers.", "tokens": [51243, 27221, 300, 264, 15395, 23815, 1080, 1065, 10957, 44892, 1553, 18006, 27233, 22827, 13, 51480], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11464005774194068, "compression_ratio": 1.5440613026819923, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956328276555242e-12}, {"id": 680, "seek": 251202, "start": 2512.02, "end": 2518.44, "text": " And we moved to roboticists, translating those biological ghosts into coupled oscillators using the Kuramoto model.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 321, 4259, 281, 30468, 1751, 11, 35030, 729, 13910, 21744, 666, 29482, 18225, 3391, 1228, 264, 16481, 35858, 2316, 13, 50686], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14591787629208322, "compression_ratio": 1.4148936170212767, "no_speech_prob": 1.8899484841711223e-12}, {"id": 681, "seek": 251202, "start": 2518.8, "end": 2526.44, "text": " We broke down Tristan Needham's AmplitWist, the complex geometry of scaling and rotation that perfectly maps onto our marching band's synchronization.", "tokens": [50704, 492, 6902, 760, 1765, 7559, 16984, 4822, 311, 2012, 564, 270, 54, 468, 11, 264, 3997, 18426, 295, 21589, 293, 12447, 300, 6239, 11317, 3911, 527, 30523, 4116, 311, 19331, 2144, 13, 51086], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14591787629208322, "compression_ratio": 1.4148936170212767, "no_speech_prob": 1.8899484841711223e-12}, {"id": 682, "seek": 252644, "start": 2526.44, "end": 2540.06, "text": " We examined how those AmplitWist operators stack hierarchically, creating an assembly index that allows a single master equation to generate walks, trots, and gallops simply by turning the dial on phase offsets.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 30972, 577, 729, 2012, 564, 270, 54, 468, 19077, 8630, 35250, 984, 11, 4084, 364, 12103, 8186, 300, 4045, 257, 2167, 4505, 5367, 281, 8460, 12896, 11, 504, 1971, 11, 293, 8527, 3370, 2935, 538, 6246, 264, 5502, 322, 5574, 39457, 1385, 13, 51046], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06495142557534826, "compression_ratio": 1.521551724137931, "no_speech_prob": 1.6813268442425477e-12}, {"id": 683, "seek": 252644, "start": 2540.4, "end": 2549.38, "text": " We shattered a state-centric myth of balance, redefining it not as a frozen x-ray pose, but as juggling a continuously regenerated coherence.", "tokens": [51063, 492, 35209, 257, 1785, 12, 45300, 9474, 295, 4772, 11, 38818, 1760, 309, 406, 382, 257, 12496, 2031, 12, 3458, 10774, 11, 457, 382, 361, 29921, 257, 15684, 26358, 770, 26528, 655, 13, 51512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06495142557534826, "compression_ratio": 1.521551724137931, "no_speech_prob": 1.6813268442425477e-12}, {"id": 684, "seek": 254938, "start": 2549.38, "end": 2555.5, "text": " And finally, we looked at how Fliction fearlessly puts this beautiful theory on the chopping block with the seismic stumble test,", "tokens": [50365, 400, 2721, 11, 321, 2956, 412, 577, 3235, 4105, 4240, 12048, 8137, 341, 2238, 5261, 322, 264, 35205, 3461, 365, 264, 40159, 299, 41302, 1500, 11, 50671], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10759801410493397, "compression_ratio": 1.6982456140350877, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111249262472984e-12}, {"id": 685, "seek": 254938, "start": 2555.96, "end": 2561.9, "text": " challenging empirical biomechanists to prove the geometry wrong using data sitting on their hardwaves right now.", "tokens": [50694, 7595, 31886, 3228, 423, 3484, 1751, 281, 7081, 264, 18426, 2085, 1228, 1412, 3798, 322, 641, 1152, 86, 5423, 558, 586, 13, 50991], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10759801410493397, "compression_ratio": 1.6982456140350877, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111249262472984e-12}, {"id": 686, "seek": 254938, "start": 2562.1, "end": 2564.38, "text": " It is a remarkable piece of theoretical synthesis.", "tokens": [51001, 467, 307, 257, 12802, 2522, 295, 20864, 30252, 13, 51115], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10759801410493397, "compression_ratio": 1.6982456140350877, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111249262472984e-12}, {"id": 687, "seek": 254938, "start": 2564.88, "end": 2571.92, "text": " And as Fliction notes in the closing remarks, even if the geometric AmplitWist reading ultimately fails the empirical foot strike or stumble tests,", "tokens": [51140, 400, 382, 3235, 4105, 5570, 294, 264, 10377, 19151, 11, 754, 498, 264, 33246, 2012, 564, 270, 54, 468, 3760, 6284, 18199, 264, 31886, 2671, 9302, 420, 41302, 6921, 11, 51492], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10759801410493397, "compression_ratio": 1.6982456140350877, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111249262472984e-12}, {"id": 688, "seek": 254938, "start": 2572.4, "end": 2574.78, "text": " the foundational biological truth remains.", "tokens": [51516, 264, 32195, 13910, 3494, 7023, 13, 51635], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10759801410493397, "compression_ratio": 1.6982456140350877, "no_speech_prob": 1.8111249262472984e-12}, {"id": 689, "seek": 257478, "start": 2574.78, "end": 2580.78, "text": " Yes. Movement is generated by continuous rhythmic histories, not by stacking discrete frozen poses.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 26523, 307, 10833, 538, 10957, 46967, 30631, 11, 406, 538, 41376, 27706, 12496, 26059, 13, 50665], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14217663847881815, "compression_ratio": 1.58984375, "no_speech_prob": 1.957980218930677e-12}, {"id": 690, "seek": 257478, "start": 2581.1200000000003, "end": 2587.1200000000003, "text": " Before we wrap up, I want to leave you with one final thought, building on this idea of continuous self-regenerating histories.", "tokens": [50682, 4546, 321, 7019, 493, 11, 286, 528, 281, 1856, 291, 365, 472, 2572, 1194, 11, 2390, 322, 341, 1558, 295, 10957, 2698, 12, 265, 21848, 990, 30631, 13, 50982], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14217663847881815, "compression_ratio": 1.58984375, "no_speech_prob": 1.957980218930677e-12}, {"id": 691, "seek": 257478, "start": 2588.02, "end": 2594.36, "text": " If our very movement is driven by coupled rhythms rather than a stored archive of physical poses,", "tokens": [51027, 759, 527, 588, 3963, 307, 9555, 538, 29482, 44892, 2831, 813, 257, 12187, 23507, 295, 4001, 26059, 11, 51344], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14217663847881815, "compression_ratio": 1.58984375, "no_speech_prob": 1.957980218930677e-12}, {"id": 692, "seek": 257478, "start": 2594.98, "end": 2597.8, "text": " how does this reshape our understanding of muscle memory?", "tokens": [51375, 577, 775, 341, 725, 42406, 527, 3701, 295, 8679, 4675, 30, 51516], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14217663847881815, "compression_ratio": 1.58984375, "no_speech_prob": 1.957980218930677e-12}, {"id": 693, "seek": 257478, "start": 2597.88, "end": 2598.84, "text": " Oh, that's interesting.", "tokens": [51520, 876, 11, 300, 311, 1880, 13, 51568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14217663847881815, "compression_ratio": 1.58984375, "no_speech_prob": 1.957980218930677e-12}, {"id": 694, "seek": 259884, "start": 2598.84, "end": 2603.6400000000003, "text": " Like when we spend hours practicing a golf swing or repeating a scale on the piano,", "tokens": [50365, 1743, 562, 321, 3496, 2496, 11350, 257, 12880, 11173, 420, 18617, 257, 4373, 322, 264, 9211, 11, 50605], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 695, "seek": 259884, "start": 2603.6400000000003, "end": 2609.88, "text": " are we actually physically tuning the coupling offsets in an internal AmplitWist chain?", "tokens": [50605, 366, 321, 767, 9762, 15164, 264, 37447, 39457, 1385, 294, 364, 6920, 2012, 564, 270, 54, 468, 5021, 30, 50917], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 696, "seek": 259884, "start": 2610.26, "end": 2611.02, "text": " That would make sense.", "tokens": [50936, 663, 576, 652, 2020, 13, 50974], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 697, "seek": 259884, "start": 2611.1400000000003, "end": 2615.96, "text": " And if so, could certain neurological movement disorders be viewed entirely differently?", "tokens": [50980, 400, 498, 370, 11, 727, 1629, 48185, 3963, 20261, 312, 19174, 7696, 7614, 30, 51221], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 698, "seek": 259884, "start": 2616.32, "end": 2621.2000000000003, "text": " Maybe they are at a hardware failure of the limbs or a corrupted software file of stored poses in the brain.", "tokens": [51239, 2704, 436, 366, 412, 257, 8837, 7763, 295, 264, 29315, 420, 257, 39480, 4722, 3991, 295, 12187, 26059, 294, 264, 3567, 13, 51483], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 699, "seek": 259884, "start": 2621.36, "end": 2621.6800000000003, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51491, 1779, 13, 51507], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 700, "seek": 259884, "start": 2621.86, "end": 2625.2400000000002, "text": " Maybe they are simply a localized desyncing of this internal chain.", "tokens": [51516, 2704, 436, 366, 2935, 257, 44574, 730, 2534, 2175, 295, 341, 6920, 5021, 13, 51685], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 701, "seek": 259884, "start": 2625.3, "end": 2625.52, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51688, 865, 13, 51699], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12837287599006586, "compression_ratio": 1.6366782006920415, "no_speech_prob": 1.7551417133901404e-12}, {"id": 702, "seek": 262552, "start": 2625.52, "end": 2629.14, "text": " A tragic inability of the joints to hear the rhythm of the marching band.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 20385, 33162, 295, 264, 19949, 281, 1568, 264, 11801, 295, 264, 30523, 4116, 13, 50546], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}, {"id": 703, "seek": 262552, "start": 2629.52, "end": 2634.6, "text": " Viewing motor disorders as a collapse of internal coherence rather than a failure of physical states", "tokens": [50565, 13909, 278, 5932, 20261, 382, 257, 15584, 295, 6920, 26528, 655, 2831, 813, 257, 7763, 295, 4001, 4368, 50819], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}, {"id": 704, "seek": 262552, "start": 2634.6, "end": 2638.54, "text": " could open entirely new avenues for therapy and neural rehabilitation.", "tokens": [50819, 727, 1269, 7696, 777, 43039, 337, 9492, 293, 18161, 33700, 13, 51016], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}, {"id": 705, "seek": 262552, "start": 2639.42, "end": 2640.66, "text": " It is a profound question.", "tokens": [51060, 467, 307, 257, 14382, 1168, 13, 51122], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}, {"id": 706, "seek": 262552, "start": 2640.94, "end": 2643.92, "text": " Definitely something to ponder the next time you go for a walk.", "tokens": [51136, 12151, 746, 281, 280, 8548, 264, 958, 565, 291, 352, 337, 257, 1792, 13, 51285], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}, {"id": 707, "seek": 262552, "start": 2644.34, "end": 2649.48, "text": " Just feel that continuous invisible rhythm generating your path millimeter by millimeter.", "tokens": [51306, 1449, 841, 300, 10957, 14603, 11801, 17746, 428, 3100, 17942, 538, 17942, 13, 51563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}, {"id": 708, "seek": 262552, "start": 2650.2599999999998, "end": 2653.5, "text": " Thank you for joining us on this deep dive into the geometry of locomotion.", "tokens": [51602, 1044, 291, 337, 5549, 505, 322, 341, 2452, 9192, 666, 264, 18426, 295, 36369, 19228, 13, 51764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}, {"id": 709, "seek": 262552, "start": 2653.78, "end": 2654.92, "text": " We'll see you next time.", "tokens": [51778, 492, 603, 536, 291, 958, 565, 13, 51835], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1621136950631427, "compression_ratio": 1.689102564102564, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967615242864277e-12}], "language": "en"}
